on to express and promote its unique socio-cultural identity and also to meet the challenges of the times. There are moments in history when a new direction has to be given to an age-old process. That moment is today and education is the highway to that goal.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We have a firm belief that all wisdom is not concentrated in the reports of various commissions and committees. An ordinary person having common sense can come out with better solutions of the problems in this field. The present issue of the journal is more truth-oriented. It is not figure oriented. Every one knows that figures available in the field of education are inflated at different levels.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em><strong>It is a refereed and peer reviewed journal.</strong></em></p>\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 26px;\">Content unavailable at this movement.</span></p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 26px;\">Content unavailable at this movement.</span></p>\r\n',NULL,'2013-09-19 05:20:24'),(13,'10','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	International&nbsp;<strong><u>Journal</u></strong>&nbsp;of Science and Engineering <strong>(IJSE)</strong> &nbsp;is a journal for the publication of peer reviewed, original research for all aspects of science and engineering. Critical review articles are also welcome; submission of these is strongly encouraged. The journal provides a&nbsp;<strong><u>forum</u></strong>&nbsp;for the discussion of the applied scientific and engineering development and review of traditional indicator approaches for sustainable development.&nbsp;The International Journal of Science and Engineering <strong>(IJSE)</strong> is an international&nbsp;research&nbsp;journal, which publishes top-level work on sciences and engineering. The Journal IJSE is a direct successor of the Journal ITMSC with the aim of publishing papers in all areas of the science and engineering. The Journal also seeks to publish papers on new developments of scientific methods, especially those that have relevance to more than one field of application and also new techniques suggested by particular applications. Longer papers which survey recent progress in topical fields of science and engineering and their applications are also published. IJSE publishes original research papers, review articles, survey articles, book reviews, dissertation abstracts in all areas of engineering and sciences including chemistry, physics, mathematics, zoology, botany, microbiology, biotechnology, geology, pharmaceuticals, agricultural, environment and their broad range of applications.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	<em><strong>It is a refereed and peer reviewed journal.</strong></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	<strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">IJSE A</strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">ims to:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:14.2pt;\">\r\n	&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Promote the cause of advanced study and research and to effect coordination of research and investigations in all disciplines of science and engineering.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:14.2pt;\">\r\n	&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Promote&nbsp;<strong>exchange</strong>&nbsp;of ideas amongst the scientists, researchers, technologists belonging to various facets like engineering, chemistry, physics, mathematics, zoology, botany, microbiology, biotechnology, pharmaceuticals, ecology, geologists, environment, water management&nbsp;<em>etc</em>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:14.2pt;\">\r\n	&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The main aim is to improve our capacity to represent, understand, predict or manage the behavior of&nbsp;<strong>scientific systems</strong>&nbsp;at all practical scales, and to communicate those improvements to a wide scientific and professional audience.</p>\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>\r\n	IJSE cover aspects of science and applications of systems - oriented ideas to the physical, biological, social, technological&nbsp; and behavioral sciences. Journal will publish research articles and reviews within the whole field of Sciences, and it will continue to provide information on the latest trends and developments.The International Journal of Science and Engineering <strong>(IJSE)</strong> publishes high quality, original papers, review papers, technical notes, and book reviews that contribute to the methodology of science and engineering.IJSE will act as a platform to encourage further research in science and engineering, optimization, validations and their applications. IJSE helps to&nbsp;professionals, academics, researchers and practitioners, working in science and engineering field, their research output and applications in the rise economy and society, to discuss of important thought, concepts and expand&nbsp;information.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><em>Topics covered</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please review the subject matter given below to determine in which section your manuscript is appropriate for the <strong>IJSE.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chemistry, Zoology, Botany, Biotechnology, Agricultural Research, Microbiology, Aquatic Science, Mathematics, Pharmaceuticals, Ayurveda, Biodiversity, Biochemistry Research, Biotechnology &amp; Molecular, Different aspects of Modeling and engineering, Engineering ,Ecology, Environmental Impact Assessment, Environmental policies, Ethno botany, Medicinal Plant Research, Natural resources, Occupational safety and industrial hygiene, Quality&nbsp; Control and Quality Assurance, Pollution, Pure &amp; Applied Chemistry, Analytical/Industrial Chemistry, Scientific Research, Total Quality management, Wildlife biology and other disciplines related to science, engineering and environment.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><em>The following contributions will be accepted</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Original research papers&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Review articles</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Special themed issues</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Short notes and case studies</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Viewpoint articles&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Letters to the Editor</p>\r\n','<div>\r\n	INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE AUTHORS</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Preparation of Manuscript</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	 Manuscript must be type written on one side, with double spacing, with wide margin on all sides on A4</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	paper format and page numbers should appear on the right top of pages.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	 Authors are requested to send the</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	manuscript online.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Title/Abstract/Keywords</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	 The title of the paper should be typed in capital, bold face letters. It should be short, specific and</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	informative. Please write name (s) of authors (s) in bold face followed by address (es) in italics and</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	them e-mail address (es).</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	 The titles of the Sections, Abstract, Acknowledgement, References should be typed centered in capital</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	bold face.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	 An abstract not exceeding 200 words should be typed in italics. It should not contain bibliographical</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	references or references of the figures or abbreviations.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	 Two to five keywords clarifying the subject of the manuscript should be given below the abstract in</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	alphabetical order.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	 Citation in the text should be in the form Kilbas and Saigo [8], Prudnikov et al. [11]. Equations should</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	be numbered according to the section at the right hand side as (1.1), (1.2), (2.1) etc.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	References</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	References should be given at the end of the paper in alphabetical order of the surname of the author in</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	the following way:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	(i) Books</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Atkinson, J.W., (1964). An Introduction to Motivation, Van Nostrand, Princeton.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	(ii) Journals</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Rivlin, R.S. and Ericksen, J.L., (1995). Stress deformation relations for isotropic materials, J. Rat.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Mech. Anal., 4,323.</div>\r\n',NULL,'2014-10-14 21:18:09');
