INSERT INTO `paper_published` VALUES (1,'OPTIMAL POLICIES IN FUZZY ENVIRONMENT FOR THE RETAILER WITH DEFECTIVE LOT AND TRADE CREDIT  ','Due to the gradual shifting of production system in-control to out-control the product which manufactured contains the defective product also. When the manufacturer sold this item to the retailer and retailer sold it directly without inspected it, their goodwill may be lost in market. So it is advisable for the retailer to maintain their goodwill they must first inspect the items and defective products, must repair before to sell it. This phenomenon we consider in our model formulation. As we know that to maintain in market manufacturer used different proposal which attract the retailer one of this is trade credit. So, we are going to discuss the effect of this in our proposed model. As we know that costs which include in inventory are imprecise and vague in nature. So for making this model more realistic we consider all the costs parameters fuzzy in nature.  ','','-  ','  S.R. Singh, Rachna Kumari, Dharmendra Yadav  ','1-14    ','NO','19 ITMSC.11.docx','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(3,'FUZZY INVENTORY MODEL FOR FINITE RATE OF REPLENISHMENT USING SIGNED DISTANCE METHOD   ','In the present paper an EPQ model is discussed in fuzzy environment. Costs involved i.e. set-up cost and holding cost is taken as the fuzzy parameters. Both the costs are represented by fuzzy triangular numbers. Optimum lot size is calculated using signed distance method for defuzzification. Finally a numerical example along with sensitivity analysis is given to illustrate the model.   ','','-   ','   S. R. Singh, C. Singh   ','27-34      ','NO','17 ITMSC.11.docx','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(4,'Text Hiding Using BMP Images An Steganography Approach','Steganography, the idea of hiding messages and data within other pieces of data, can be useful in many real-world applications alongside encryption and other code-writing methods. Steganography often are used in conjunction with cryptography so that the information is doubly protected; first it is encrypted and then hidden so that an adversary has to first find the information and then decrypt it. A very generic description of the pieces of the steganographic process: cover_medium (BMP Images) + hidden_text + stego_key = stego_medium. Steganography is used to hide the occurrence of communication. The method described of steganography known as least significant bit substitution, in which the pieces of a message are hidden within the actual binary data of a computer file. Text is hidden by adding or altering insignificant bits of information of a file. An algorithm designed to embed a text message might slightly alter information describing the RGB composition of a pixel for an image file.','','-','Uruj Jaleel, Sharad Saxena, Jagdish Chandra Patni and Himanshu Choudhary','1-12','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(5,'A Two Non-identical Unit Standby System Model with Different Repair/Replacement Policies and Repair Machine Failure','The present paper deals with the analysis of a two non-identical unit standby system model with repair machine failure. Here p-unit has three modes  normal, quasi-normal and total failure while o-unit is non-reparable with two modes normal and total failure. The repair of failed p-unit is done by repair machine (RM) while the failed RM is repaired by a repairman. The replacement of the failed units is done by a replacement facility. The different measures of systems effectiveness are obtained by using regenerative point technique.','','-','Aqil Ahmad , Lakhan Singh and Gaurav Varshney','13-22','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(6,'gp-REGULAR AND gp-NORMAL SPACES IN TOPOLOGICAL AND BITOPOLOGICAL SPAES  ','In this paper we generalized g-regular and g-normal spaces in topological and bitopological spaces using pre-open sets by the name of gp-regular, gp-normal spaces, pairwise gp-regular, pairwise, gp-normal spaces.  ','','-  ','  V.K.Sharma & Yogesh Kumar  ','35-44    ','NO','16 ITMSC.11.docx','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(7,'RAYLEIGH-TAYLOR INSTABILITY OF WALTERS (MODEL B\') VISCO-ELASTIC DUSTY PLASMA IN THE PRESENCE OF VARIABLE MAGNETIC FIELD THROUGH POROUS MEDIUM','The Rayleigh-Taylor instability of Walters (Model B\') visco-elastic dusty plasma in the presence of variable magnetic field in porous medium has been investigated. Upon application of normal mode techniques, the dispersion equation is obtained. The important results obtained in this paper include the instability of non-oscillatory modes and the stability of oscillatory modes. Also found that system is stable for   and unstable for   under certain conditions. Also, the instability of the plane interface between two visco-elastic superposed fluids has been investigated. The important result is for  , the system is stable under certain conditions.','','-','Vivek Kumar , Rimple Pundir, S. P. Singh and Sudhir Kumar Pundir','45-58','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(8,'POLICY DECISIONS FOR A STOCK DEPENDENT DEMAND RATE INVENTORY MODEL WITH PROGRESSIVE PERMISSIBLE DELAY IN PAYMENT','In this paper, we developed an EOQ inventory model to formulate optimal ordering policies for supplier who offers two progressive permissible delay periods to the retailer to settle his/her account. We assumed that the demand rate is partially constant and partially dependent on the stock with constant rate of deterioration and time-varying holding cost. Shortages in inventory are allowed which is fully backlogged. An algorithm is given to find the flow of optimal ordering policy. The results are illustrated with the help of numerical example.','','-','R. K. Pandey , Mukesh Kumar and Pankaj Kumar','59-74','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(9,'NEARLY   ?  -REFINABLE SPACES','In the present paper, a new class of topological spaces, namely, the class of nearly  -refinable spaces has been introduced. This class contains the class of  -refinable spaces. Several characterizations and properties of nearly  ? -refinable spaces are investigated.','','-','V.K. SHARMA','75-86','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(10,'AN OPTIMAL INVENTORY MODEL FOR VARIABLE RATE OF DETERIORATION AND ALTERNATING PRODUCTION RATES WITH EXPONENTIALLY DECLINING DEMEND','In this paper items are produced at different rates during sub-period with exponentially decreasing demand. The deterioration is taken as special form of Weibull density function for time allowing shortage. In all cycle special cases are discussed.','','-','Anil Kumar Sharma , Madhu Goyal, Ravi Kant Sharma','87-94','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(11,'Availability and Frequency Measures of a Two Unit Non-Identical Parallel System.','This paper deals with the presence of Lethal Common Cause Shock failures (LCCS failures) as well as NCCS failures in addition to individual failures in the system reliability analysis. The model considers the two component non  identical parallel system, which is under the influence of lethal as well as non-lethal common cause shock failures in addition to individual failures. The system reliability indices, viz., the availability and frequency of failures are developed for a repairable system which is affected by common cause shock failures in addition to individual failures. Numerical results are also presented in this paper.','','-','G. Y. Sagar, Y. Raghunatha Reddy, S.Madhusudana Verma','95-102','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(12,'Queuing Discipline to reduc Connection-Tracking Flaws in Protocols That uses Quantum Periodicity for Scalable Network Services.','In this paper, authors argue a mechanism for preventing intermediate session tracking, during subsystem interaction with kernel (main system). QdQp (Queuing discipline with Quantum periodicity) interacts via privileged PID (unique process identifier) either to track session records (e.g. TCP-traffic) to analyze and check the authorization/authentication policies. Based on results, it invokes command signals/processes to allow or drop that sessions further transmissions. As a intrusion point of view whenever QdQp interacts with kernel, there might be a possibility that Communicating/requesting service stopped /killed accidentally or forcefully by another process-service (this service might be initiated /generated intentionally by intruder) and at same time intruder runs another process with same PID as QdQps process; to track same session for analyzing details for sophistication, either by internal user with low privileges or by externals-intruders. This subsystem implements different Qubits of Classes for local processes and public processes, to prevent erudition either by local process itself or with support/help from trozen horses. QdQp processes maintain start and stop semaphores in Dqueue structure before passing through mangling hooks. The semaphore locks return non-negative values, to prevent hook accesses with time slot boundaries.','','-','M.P. Singh, Monika and Pradeep Yadav','103-122','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(13,'Two Warehouse Inventory Model for Deteriorating Items with Shortages Under the Conditions of Permissible Delay in Payments.','In this paper, a deterministic inventory model for deteriorating items with two warehouses and shortages is developed. The conditions of permissible delay in payments are also taken into consideration. A rented warehouse is used when the ordering quantity exceeds the limited capacity of the owned warehouse, and it is assumed the deterioration rates of items in the two warehouses may be different. In addition, shortages are neither completely backlogged nor completely lost assuming the backlogging rate to the inversely proportional to the waiting time for the next replenishment. We obtain the condition when to rent the warehouse and provide simple solution procedures for finding the minimum total cost per unit time. We presented special cases of this model. In one of the case we considered that the capacity of OW is infinite so there is no need of rented warehouse. In other case we consider that deterioration is not allowed and shortage are allowed and completely backlogged','','-','S.R. Singh, Neeraj Kumar, Rachna Kumar','123-134','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(14,'Meir-Keeler Type Fixed Point Theorems in Fuzzy Metric Space','This work is intended to find out a fixed point theorem in fuzzy metric space using the  contractive condition, however, without using the continuity of the mappings. In this paper, we first formulate an contractive condition in the setting of a fuzzy metric space and then apply it to prove fixed point theorems. We thus find out an affirmative answer to the problem of Rhoades [9] in fuzzy metric space. The following results can be seen as fuzzy analogue of the results of Pant [6].','','-','S. Padaliya, Vyomesh Pant and Achin Jain','135-140','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(15,'An Integrated Production Inventory Model with Expiration Date and Uncertain Lead time in a Supply Chain','This paper analyses a perishable inventory system with expiration date, available capital constraints and uncertain lead time for items. The objectives of this study is to develop the model of season pattern demand with product expiration date when the product in stock deterioration with time. Numerical illustrations of sensitivity analysis with regard to different parameter are also provided.','','-','S.R. Singh, Urvashi, Vikas Sharma','141-156','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(16,'Policy Decisions for Perishable Products with Ramp-Type Demand and Random Rate of Deterioration.','This paper deals with the development of a model for deteriorating seasonal products with time dependent ramp-type demand function. Random deterioration rate is considered and shortages are not allowed. Linear increasing holding cost is also assumed. The running cost of the system for the entire season is derived and minimized by determining the optimal ordering quantity of the system.','','-','Anand Chauhan, Harikishan, A. P. Singh','157-166','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2013-07-23 17:35:19','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(18,'C Estimation of Order Statistics for Inverse Generalized Exponential Distribution','In this paper we establish some distributional properties of the Inverse Generalized Exponential Distribution. In this paper we introduce a new probability distribution. We developed the marginal joint distribution for minimum and maximum order statistic. It also proved the moments of order statistics from Inverse Generalized Exponential distribution. Further, moments and inverse moments of single order statistics are deduced from the product moments. Here we also derive the conditional distributions of first order Statistic and the nth order statistic of Inverse Exponential distribution','','-','M. Shuaib Khan','23-29','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(19,'a-s-Closedness of Fuzzy Topological Spaces','The prime objective of this paper is to introduce a compact-like notion on FTS called -closedness and characterize such property in terms of finite intersection property (FIP), ordinary nets and filters','','-','Pankaj Chettri','31-35','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(20,'Incorporating BB84 in the Mutual Authentication & Key Management in IEEE 802.11i : The Quantum Cryptographic Handshake','Quantum Mechanics as a Quantum cryptography can be a solution for providing fool proof security in wireless networks in future. Our endeavour is to incorporate this technology in wireless local area networks (WLANs). Various experiments have been done to distribute quantum keys in free space, though these experiments are in nascent stage. Therefore it is a better idea to implement this concept in WLAN as compared to Mobile Networks as the WLAN stations are relatively static compared to mobile stations and not far apart. In thi