mand rate is the linear function of time. In this paper we have done all work in the environment of permissible delay of payments. A number of structural properties of the inventory system are studied analytically. We have discussed the minimum total system cost under the condition of permissible delay is relaxed to that at the end of the credit period, the retailer will make a partial payment on total purchasing cost to the supplier and pay off the remaining balance by loan from the bank. Numerical examples are taken to illustrate the procedure of finding the optimal total inventory cost and production cycle time. Sensitivity analysis is carried out to demonstrate the effects of changing parameter values on the optimal solution of the system.','','-','S. R. Singh and Narayan Singh','73-82','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(24,'Bayesian Estimation of a Complex Repairable System Under Different Loss Functions','In this paper, we consider a 1out-of-N:G repairable system with an assumption that repair hazard rate increases monotonically as time parameter increases. The object of the present paper is to obtain Bayes estimator of the scale parameter and reliability function under different loss function with vague priors besides it is an increasing function of ?. A numerical example is given.','','-','Sanku Dey','83-92','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(25,'Effect of Radiation on MHD Free Convection Flow near the Lower Stagnation Point of a Porous Isothermal','The free convection MHD flow of an incompressible, viscous fluid with temperature dependent viscosity and temperature dependent thermal conductivity in the presence of radiation, near the lower stagnation point of porous circular cylinder has been studied. The cylinder was assumed to be isothermal. The governing equations of motion and energy are coupled non-linear partial differential equations. These equations have been transformed into a system of non-dimensional coupled non-linear ordinary differential equations by using similarity transformations and solved by using Runge-Kutta and shooting method. Velocity profile and temperature distribution for the flow have been presented for various values of radiation parameter, viscosity variation parameter, thermal conductivity variation parameter, magnetic parameter, porosity parameter and Prandtl number. The skin friction factor and local Nusselt number are also calculated for these parameters. It has been observed that with the increase in radiation parameter the velocity and temperature both decrease','','-','Ziya Uddin, Manoj Kumar and Vandana Bisht','93-101','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(26,'An Order Level Model with Variable Demand and Partial Backlogging with the Permissible Delay in Payments','Classical EOQ models assume that the payment of order quantity is made on the basis of the receipt of items by the inventory systems. However, in reality suppliers usually offer their customers a certain credit period for settling the account. In such cases, there is no interest charged if the account is settled with in the permissible delay period. Beyond this period, the supplier will charge a certain interest. In many cases customers are conditioned to a shipping delay, and may be willing to wait for a short time in order to get their first choice. Generally speaking, the length of the waiting time for the next replenishment is the main factor for deciding whether the backlogging will be accepted or not. The willingness of a customer to wait for backlogging during a shortage period declines with the length the waiting time. In this study a