uter','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(29,'Note on Vorticity MHD Flow of Viscous Fluid Past Impulsively Moving Isothermal Vertical Porous Medium with Chemical Reaction and Heat Source','The problem deals with the study of vorticity of flow an electrically conducting incompressible viscous fluid past an impulsively moving isothermal vertical plate through porous medium with chemical reaction and heat source in the presence of uniform suction, the vorticity profiles are studied for various different parameters. The results obtained are discussed with the help of graphs','','-','Giri Raj Gupta and Alok Darshan Kothiyal','131-135','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(30,'Demographic Study of SAARC Countries','Demographic parameters as population growth, C.B.R., C.D.R., I.M.R., expectation of life, median age and percentage of urban population of SAARC countries in various years and its comparison with others less development countries in various years have been studied. This study is based on the data \"`World of demographic estimates and projection, 1950-2050, united nations, New York, 1988. The study revealed that the population growth rate in SAARC countries is lower than the growth rate in less development regions because the mortality level in SAARC countries is higher than the less development countries. All the SAARC countries except Sri Lanka and India for some values have less favourable demographic value than corresponding value of less development countries. Also some demographic parameters such as mortality rates, infant mortality rates, expectation of life etc. of Sri Lanka are close to the developed countries.','','-','G. S. Yadav, Sushil Kumar Yadav and Sanjay Kumar','137-146','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(31,'An Approximate Method of Investigating the Highest Waves at the Interface of Two Different Homogeneous Liquids','Highest waves on the interface of two heavy homogeneous liquids in which the density of the upper liquids is less than of the lower one are obtained by Michell method. An approximate method is developed to find the ratio of its height to the wave length (h/?) for density ratio d (0 = d < 1). The value of (h/?) found approximately equal to 0.138 as against 0.142 found by Michell.','','-','Prabir Kumar Shrivastava, Sunny Verma, Deepika Sonal and Praveen Kumar','147-156','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(32,'An Order level Inventory Model for Decaying Items with Ramp Type Demand and Partial Backlogging','An EOQ inventory model is developed for variable rate of deterioration having a ramp type demand rate. In this demand, demand decreases exponentially for the same initial period and become steady later on. Now-a-days, a customer neither has the patience nor the requirement to wait for the seller to replenish his stock. This result in lost sales of the seller. So in this model, shortages are occurring with partial backlogging. Backlogging rate is considered as exponential decreasing function of time. The effect of inflation and variable holding cost are also considered. Numerical illustrations are also discussed.','','-','M. M. Sharma, V. C. Goel and R. K. Yadav','157-166','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','2','2','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(33,'Studies on Intrusion Detection System & Scope in Computer Crimes','Past few years have witnessed a growing recognition of intelligent techniques for the construction of efficient and reliable internet content blocking systems. 