,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(38,'On Increasing Convex Functions','We study some growth properties of the functions  and U, where  is an increasing convex function of a and','','-','Mangey Ram* and Satendra K.Vaish','17-21','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','3','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(39,'On The Cutoff Characteristics of A Metallic Sheath Helix Cladded Chirofiber','An analytical study of an optical fiber having a chiral core and surrounded by a dielectric medium with a metallic sheath helix at the core cladding boundary is presented. The characteristic equation for the system is derived and the cutoff conditions for the various modes have been solved analytically. Interestingly the pitch angle of the metallic sheath helix has no effect on the cutoff behaviour of various modes of the fiber.','','-','Sushil Kumar, U.N. Singh and Kh. S. Singh','23-32','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','3','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(40,'Two-Warehouse Perishable Inventory Model With Xponential Demand and Partial Backlogging','In the present study two warehouse inventory models have been developed with LIFO and FIFO dispatching policies. Deterioration rates are taken as linear function of time for both the warehouses. Shortages are allowed and partially backlogged in the models. Demand rate is taken as the exponential increasing function of time and the production rate is taken as demand dependent.','','-','Shiv Raj Singh and Tarun Jeet Singh','33-48','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','3','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(41,'Regression Analysis of Ground Water Quality of Nimrana Industrial Area, Alwar (Raj.)','The paper deals with study of water quality parameters in handpump and pond water near Nimrana industrial area. The samples were 