d. The production rate has been specified as demand dependent to take into consideration the market forces also. Optimal solution for proposed model is derived.','','-','Deepa Sinha and Diksha','73-86','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','3','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(44,'Electronic-Government in Saudi Arabia : A Positive Revolution in The Peninsula','The informatization practice of countries all over the world has shown that the level of a government\'s informatization is one main factor that can affect its international competitive power. At present, e-government construction is regarded as one of the most important tasks for the national economy and society upliftment and informatization in Saudi Arabia. Unlike the traditional governments, an e-government takes on a new look with its framework and operation mode more suitable for the contemporary era. In fact, it is a basic national strategy to promote Saudi Arabias informatization by means of e-government construction. This talk firstly introduces the basic concepts and relevant viewpoints of e-government, then reviews the development process of e-government in Saudi Arabia, and describes the current states, development strategies of e-government in Saudi Arabia. And also review e-government maturity models and synthesize them e-government maturity models are investigated, in which the authors have proposed the Delloites six-stage model, Layne and Lee four-stage model and Accenture five-stage model. So, the main e-government maturity stages are: online presence, interaction, transaction, transformation and digital democracy. After that, according to many references, the main technologies which are used in each stage are summarized.','','-','Omar S. Al-Mushayt, Kashiful Haq and Yusuf Perwej','87-98','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','3','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(45,'Quantile Analysis of The Inverse Weibull Distribution','This paper presents the Quantile analysis of the inverse Weibull distribution also the properties of the Quantile analysis as the percentile life used B-life in engineering terminology. The main interests are in the relationship between and various B-lives; measure of variability for B-lives as the numerical quantities that describe the spread of the values in a set of data. Here these quantiles models presented graphically and mathematically.','','-','M. Shuaib Khan, G.R Pasha and Ahmed Hesham Pasha','99-112','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','3','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(46,'Thermosolutal Instability of Couple-Stress Rotating Fluid in The Presence of Magnetic Field','The problem of thermosolutal instability of a couple-stress rotating fluid is considered in the presence of magnetic field. It is found that magnetic field and couple-stress has both stabilizing and destabilizing effect under certain conditions whereas stable solute gradient and rotation have a stabilizing effect on the thermal convection when gravity increase upwards from its value . Graphs also have been plotted by giving some numerical values to the parameters. It is also found that oscillatory modes are introduced due to the presence of rotation and magnetic field and stable solute gradient which were non-existent in their absence.','','-','Vivek Kumar, Abhilasha and Sudhir Kumar Pundir','113-124','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','3','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(47,'A New Form of Marketing Myopia','Since the introduction of Marketing Myopia many things have been written on it. It appears myopia relate to several types of narrow mindedness. The purpose of this paper is to throw light on that change in product or promotions can sustain the brand even in the light of emerging competition. This paper will briefly review the different explanations of Marketing Myopia. It covers the last two decades of Indian market perspective.','','-','Nidhi Tandon','125-131','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(48,'Bioremediation Of Waste Water Collected From Pharmaceutical Industry','Wastes produced from pharmaceutical research and development includes halogenated and non-halogenated solvents, acids, bases and oxidizers. Biopharmaceutical research also generates significant amounts of waste materials, including biological and medical wastes. The pollution by these industries can be minimized by material substitution, process modifications, spill preservation etc. But still there are some wastes which are indispensable. Bioremediation is one of the ways for the treatment of such waste products in large scale. Various samples having different characteristics from different industries (Dabur India Limited, Maharashi Arvind Pharmaceutical Ltd. (M.A.P.L), Paras India Ltd) are being considered. An assumption was made that the micro-organism isolated from the environment if inoculated again in the same environment, they adapt well to it and, hence can use the pollutants for the fulfillment of their nutritional needs and, thus can fix them. Gram positive and Gram negative bacterias, fungus and yeasts have been isolated from these water samples. Suspension and immobilized culture of these microbes have been utilized for bioremediation. Drastic changes in the water quality (physico-chemical parameters) were observed after treatment. For example, the BOD of pretreated sample (1027mg/l) from Dabur India Ltd. reduced to 943 mg/l when treated with cell suspension and reduced to 895 mg/l after treatment with immobilized cells. The turbidity of the pretreated sample from M.A.P.L. at 640 nm (0.189) reduced to 0.009 when treated with cell suspension and 0.007 when treated with immobilized cells. The odour and colour of the pretreated sample from Paras India Ltd. (Pungent milky & Golden Type) changes to milky & light milky when treated with cell suspension and immobilized cells. The pH of the pretreated sample from Dabur (7.5) reduced to 7.1 when treated with cell suspension and reduced to 7.2 when treated with immobilized cells.','','-','Vinay Dwivedi, Rashmi Chandra and Aarti Dwivedi','133-142','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(49,'Effect of Pesticide (Malathion) on Vegetables','Malathion, an organophosphate pesticide is most commonly used in our country. Malathion 51% EC is a liquid powder and is useful for crops like cotton, stone fruits, potato, rice and vegetables. It kills harmful pests and insects like hemiptera, dipteria, hymeptera, lepidoptera in a wide range of crops. Again this is used extensively to control anthropod disease factor in public health program, actoparasite of cattle, poultry, dogs and cats, body lice, and house hold insects. On exposure to this pesticide the common symptoms are headache, nausea, vomiting, burning eyes, abdominal pain, dizziness, memory disorder, neurological deficit, difficulty in breathing and lethargy.','','-','Jyoti Sharma and Khushbu Saxena','143-146','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(50,'A Supply Chain Production Inventory Model for Ameliorating and Deteriorating Products','In this paper, an integrated production-inventory model has been developed for linear production and demand of ameliorating and deteriorating items including time discounting factor. Supply chain consists of a supplier supplying the raw material (livestock) to manufacturer, a manufacturer preparing the finished goods and the retailer. A numerical example has been given to illustrate the model.','','-','Megha Rani, M. K. Gupta1 and S. R. Singh','147-162','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(51,'Flow of an Elastico-Viscous Second-Grade Fluid Between Two Infinite Rotating Discs with Suction and Injection','The present paper deals with the problem of an elastico-viscous second-grade fluid between two infinite rotating discs assuming suction at one of them and equal injection at the other. Numerical solution for the governing non-linear equations has been obtained by finite difference method over the entire range of the physical parameters. Effects of elastico-viscosity, suction and injection on the velocity field have been studied in detail and shown graphically for three typical cases: (a) when the discs rotate in the same sense, (b) when the discs rotate in the opposite sense and (c) when one disc rotates and the other is at rest.','','-','P. Pradhan, Parul Chaddha and H. G. Sharma','163-173','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(52,'Probability Model for Hiv Infection in Unmarried Female Migrants','This paper focuses on the study of model for the estimating the risk of vulnerability to HIV infections in female migrants having at least one close boy friend. In order to estimate the parameters of proposed model, estimation technique is used. The model provided a better fit to the observed set of data.','','-','Himanshu Pandey and Jai Kishun','175-180','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(53,'Quantile Analysis of the Inverse Generalized Exponential Distribution','This paper presents the Quantile analysis of the inverse Generalized Exponential distribution also the properties of the Quantile analysis as the percentile life. The main interests are in the relationship between and various B-lives; measure of variability for B-lives as the numerical quantities that describe the spread of the values in a set of data. Here these quantiles models presented graphically and mathematically.','','-','M. Shuaib Khan and Labibah Burki','181-193','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(54,'Variation of microwave emissivity and radar backscattering coefficient with roughness of soil surface','Real and imaginary parts of complex permittivity (?\' and ???) of soil of Alwar have been determined at a single microwave frequency 9.78 GHz and at a constant temperature 32.50C. In view of passive microwave remote sensing horizontal and vertical components of emissivity for bare and smooth soil surfaces along with for various rough surfaces are determined. The emissivity of soil is determined by Fresnel reflectivity in which dielectric constant is an input parameter. Roughness of soil surface is characterized by a roughness parameter which is proportional to RMS slope of rough surface. The co polarized radar backscattering coefficient of soil surfaces with different small level roughness is calculated by small perturbation model. It is observed that both the emissivity and backscattering coefficient increases with increasing roughness of soil surface. It was found that the active microwave remote sensing is very sensitive for roughness of soil surfaces in comparison to passive microwave remote sensing. In active microwave remote sensing detection of microwaves at the sensor in different angles is strongly related with the roughness of soil surface and as the roughness increases surfaces behave like lambertian reflectors.','','-','V. K. Gupta and R. A. Jangid','195-205','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(55,'The Time Dependent Solutions of the Markovian Queueing System','This paper represents some of the different expressions of the time-dependent solution for the number in a single-server queueing system with Poisson arrivals and exponential service with any arbitrary number i customers present initially. Further the equivalence some of these expressions is also discussed.','','-','Ashok Kumar and A. Jiran Meitei','207-215','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(56,'An Inventory Model with Power Demand, Partial Backlogging and Incremental Holding Cost Under Inflation','In this paper, an inventory model is developed for deteriorating items considering a power law form of the time dependence of demand. This paper also considers the items deteriorating after a fixed time period called life time and taking incremental holding cost. Effect of partial backlogging, inflation and shortage has also been taken in account. A comprehensive sensitivity analysis has also been done for some parameters. Cost minimization technique is used to get the approximate expressions for total cost and other parameters. Thus in the present paper an inventory model is developed for the life time items under the assumptions of all necessary factor like variable demand deterioration and backlogging under the effect of inflation.','','-','S. R. Singh1, Satish Kumar and A. P. Singh','217-226','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(57,'Thermal Instability of Stratified Visco-Elastic (Maxwell) Fluid in Porous Medium','The stability of stratified visco-elastic (Maxwell) fluid in porous medium with thermal effect had been investigated. Using the normal mode technique, the dispersion result is obtained. The important results obtained in this paper include the instability of non-oscillatory modes and the stability of oscillatory modes. It is also found that the system is stable for ? > 0 and unstable for ? < 0 under certain conditions.','','-','Shishpal Singh, Rimple Pundir and Sudhir Kumar Pundir','227-236','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(58,'Effect of weather variables on fatality and transmission of japanese encephalitis (je) in gorakhpur, u.p.','As Japanese Encephalitis (JE) is a mosquito-borne disease with a seasonal distribution, external environmental factors including weather variables play a significant role in its transmission. Studies in Gorakhpur city in the eastern part of Uttar Pradesh have suggested that weather variable, such as temperature, rainfall and relative humidity influences case fatality rate (CFR.) of Japanese Encephalitis (JE) cases. The role of weather variables in such situations may vary given the large variations in climate types, ecological characteristics, rice-growing techniques and pig breeding methods, population immunity, and public health intervention measures and socioeconomic status in the different regions identify risk factors related to weather and their role in CFR of Japanese Encephalitis (JE) with the objective of providing policy guidelines/suggestions implications for local health authorities and communities for prevention and control of dreadful disease JE.','','-','Sheela Misra and Purnima Singh','237-242','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(59,'Synthesis and Characterization of Nanocrystalline Iridium Oxide','Noble metal oxides as electrocatalysts are well established in many industrial electrochemical processes. Their coating is of commercial importance in applications for the electrochemical oxygen evolution. Many methods are available for the synthesis of noble metal based oxides. In the present work iridium oxide nanoparticles have been synthesized by oxidizing the metal precursor (IrCl3.H2O) in a molten nitrate melts at different temperatures. The characterization of the particles was carried out by using XRD and TEM analysis. TEM micrographs showed that IrO2 nanoparticles have small average diameters and narrow size distribution. The presence of tin oxide with iridium oxide decreases the pyrolysis temperature and increases the stability of particles.','','-','Anjali Goel and Sonia Sharma','243-251','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','4','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(60,'Variant Constraint Of Time Minimization Assignment Problem with Two Objectives-A Lexi Search Approach','There are n jobs to be carried out and m (n) machines only are available, out of the n jobs k jobs are necessary to be done on the available machines. Each job has to be done only on one of the machines (i.e. one can not start processing a job on one machine and halfway shift it to another machine). Also, each machine is required to process not less than mil (at least) and not more than miu (at most) jobs; thus, it is permissible that some jobs may have to go There are n jobs to be carried out and m ( n) machines only are available, out of the n jobs k jobs are necessary to be done on the available machines. Each job has to be done only on one of the machines (i.e. one can not start processing a job on one machine and halfway shift it to another machine). Also, each machine is required to process not less than mil (at least) and not more than miu (at most) jobs; thus, it is permissible that some jobs may have to go unprocessed i.e . With this idea the problem of TMAP was developed with different objectives: The first one is to difference minimization between machine times, required for processing the jobs on these machines. second one is to minimize the maximum of the total times