pul and S. K. Shon','445-454','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(127,'Impact of Microfinance on Poverty: A Review','While poverty eradication has been a most significant challenge among the policy makers of almost all the nation in this millennium, it is also very clearly stated in the millennium development goals that aim at halving poverty by 2015. With Mohammed Yunus being recently awarded the Noble Prize for his pioneering approach and sustained efforts in addressing problem of poverty, microfinance grew by leaps and bounds globally, particularly in Africa and South Asia. There are many studies which conclude the overwhelming success of microfinance programs most prominently in underdeveloped world. Benefits of microfinance are said to be realized in terms of higher income, livelihood security, womens empowerment, development of micro enterprise and many more. Micro-finance attempts to unleash forces transforming lives from debt-driven to self driven, so as to cause and trigger growth particular in rural areas. The rationale is that economic empowerment of the poor through strengthening the income generating capacity, equips the poor to access all the development requirements to get out of the multifaceted dimensions of poverty.  The present work is a review paper in which many studies conducted earlier, are reviewed and analyzed so as to bring forth the effects and benefits of microfinance on poverty.','','-','A.K. Pokhriyal and Vipin Ghildiyal','455-468','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(128,'Study and Application of Value Stream Mapping for the \r\nOverhauling of Orpheus Engine','Study and Application of Value Stream Mapping for the Over hauling of Orpheus Engine was carried out at Engine division of ABC Limited Bangalore. The present study covers salient details related to the implementation of PMS technique viz., the lean manufacturing principles, at the Engines Division of the factory at which the study was taken up. The study is intended mainly to reduce the Turn Around Time (TAT) in order to utilize the released manpower for other assignments.  In view of the rising competition and in order to hold on to the existing customer base and to attract new customers, the factory   felt the immediate need and pressure to improvise on their existing systems to become more competitive. The company has pertinently adopted the lean manufacturing techniques to reach world class status. The lean manufacturing tool (such as the value stream mapping, VSM) has been introduced to study and analyze the existing system.  Lean manufacturing is gaining momentum in the advanced manufacturing domains with the advent of new and revolutionary ideas and processes. Lean manufacturing aims at elimination of wastes and improving productivity. The auto giant Toyota has made the most of lean manufacturing and has come out with the popular Toyota Production System (TPS). The basis of this is the absolute elimination of waste. The two pillars needed to support the system are (a) just in time (JIT) concept, and (b) automation with a human touch.','','-','G.S. Prakash, N.V.R. Naidu and K. Mallikharjuna Babu','469-480','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(129,'Electrical and Structural Properties of CdTe/ZnTe Heterojunction Thin Films','Thin film of highly pure (99.999%) CdTe/ZnTe was prepared by high vacuum technique (HVT 5x10-6 torr), on glass substrates at different substrate temperatures. Thin Films have thickness 0.25 ?m. The X-ray diffraction study of the film represents amorphous nature at lower deposition temperature but poly-crystalline nature at higher deposition temperature.  The film deposited at lower temperatures was annealed for one hour in vacuum of 5x10-4 torr at as-deposited to 600K. The annealed film also represent poly-crystalline nature as film deposited at higher substrate temperature, because all films having different grain sizes, for lower  temperature the conductivity is essentially temperature dependent and at higher temperature the potential barriers localized at grain boundaries limit.','','-','P. K. Pandey, K.S.Upadhyay, S. N. Shukla, P. K. Singh and D.Sharma','481-488','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(130,'Load Balanced Energy Efficient Routing Protocol for WSN','In recent years, there has been a growing interest in wireless sensor networks. A wireless sensor network is designed to monitor event and reports this information to central location or sink node. The information is required to efficiently travel through the network. It is the job of routing protocol to officiate this process. Since the sensor nodes have limited available power, one of the major issues in wireless sensor network is developing an energy-efficient routing protocol. There are others issues also like commutation capability, traffic pattern, and application specific nature. However, energy awareness dominates all other issues in designing protocols for WSNs. Routing protocols in WSNs might differ depending on the application and network architecture. In this paper, we present a study of hierarchical routing protocols for wireless sensor networks with special emphasis on their energy efficiency and will point out there some limitation and make a proposal say Load-balanced energy efficient routing protocol (LERP) to overcome those limitations.','','-','Saroj Poonia, Mrityunjay Singh and Monika Sethi','489-498','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(131,'Issues of Internet Security','There are plenty of sorts of firewalls. However the main parts of them are a piece of software installed on the router of the company or on another host. But there are also hardware firewalls. It is an electronic board which is plugged inside the computer. There are different role for a firewall. Some are packet filtering router, dual-home gateway, bastion host, etc. There is also a wide range of firewalls for each operating system: UNIX, Novell Netware, Windows NT, LINUX, and so on ...','','-','Sanjeev Uppal','499-514','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(132,'An EPQ Model with Flexible Production Rate, Inflation Induced Demand with Partial Backorder for Two Warehouses','In this paper, a two warehouse production inventory model for deteriorating items with inflation induced demand and partial backlogging has been developed. A finite planning horizon inventory problem having two separate warehouses, one is an own warehouse (OW) of finite dimension and other a rented warehouse (RW) is developed with deterioration rate of the items to be different in different warehouses. Production rate is taken as a linear combination of demand and on-hand inventory in this chapter. Further, we use a numerical example to illustrate the model and sensitivity analysis on some parameters is made.','','-','Monika Vishnoi, S.K.Shon','211-224','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(133,'Modeling And Analysis Of A Two Storage Inventory Model With Variable Demand And Exponential Backlogging','Two warehouse inventory models have discussed with exponential demand rate for LIFO dispatching policy. Deterioration rate is linear function of time for both warehouses. In this paper, we have taken demand dependent production rate Shortages are allowed and the partially backlogged. Backlogging rate is exponential decreasing function of time. The effect of inflation is also considered in this study. We have used the cost minimization technique.','','-','S.R. Singh, Ajay Singh Yadav, Satish Kumar','225-232','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(134,'Vibrational Spectral Analysis, Molecular Polarizability and Structural Parameters For Substituted Aniline','The Laser Raman and IR spectra of 2-Bromo-4,6-dinitro aniline have been recorded in the solid phase . Utilizing the observed FTIR and FT-Raman data, a complete vibrational assignment and analysis of the fundamental modes of the compounds were carried o?ut in the range (4000-400 cm-1 ) for FT-IR spectra & (0-2000 cm-1) for  Raman spectra. The molecular structure of the said compound has been obtained by comparing it with the earlier work on similar molecules. Molecular polarizability of the said compound has been calculated using bond parallel component and perpendicular component by Lippincott Delta function potential model.','','-','M K Yadav, Bandana, Jayant','233-243','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(135,'Optimal Inventory Policy for Perishable Items under the Effect of Inflation and Partial Backlogging','In this paper, an inventory model has been developed for perishable items with linear trend demand under the effect of inflation. Time dependent deterioration rate is considered in the model. The most decision makers think that the inflation does not have significant influence on the inventory policy; however, from a financial point of view it is necessary to consider the effects of inflation on the inventory system. Constant rate of inflation is taken in the model, shortages are allowed and partial backlogging of unsatisfied demand is considered. Constant backlogging rate is considered. The model is solved numerically to obtain the optimal solution of the problem.','','-','Bindu Vaish, Garima Garg, Neeti Agrawal','245-260','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(136,'Application of Value Stream Mapping In Garment Industries','This paper unravels some of the issues, ideas and challenges faced in the field of Value Stream Mapping. Value stream mapping enables you to identify the wastage in your processes. If an activity is not adding value to your products, it is waste and should be removed. When the value stream is analyzed, most companies are shocked as to the amount of time that no Value adding activities are taking place. Building batches and keeping it as Work In Progress (WIP) is simply adding waste to the process and extending the total processing time. Value Stream Mapping is a visual method of mapping the flow of materials and information from the time products come in from goods inwards, through all the manufacturing processes and finally ready for dispatch. Value stream mapping is a key tool in Lean Manufacturing Principles. The advantages of VSM includes, identifying the complete production process not just a single process, allowing identifying the sources of waste. The Current state map and future state map help form an implementation plan for change and improvement. The paper aims at reducing the cycle time of a garment manufacturing section of M/s. XYZ company. This organization mainly deals with production of different types of readymade garments in terms of coats, shirts, pants, etc mainly to cater to overseas markets. The problems faced by the company includes, the reduced average output per day, Longer Production lead-times, Reduced Value-added percentage. The results of the study after comparing the current and future state Maps yielded positive results.','','-','Chethan Kumar C S, K. Ravindranath, N V R Naidu','261-276','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(137,'Replenishment policy for deteriorating items with Quadratic demand and two-storage facilities   ','Two warehouse production inventory model for decaying items with quadratic demand has been developed. In this study, we have considered the deterioration cost is time dependent and holding cost is constant for OW. The deterioration rate is constant and holding cost is time dependent for RW. This article aids in minimizing the total inventory cost by finding an optimal replenishment policy. Finally, we use numerical example to illustrate the model and sensitivity analysis on some parameter is made.   ','','-   ','   S. R. Singh, Krishan Pal*   *Research Scholar Singhania University, Pacheri Beri    ','277-290      ','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-11-06 03:02:45','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(138,'Effect of Heat Transfer on Mhd Flow of a Dusty Visco-Elastic Liquid Through Porous Medium Past an Inclined Plane','The present problem is concerned with the effect of heat transfer on MHD laminar flow of an unsteady visco-elastic (Kuvshiniski type) liquid through porous medium with uniform distribution of dust particles past an inclined plane under the influence of exponential pressure gradient and mass transfer. The liquid is bounded by a parallel upper surface at a distance h from the plane. Analytical expressions for velocities of liquid and dust particles and concentration are obtained which are in elegant forms. The numerical results are presented graphically for different values of the various parameters entering into the problem.','','-','U. R. Singh, Ajay Kumar Sharma, Rajeev Jha','291-299','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(139,'Fuzzy Logic Approach towards Business Process Reengineering of Manufacturing Systems','In response to an increasingly global and competitive environment, the flexibility to adapt to changing market needs and develop innovative cross-functional processes is quintessential to success. Reengineering is a fundamental rethinking and radical redesign of business processes to achieve dramatic improvement in cost, quality, speed, and service. This work presents a method of taking the decision of reengineering manufacturing systems based upon fuzzy techniques. Reengineering of manufacturing systems requires multi-variable decision making based upon complicated mathematical methods and involves a large amount of data to be processed. Fuzzy logic allows the extraction of precise conclusions based on vague human perceptions involved in reengineering. This paper presents a novel fuzzy-logic approach for measuring necessary degree of change that exploits linguistic variables for quantifying pertinent factors. The model is illustrated with an example.','','-','S.R. Ansari, P.K. Mittal, Ritu Chandna','301-324','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(140,'Association Between Age-Groups, Sex and Japanese Encephalitis Cases','Japanese Encephalitis (JE) an important disease of viral origin has attracted the attention of public health specialists in South East Asia Regions especially in the BBIN (Bangladesh Bhutan, India & Nepal) countries due to its endemicity, high case fatality rate (CFR) and residual problems among survivors. JE has been occurring in the endemic form since long back particularly in northern states of India. Maximum number of JE cases occurred in 2005 as per records. So we have chosen year 2005 for analysis of age and sex distribution of JE cases and their association. So we divided ages in three age groups 0-4, 5-9, 10-14, 15 & above; these age groups are associated with JE cases (survive & deaths) in different districts in U.P.As per observation it is tested whether age groups and consequences of JE attacks are associated or not. The data analysis was done for seven districts viz Gorakhpur, Mharajganj, Kushinagar, Deoria, Basti, Siddhartha Nagar and Sant Kabir Nagar in U.P. Though it is evident that age groups and sex have its impact on death or survival of JE cases; in many cases no evidence was found to be statistically strong. This may be due to limitation of the statistic used for testing the hypothesis. A deeper and more sensitive analysis is required to be carried out as it is found that a specific age group and sex seems to be more affected by the consequence through previous records consistently barring a few exceptions.','','-','Purnima Singh, Manindra Kumar Srivastava, Babu Banarasi Das','325-330','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(141,'Ion Exchange capacity Determination of Antimony(iii) molybdovanadate a Synthesized Inorganic material and its Characterization','In the present work , the ion exchange capacity is found to be more than the reported ion exchanger based on antimony(iii) . Antimony(iii) molybd-ovanadate has been synthesized and charged to use as an exchanger . This ion exchanger has been characterized on the basis of thermal stability , x-ray analysis FTIR study and other parameters. Chemical stability of the exchanger has been accessed in acidic and basic media . The ion exchange capacity of the exchanger is found to be 0.78 meq/g. The ion exchange capacity of the material for Na+, K+, Ca++, Mg++, Ba++ is found to be 0.78 , 0.84 , 1.1 , 1.2 , 1.3 meq/g. respectively . The effect of temperature on ion exchange capacity has been studied. Distribution coefficient values for seven metal ions have been determined. From distribution studies it is found that Antimony(iii) molybd-ovanadate is selective for Ni++ions.','','-','Subhash Chand, Seema, Rekha Rani , Vijayata','331-341','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(142,'Monthly Variation of a few Parameters of Water of Different Underground Sources at Bhiwadi (Rajasthan)','A study has been carried out to determine the quality of water of Bhiwadi city in district Alwar. The samples of underground water from three different sites viz. Santhalka village (Bore well water), RIICO Chowk (Hand pump water) and CETP (Bore well water) were collected and studied for different physico-chemical and microbiological parameters. In comparison to site-1 and site-2, water of site-3 showed high concentration of pollutants. The results indicate that water of these sources is unfit for human consumption and irrigation without the treatment.','','-','Jyoti Sharma, Deepti Dhama','343-347','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(143,'Inventory Management Simulation','Inventory management plays very important role in production operations. Inventory management is required for just-in-time manufacturing under different environmental situations. Different simulation approaches have been extensively used to compute required inventory level for a production system. This paper describes basic need and requirement to establish a simulation model for inventory management system. It focuses on comparison of analogue and hybrid simulation models used to establish inventory system. It discusses its application for basic inventory control policies such as, ordering quantity, reorder level and reorder cycle. It discusses the features to be included in an inventory simulation model and the extent of details affecting the model performance. This paper describes a study on conceptual inventory simulation modeling and comparison between application methods.','','-','Pratiksha Saxena','349-356','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(144,'Professional Education: Mandatory for Survival as well as success in Todays World','NA','','-','Vasudha Sharma','357-360','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(145,'A Statistical Analysis of Problems of Women Entrepreneurs Regarding various sectors across different States','This research paper takes up the study of opportunities, growth and problems of women in business in the state of Utter Pradesh, Haryana, Uttarakhand and union territory of Chandigarh. Chi-square test, through R-software, has been used for measurement of the economic performance of women entrepreneurs.','','-','U.P. Sarbhai, P.K.Kaushik, P. K. Gupta, Rajesh Verma','361-374','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','16','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(146,'Finite Element Model To Study Unsteady State Cytosolic Calcium Diffusion','Calcium plays a significant role in the signal transduction in neurons. In this paper, an attempt has been made to develop a finite element model to understand the mechanism of signal transduction in neurons. The proposed model elucidates the process of cytosolic calcium diffusion, and incorporates all the necessary parameters like time, association rate, influx, buffer concentration, diffusion constant etc. The proposed mathematical model leads to a partial differential equation equipped with initial and boundary conditions. Finite element method is used to obtain calcium concentration in space dimensions and Numerical Integration is used to compute calcium profile with respect to time. A program has been developed for the entire problem