in Applied Sciences','17','17','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(149,'Effect of Hydrostatic Pressure on Ga As 1-x Px Material With Different Doping Levels','In the present work, the effect of hydrostatic pressure on the mobility, effective mass and ionization energy of the electrons in conduction valley in GaAs1-xPx materials, taking the effect of band tailing into account, which has not been considered by earlier works. The theoretical analysis is based on an examination of the relative distribution of charge carriers in the valley (000) and (100) as the crystal is subject to hydrostatic Pressure. The donor levels associated with valley (100) and band tail associated with valley (000) have been considered .The effect of the donor level is dominant at higher pressures .The effect of band- tailing is to decrease the number of carriers in the conduction band of first valley, conformity  with earlier results','','-','Govind Kumar, R.P. Gairola and S.C.Gupta','413-418','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','17','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(150,'Hill reaction rate of lower half leaves in affected roadside plants due to motor driven vehicles around the crossing of Meerut','Light plays an important role in physiological activites of leaf. Leaves of plants are concerned with photosynthesis, chloroplast are the organelles of the cell which are concerned with photosynthetic activity, disorganization of chloroplast is described as one of the first events to appear by the effect of various pollutants. \r\nIn a comprehensive survey of pollution impact on the photosynthetic efficiency of  certain plants in city junctions of Meerut i.e. Hapurstand, Begumpul, Collectorate crossing Mawana stand and in outskirts area i.e. Medical college, Delhi road, Pallavpuram, Shastri nagar L-block, a clear cut adverse impact has being recorded in the various process of photo