(III) catalyzed oxidation of isoleucine by hexacyanoferrate(III) in aqueous alkaline medium. The molar absorptivity & sandells sensitivity are found 4.42 x 103  5.57 x 103 l mol-1cm-1 & 0.0435 - 0.0345 ?g cm-2 respectively. The value of correlation coefficient lies between 0.9997 to 0.9989. The effect of few interferrants has also been worked out. For developing the calibration curves in terms of absorbance or initial rates or pseudo first order rate constant vs.[Ir(III)] plots, absorbance was noted at ?max 420 nm. The result show that the present method is more simple & sensitivity than the reported methods and especially useful in absence of the expected interferrants. The standard deviation estimated from six independent determination in sample of Ir(III) for the concentration of 6.7?10-6M are 0.0634 to 1.14.','','-','Anjali Goel, Savita Gupta and Sonia Sharma','559-566','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(160,'The present paper deals with certain generating functions of Gottlieb polynomials of several variables.','Some New Generating Functions for Gottlieb Polynomials of Several Variables','','-','Mumtaz Ahmad Khan and Mohd Akhlaq','567-570','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(161,'Strong Cylindrical Shock Waves in Real Gas','This paper deals with the propagation of strong cylindrical shock in uniform real gas. Analytical relations for shock velocity and shock strength have been obtained for two cases viz. (1) when shock moves freely and (ii) when it moves under the influence of overtaking disturbances. The dependence of shock velocity and shock strength on propagation distance (r), specific heat index (?) and real gas constant (b) is discussed with the help of tables. Using the relations profiles of flow variables of perturbed real gas have been prepared. The results for real gases obtained here are compared for ideal gas obtained elsewhere.','','-','R.P. Yadav, Virendra Kumar Gangawar and Vijay Pal','571-580','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(162,'Structural studies and Ab initio, density functional theory \r\nof 2,6-diamino-3-nitrosopyridine','In the present work, the experimental and theoretical vibrational spectra of 2,6-di-amino-3-nitroso pyridine (2,6,3-DANP) were studied. FTIR spectra of (2, 6, and 3 -DANP) in the solid phase were recorded in the region 4000400cm-1 and 350050cm-1, respectively. The structural and spectroscopic data of the molecule in the ground state were calculated by using Hartree-Fock and density functional method (B3LYP) with  6-31+G(d,p),  basis set. The scaled values have been compared with experimental FTIR spectra. The observed and calculated frequencies are found to be in good agreement.','','-','B. S. Yadav, Rajesh Kumar, Manoj Kumar Singh and Jayant Teotia','581-594','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(163,'A Result on Certain Characteristics of Average Outgoing Quality Limit','This paper describes some special characteristics of AOQL which is not seen in many other quality indices. Using this property a selection procedure for an Optimum Sampling Plan, offering maximum consumer protection in terms of greatest lower bound (g.l.b) of AOQL, with fixed MAPD is suggested. Tables are provided to select Optimum sampling plans and values of AQL and g l b of AOQL. Different Empirical relations were developed in terms of AOQL and MAPD. Lower and Upper bounds of AOQL for some parametric sampling plans are listed.','','-','Ramkumar T. B.','595-602','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(164,'Decomposition of Recurrent Curvature Tensor Field in Tachibana Space','The purpose of the present paper is to decompose recurrent curvature tensor field in a Tachibana space and to establish the relation between the recurrence vectors and other tensors into which the recurrence curvature tensor field have been decomposed.','','-','Girish Dhobal and K. S. Rawat','603-608','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(165,'Infrared, Laser Raman Spectral Studies and Thermodynamic Properties of 2-amino-4, 6-dimethoxy Pyrimidine Molecule','The Infrared and Laser Raman Spectra of 2-amini-4, 6-dimethoxy pyrimidine have been reported the assignments of fundamental frequencies to various modes of vibrations have been reported. Tautomeric forms are also discussed. Thermodynamic properties have been computed and discussed.','','-','\"\"B. S. Yadav, Manoj Kumar Singh,  ;\r\nVijay Kumar, Manju Singh and Jayant Teotia\"','609-620','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(166,'Mathematical Model for the Effect of Micropolar Parameter  in Stenotic Artery','The effect of micropolar parameter in stenotic artery has been investigated in this work. Here the micropolar model for axisymmetric blood flow through an axially nonsymmetrical but radially symmetric stenotic artery is presented. It is observed that the pressure drop, axial velocity flow and shear stress distribution in stenotic region have been computed for the Coupling number(C), the shape parameter (n), and the micropolar parameter (M). The results show for the micropolar fluid, the pressure drop increases with C and decreases with M and the axial velocity increases with M and decreases with C. Finally this investigation can provide much valuable information about the velocity profile, pressure drop, stenotic height and different parameters involved in this problem.','','-','Sanjeev Kumar and Archana Dixit','621-628','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(167,'Comparative Structural Analysis of PBZT Nanoceramics  Synthesized by Co-precipitation and Sol-gel Method','In this study a comparative structural analysis of bismuth doped PZT nanoceramics (i.e.Pb0.98Bi0.02 (Zr0.52Ti0.48)0.98 O3) prepared by chemical co-precipitation and sol-gel methods has been made. Perovskite PZT phase in the compound prepared by sol-gel method can be seen at the temperature as low as 2500C whereas the evolution of PZT phase along with small amount of pyrochlore phase take place only after 4000C temperature in the samples prepared by co-precipitation method. The X-ray diffractogram of pellets sintered at 11000C also confirms that bismuth doping does not affect the crystal structure of the compounds and a tetragonal unit cell structure was formed in both of the cases.','','-','Amar Pal, Manoj Kumar and Bikas Prasad','629-634','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(168,'A Survey of Aeromycoflora of Libraries of Dehradun District','Aerobiology is defined as a discipline of investigation of aerial transport of biological materials. Fungal spores are an important component of bioaerosol. The biological features of fungi i.e. their ease of dispersion makes fungi one of the chief agents of contamination of any type of substrate including cellulose materials in the books of library. The objective of the present paper is the identification of predominant fungal spores present in the library. The study of aeromycoflora of two libraries of Dehradun District viz. Khushi Ram Library, Dispensary Road and Shri Guru Ram Rai (P.G.) College Library, Pathri bagh were carried out between the months of May-June. During the summer month, when the high temperature and humidity predominate, the fungal load in air increased. Air borne fungal spores recorded were representatives of the three major groups i.e. Ascomycotina, Zygomycotina and Deuteromycotina.','','-','M. Ram Naresh, S. Saxena, P. Sharma and S. Guleri','635-640','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(169,'The Utilization of Fly ASH & ITS Threats to Environment','Combustion of coal is the process which generates fly ash in the form of residue behind it. Coal fired power plants are the sources of fly ash from where it is generally captured from power plants chimneys. Fly ash is one of the two types of ashes that are jointly known as coal ash. Coal ash is the by product of the combustion of coal and it is the combination of fly ash and bottom ash. Bottom ash is removed from the bottom of the coal furnaces. It is to be noticed that the components of the fly ash vary considerably as its quality and composition depend on the source and the make up of the coal being burned. The main components of fly ash include substantial amounts of Silicon dioxide and Calcium oxide. Other than these components, fly ash also contains some toxic amount of arsenic, beryllium, boron, cadmium, chromium, chromiumVI, cobalt, lead, manganese, mercury, molybdenum, selenium, strontium, thallium, and vanadium, along with dioxins and PAH compounds.','','-','Bikas Prasad, S.K. Singh G. Kumar','641-652','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(170,'Optimal Ordering Policy with Time Dependent Ramp Type Demand, Life Time and Variable Rate of Deterioration','This paper deals an order level inventory system for non-instantaneous decaying items with ramp type demand rate. Deterioration rate is taken as time dependent. In this model, we have discussed two cases; one is model started without shortages and second is model started with shortages. Holding cost is a linear increasing function of time. Shortages are allowed with partial backlogging. Backlogging rate is taken as an exponential decreasing function of time. The models are illustrated with some numerical data. Finally, numerical examples are presented to demonstrate the developed model and solution procedure.','','-','A.P. Singh, Pankaj Kumar, Anand Chauhan','653-666','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(171,'Seed Galactomannans : A Natural Source of Industrial Potential','With the obvious exception of starch, the galactomannans are the most extensively studied of the storage polysaccharides of higher plants and there can be little doubt that the principal reason for this is their commercial importance. Certain plant galactomannans, notably those from carob (Ceratonia siliqua) and guar (Cyamopsis tetragonoloba) seeds, find widespread application as industrial gums. Their main application is in the rheological control of the aqueous phase. Many galactomannans perform as simple thickeners. Such materials are low cost commodities, and in general the cheapest find greatest application. As a result it is now recognised that the biochemical and biotechnological tailoring of galactomannan structure can results in an optimisation of functional properties.','','-','Vikas Rana and Rakesh Bachetii','667-680','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(172,'Unstudy Free Convective Mhd Flow between Two Heated Vertical Parallel Plates with Varying Temperature','In this paper, we are investigating the fully developed free convection laminar flow of an incompressible viscous electrically conduction fluid between two vertical parallel plates in presence of uniform magnetic field applied transversely to the flow. This induces a field along the lines of motion, which varies transversely to the flow. The temperature of the fluid motion is assumed to be changing with time, the analytical solutions for velocity induced electric field and the temperature distributors are obtained for small & large electric Reynolds number [Rm]. The skin friction of the plates are obtained for different electric field parameters and plotted graphically.','','-','M.S. Bisht, A.P. Singh and Amit Singh Negi','681-688','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(173,'Seasonal Variations In Physico-Chemical Parameters Of River Ganga At Garhmukteshwar  District Ghaziabad','This paper is an attempt to analyze the water quality of river Ganga at Garhmukteshwar district Ghaziabad. Water samples were collected from five sampling stations. The study area has been divided into three seasons: Winter, Summer and rainy. The study of physico-chemical parameters like temp., pH, electric conductivity, dissolved oxygen, biological oxygen demand, chemical oxygen demand, hardness, alkalinity, ammonical nitrogen has been studied in the period of 2007-2008. The study shows the seasonal variation in the physico-chemical parameters.','','-','Praveen Chauhan, Lakshmi Chauhan','689-694','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(174,'A Linear Fractional Program and Algorithm','This paper presents an algorithm for solving a linear fractional functionals programming problem by a finite iterative method. The solution of the system of inequalities results in to the solution of the given problem. The objective function is made as one of the linear constraints of the system. The method goes through steps before termination. In each step, one variable is eliminated from the system and a new system of linear inequalities in the remaining variables is derived, which is then solved by going to the next step. The last step results in an objective function variable inequality. This inequality may be linear or non-linear.','','-','S.S. Chadha and Veena Chadha','1-8','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(175,'Two Echelon Supply Chain Model with Imperfect Production, for Weibull Distribution Deteriorating Items under Imprecise and Inflationary Environment','In this paper a two echelon supply chain model is developed from the perspective of both the manufacturer and the retailer in an imprecise and inflationary environment. However, during a production run, a process may shift to an out-of-control state. If the shift is not detected until the end of the production cycle, it results in some fixed proportion of the produced items to be defective. When finally these defective items are detected at the end of the production cycle, a rework cost is incurred for the same.  Raw material and the finished goods follow the different weibull distribution deterioration rate. Shortages are allowed at the retailers part only and the unfulfilled demand is partially backlogged. In this paper, an integrated optimal control approach is proposed to optimize the production, recycling and disposal strategy so that expected value of total cost is minimized. Integrated cost policy is compared with the independent decisions made by the manufacturer and the retailers and the necessary conclusions are made. The optimum results are presented both in tabular form and graphically. Mathematica5.2 has been used to reach the optimal policies.','','-','Chaman Singh and S.R. Singh','9-25','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(176,'Designing a Quality Interval Single Sampling Plan','Attribute Sampling Plans on quality indices like AQL(p1), MAPD(p*), LTPD(p2) pave the way for Suspicious and Reliable Quality Regions SQR = (p* - p1), and RQR = (p2 - p1). At the initial stage of production where the exact quality of the product was not known, optimum information on Acceptable (AQL), Allowable (MAPD) and Worst admissible (LTPD) proportion of defectives would be better for protecting both Consumer and Producer. New Single Sampling Plan was developed by suggesting a unique monotonic decreasing function (Tabular values) corresponding to c = 1, 2,, 20. Efficiency of this plan over other plan was noted and suitable examples were illustrated. Also an Optimum Sampling Plan is suggested under a feasible range of MAPD falling within p1 and p2. OC curves were compared w.r. to probability of acceptance of good lots changing SQR or RQR. Another SSP is also mentioned on Balanced Quality Region (BQR) with SQR. Some interesting relations on AQL, LTPD, and IQL with MAPD were presented.','','-','T. B. Ramkumar','27-40','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(177,'Solution of Multi-objective Linear Programming Problem with Constraints as Fuzzy Equations','We propose a methodology for the solution of multi-objective linear programming problem with constraints taken as fuzzy equations based on fuzzy programming approach. Firstly we find the feasible solution set and give an algorithm to compute minimal and maximal solutions of objective functions which can also be computed by computer program developed by us and then works for the minimization of perpendicular distances between the parallel hyper planes at the optimal points of the objective functions. Suitable membership function has been defined with the help of supremum perpendicular distance. A compromise optimal solution is obtained as a result of minimization of perpendicular distance. An example is given in the last to illustrate our model.','','-','Sanjay Jain  and Kailash Lachhwani','41-53','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(178,'A volume flexible inventory model for Defective Items with Multi-Variate Demand and Partial Backlogging','In this paper, we studied an imperfect production system for decaying items with volume flexibility and multi-variate demand. Here demand of the item depends on selling price, marketing cost and quality level. The selling price of an unit is determined by a mark-up over the unit production cost and unit production cost depends on the cost of raw material and labor charge. We discussed two models: in first model, number of defective items is certain and in second model, number of defective items is random and follows an exponential distribution. Holding cost is a linear increasing function of time. Shortages are occurring and partially backlogged with an exponential decreasing function of time rate. Finally numerical experiment and sensitivity analysis are provided to illustrate the system.','','-','S. R. Singh, Surbhi Singhal, P. K. Gupta','55-69','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(179,'Multilevel programming problem with bounded decision variables','In this paper, a three level programming problem has been discussed in which the objective function of first level is quadratic, of the second level is linear and that of third level is a fractional function. The variables are taken to be bounded below. The feasible region has been considered as a convex polyhedron. With all constraints less than equal to zero and non-negative restriction on variables the problem of maximization of objective functions is more appropriate in comparison to that of minimization. Therefore the case of maximization of the objective functions has been considered in this paper.','','-','Sonam Sharma, Mehga Rani and S.M. Gupta','71-83','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(180,'A Multi Item Inventory Model with Machine Breakdown, Flexible Strategy and Capacity Constraint over Fuzzy Environment','This paper investigates a volume flexible inventory model with machine breakdown. It is assuming that there exists an enthusiastic production facility as well as a separate management units for each of the items. Machine breakdowns resulting idle times of relevant management units taken into account. Production rates are treated as volume flexible in nature. We developed the model with multi item. We considered the demand rate is triangular fuzzy number and items deteriorate at constant rate. Optimal production policy is consequent with minimization of total cost as criterion of optimality. Numerical illustration of the model is given in the end. Sensitivity analysis shows the stability of the model.','','-','S. R. Singh and Urvashi','85-94','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(181,'A Stochastic Model For Estimation of Time to Stop Enrolment For Recruitment','Certain organizations engaged in HRM activities, take up the process of registration of personnel for recruitment. They keep a reserve or inventory of manpower and apply the same to organizations which need manpower at random points. The reserve of manpower cannot be beyond a certain limit called the threshold, because it would be expensive and also has impact on the goodwill of the recruiting organization. Hence they stop the registration for recruitment as and when the threshold is reached. An additional manpower stock is also maintained to meet the situations which arise due to the fact that some of persons who have registered for recruitment may not turn up at the time or demand. Hence the threshold can be represented as a total of two components. Using the shock model and cumulative damage process concept the expected time to stop registration and its variance are derived in this paper. Numerical illustration is also provided.','','-','R. Elangovan, G. Arivazhagan and  R. Sathiyamoorthi','95-106','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(182,'A Supply Chain Model with Variable Holding Cost for Flexible Manufacturing System','The present paper undertakes to study the integrated model with imperfect production system where the items produced are a mixture of perfect and imperfect quality under the affect of holding cost function which is considered a function of time. In the existing literature, most of the models assume that the holding cost is constant for the entire inventory cycle. This paper considers the two different time dependent function of holding cost i.e., retroactive holding cost increase and incremental holding cost increase. Some of the imperfect quality items can be sold at a reduced selling price. The mathematical expression for the expected profit function is derived. A numerical example is provided to illustrate the model.','','-','S.R. Singh, A.P.Singh and Diksha Bhatia','107-120','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(183,'Mathematical Model for the Effect of Body Acceleration on Blood    Flow in Time Dependent Stenosed Artery','Pulsatile flow of blood under the influence of externally imposed periodic body acceleration through a time dependent stenosed artery is studied in this work. A mathematical model is developed by treating blood as a non-Newtonian fluid characterized by the casson fluid. The pulsatile flow is analyzed by considering a periodic pressure gradient, which is a function of time. In this analysis we try to find the computational results by using the  perturbation analysis, assuming that the Womersley frequency parameter is very small. The effect of body acceleration has been discussed with the help of graphs. The graphs show velocity profile, volumetric flow rate and the wall shear stress are decrease as the body acceleration parameter increase. It is noticed that the effect of yield stress and stenosis is to reduce flow rate and the presence of body acceleration is to increase the flow rate. The flow resistance is seemed to be increased substantially due to the presence of yield stress and stenosis. The body acceleration is found to reduce the flow resistance.','','-','Sanjeev  Kumar  and  Archana  Dixit','121-132','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(184,'Two levels of storage model for non-instantaneous deteriorating items with stock dependent demand, time varying partial backlogging under permissible delay in payments','This paper explores the Economic order quantity (EOQ) based model for non-instantaneous deteriorating items with stock dependent demand and permissible delay in payments. This article aids in minimizing the total inventory cost by finding an optimal replenishment policy. In the model, shortages are allowed and the backlogging rate is variable and dependent on the waiting time for the next replenishment. On the other hand, the classical inventory models usually assume the available warehouse has unlimited capacity. In many practical situations, there exist many factors like temporary price discounts making retailers buy a capacity of goods exceeding their own warehouse. In this case, retailers may rent other warehouses for the need of business. Finally, we use numerical example to illustrate the model and sensitivity analysis on some parameter is made.','','-','Monika Vishnoi and S. K. Shon','133-147','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(185,'Optimum Sample Sizes in Case of Stratified Sampling for Non-Respondents : An Integer Solution','In this paper, we have found the optimum sample sizes for the fixed total sample size and sub sample sizes of non-respondents for the fixed total cost in the case of Stratified sampling. The given problem is first formulated as a Mathematical Programming Problem (MPP) and then solved by using Lagranges Multiplier technique. We have obtained the integer solution by using the Branch and Bound Technique.','','-','Yashpal Singh Raghav, Irfan Ali and Abdul Bari','149-160','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(186,'Replenishment Policy for Non-instantaneous Deteriorating Items with Stock-dependent Demand and Partial Back Logging with Two-storage Facilities under Inflation','In this study, we propose an optimal replenishment policy by considering stock dependent consumption rate for non-instantaneous deteriorating items with two-storage facilities. In the rented warehouse, the product has no deterioration but in the own warehouse, the product has deterioration. Here, we have considered the inflation and time discounting. In this model, shortages are allowed and backlogging is partial. Solution procedure is given and explained with example. The impact of various parameters of the system on the optimal solution is analyzed by carrying out sensitivity analysis with perturbations in various parameters by using MATHEMATICA  5.2.','','-','S.R. Singh, Rachna Kumari and Neeraj Kumar','161-179','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(187,'Transient Analysis for a Two-state Bulk Arrival Queueing System with Bulk Departure','Present paper studies the transient analysis of a first-come-first-served two-state bulk queueing model. In two-state queueing models, the state of the system is  given  by (i, j),  where  i  is the  number of  arrivals  and  j  is  the  number  of departures by a given time. This type of queueing model provides better insight into the behavior of queueing systems. Bulk queues provide very useful tools for analyzing many applications in a great variety of fields: communication systems; transportation systems; manufacturing systems.','','-','Indra and Vijay Kumar','181-194','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(188,'A Priority and Non Priority Tandem Queueing System','This paper deals with the study of priority tandem queueing system in which four service facilities are linked under pre- emptive repeat Service rule. The behavior of queue system is considered in the steady state under the positions assumptions for the arrivals and departures. The study has been made using various mathematical and statistical techniques, to find mean Queue size or marginal mean queue size which may be useful parameter as an economical decision measure. The Queue length is also obtained with the help of generating function.','','-','Amit Mittal and L.M. Tiwari','195-202','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(189,'Ameliorating Inventory Model with Weibull Deteriorating Under the Effect of Inflation and Partial Backlogging','This research deals with the supply chain production inventory model of both the perspective of both the manufacturer and the retailer. Amelioration occurs when the value or utility of a product increases over time. The examples of ameliorating, young or fast growing animals such as chickens, fish and pigs. The manufacturers purchase these livestock when they are small and raise them. The manufacturers treat these livestock as the raw materials. When these livestock are kept in the farm, they will increase in value due to their growth and decrease in value due to feeding expenses and disease. When these livestock have grown up, the manufacturers use the matured livestock to produce the cooked livestock. To be more realistic, the livestocks growth is faster in the beginning and declines at the later stage. Therefore, we used weibull ameliorating rates with decreasing function with time and weibull deteriorating rate with increasing function with time.  The effect of inflation, deterioration, amelioration with multiple deliveries and time discounting are also considered. The optimal production and replenishment policy to minimize the net present total cost can be derived by using the methodologies. The result of the analysis can help manufacturers and retailers to minimize the net total cost.','','-','Anand Chauhan and A.P. Singh','203-220','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(190,'Uncertainty Measurement of Markovian Queue by Principle of Maximum Entropy','In the present paper we discussed the measurement of uncertainty in Markovian queue using principle of maximum entropy. Shannon (1948) in information theory deals with mathematical model for communication problem has been found useful in many different disciplines. Entropy is proposed as a measure of operating performance for Markovian queueing system. The concept of steady-state of a queue concerns a probability function, it is found feasible and logical that the queueing systems steady-state distribution would give the uncertainty of the model performance.','','-','S. R. Ansari, Shiv Prasad and M. S. Rawat','221-226','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(191,'Reliability Analysis of Non-Markovian Queue with Utilization of Idle Time and Unreliable Server','Unreliable server is an important performance analysis component. In this paper, we study transient behaviour of a two-dimensional non-markovian queueing model in which an unreliable server after completing the service goes on vacation to do some other task with probability one when it finds no one waiting in the queue to utilize the idle time. Arriving customers are in poisson stream. The servers service times, breakdown times and repair times are having exponential distribution whereas the vacation times are generally distributed. Laplace transforms of explicit probabilities of exact number of arrivals & departures by a given time and number of units arrive by time t, using supplementary variable technique are obtained. Further, reliability and availability of the system are analysed. Several performance measures, namely, number of units arrive by time t, number of  units depart by time t, waiting time distribution, cumulative distribution for sojourn time, reliability of the system, servers breakdown time and servers vacation time, are also presented numerically and graphically both, for the case when the vacation time is exponential. Finally, some interesting particular cases are derived there from.','','-','Indra and Sweety','227-242','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','11','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(192,'On the Vorticity of Unsteady MHD Free Convection Flow Through Porous Medium with Heat and Mass Transfer Past a Porous Vertical Moving Plate with Heat Source/Sink','In this paper, we discuss Vorticity of an incompressible viscous fluid of small electrical conductivity in a porous medium past an infinite porous vertical non-conducting moving plate in the presence of uniform transverse magnetic field is carried out. The effect of magnetic parameter (M), Permeability (K), Modified Grashoff number (Gm), frequency (w) and Schmidt number (Sc) on the vorticity  is discussed graphically.','','-','P. K. Mittal, Vijay Dhasmana, S. B. Pandey Amal Shanker Shukla','1-6','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','12','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(193,'Hydromagnetic Instability of Rivlin-Ericksen Visco-elastic Fluid in Porous Medium','The hydromagnetic instability of Rivlin-Ericksen visco-elastic fluid in porous medium is considered by applying normal mode technique, the dispersion relation has been derived and solved analytically and numerically. Important result obtained in this paper includes the sufficient condition for stability, marginal state of the system and solution of the problem for free boundaries. A variational principle for the problem under consideration is also obtained.','','-','Aftab Alam, Rimple Pundir  and Sudhir K. Pundir','7-21','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','12','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(194,'Effect of Magnetic Field on Flow of a Newtonian Fluid between Two Parallel Plates with Porous Lining','In this paper the flow of Newtonian fluid between two infinite parallel plates is considered, the plates are coated with porous material and the flow in between the plates will considered two layered flow. The effect of magnetic field in this flow is considered. This has analogy with blood flow which is considered two layered flow. The expression for velocity in the porous region with 