'','-','Ravinder Kumar Arya and S. K. Shakya','1-9','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(206,'Grain-size Effects on the Ferroelectric Behavior of Dense Nanocrystalline BaTiO3 Ceramics','A progressive reduction of tetragonal distortion, heat of transition, Curie temperature, and relative dielectric constant has been observed on dense BaTiO3 ceramics with grain size decreasing from 1200 to 50 nm. The correlations between grain size, extent of tetragonal distortion, and ferroelectric properties strongly support the existence of an intrinsic size effect. From the experimental trends the critical size for disappearance of ferro-electricity has been evaluated to be 10  30 nm. The strong depression of the relative permittivity observed for the nanocrystalline ceramics can be ascribed to the combination of the intrinsic size effect and of the size- dependent dilution effect of a grain boundary dead layer.','','-','Amar Pal and Manoj Kumar','23-36','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(207,'A Study of the Magnetic Effects on the Blood Flow in  an Inclined Artery with Stenosis','The aim of this investigation is to study the effect of an externally applied homogeneous transverse magnetic field on the flow characteristics of blood in a single constricted blood vessel. In fact this model is designed for the pulsating blood flow through a rigid inclined artery with axially symmetric stenosis. The leading equations are modeled as the Navier-Stokes equations along with the equation of continuity. The incompressible Navier-Stokes equations are solved numerically by using the finite difference method. Numerical results for the governing equations have been obtained for velocity profile, flux and the wall shear stress. The velocity profile, flux and wall shear stress, are plotted graphically for different values of H (Hartman number) for the better understanding of the problem. The results indicates that, while, increasing the magnetic field causes decreases the velocity profile, flux and wall shear stress.','','-','Sanjeev Kumar and Archana Dixit','37-47','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(208,'Analysis of Bit Error Rate Over AWGN Channel in Presence of Different Forward Error Correction','The performance of WLAN and bit error rate (BER)  is observed with the help of Matlab. Further performance improvement is achieved using forward error correction codes (FEC). Two codes, convolution code (CC) and Reed Solomon Code (RS) are considered for this purpose. In order to provide higher data rate and to mitigate the effect of fading caused by wireless channel uses OFMD (Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing) as a transmission scheme based on multicarrier modulation','','-','Vipin Saini and Ravish Kumar and S. C. Gupta','49-54','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(209,'Band Edge Modulation in Chemically Grown PbS Nano Particles','Nano particles of lead sulphide have been grown successfully in methanolic solution of Pb(NO3)2. Sulphur exchange was achieved by the controlled reaction of Na2S.The colloidal solution was subjected to optical absorption studies. The prepared particles were characterized by UV/Visible absorption spectra in the range 700nm to 250 nm and the corresponding energy band gaps have been calculated assuming the effective masses of the electrons and holes in the nano particles to be same as that of bulk. The particle size has been determined by using the Wang and Mahler theoretical approach. It is found that, the band gap of the bulk compound gradually increases as the size of the particle decreases','','-','Pawan Kumar, T. P. Singh, Viney Kumar, Gulvir Singh, Kamal Sahay and Pravesh Kumar','55-59','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(210,'Realization of CORDIC and Its Application for Arithmetic Logic Unit','The   CORDIC (COordinate Rotation DIgital Computer) algorithm was introduced by Volder in 1959 and   later generalized by Walther.  It  is  an  iterative  algorithm  for  the calculation  of  the  rotation  of  a  two  dimensional  vector  in  linear,  circular  or  hyperbolic coordinate systems. Over the last decade, the CORDIC algorithm has been extended to varied mathematical functions like square roots matrix inversion, filtering, eigenvalue calculations, SVD algorithms, orthogonal transforms, etc. This paper deals with the concept of CORDIC processor and how it can be used for calculation of Singular Value Decomposition (SVD).','','-','Subhash Kumar Sharma, Himanshu Pandey, Vishal Kumar Srivastava','61-67','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(211,'Ecology of Rhizosphere and Non Rhizosphere Soil Mycoflora of Forest Soils of Dehradun District Uttarakhand','This paper deals with different rhizospheric and non rhizospheric forest soils of Dehradun District, giving their physical characteristics and distribution of fungi during different seasons. A total of 23 genera of micro fungi were isolated from 45 soil samples. With the identification of these isolates 57 species plus 2 sterile fungi were identified. Two soil types sandy and sandy-loam were investigated. pH of the soil samples ranged from 7.0 to 8.6 and moisture content ranged from 13.5% to 18.5%. Each soil has unique mycoflora. Deuteromycotina members were dominant. Aspergillus was dominant genus among all the seasons. Maximum numbers of fungal genera were isolated during winter season while maximum species were isolated during summer season. The findings are further beneficial in the control of soil borne diseases and in the conservation of fungi..','','-','S. Guleri, B.S. Bhandari and S. Saxena','69-77','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(212,'A Survey Paper for Simulation Software: Real World Application','Simulation and modeling of a system is widely used in different areas like, manufacturing, network, flight dynamics, control systems, communication and health. Simulation run for hours and days can be converted to few minutes simulation run with the help of computer simulation. Firstly it was used for military in World War II, to model the process of nuclear detonation. After that simulation and simulation techniques are continuously in use for different objectives in different areas. Advanced computer programs can simulate weather conditions, electronic circuits, chemical reactions, atomic reactions, even biological processes. This paper follows simulation software just after the first discovery. It also highlights features and use of simulation software in different kind of industries. Finding of survey traces concept, parameters, requirement and use of variety of simulation software. This paper presents detailed information about the simulation software.','','-','Pratiksha Saxena','79-85','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(213,'Effect of Hydrostatic Pressure on Ga As 1-x Px Material with Different Doping Levels','In the present work, the effect of hydrostatic pressure on the mobility, effective mass and ionization energy of the electrons in conduction valley in GaAs1-xPx materials, taking the effect of band tailing into account, which has not been considered by earlier works. The theoretical analysis is based on an examination of the relative distribution of charge carriers in the valley (000) and (100) as the crystal is subject to hydrostatic Pressure. The donor levels associated with valley (100) and band tail associated with valley (000) have been considered. The effect of the donor level is dominant at higher pressures. The effect of band- tailing is to decrease the number of carriers in the conduction band of first valley, conformity with earlier results','','-','Govind Kumar, R.P. Gairola and S.C. Gupta','87-92','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(214,'Cell Sizes of GSM Network','Global system for mobile communication (GSM) is a globally accepted standard for digital cellular communication. GSM is the name of a standardization group established in 1982 to create a common European mobile telephone standard that would formulate specifications for a pan-European mobile cellular radio system operating at 900 MHz. It is estimated that many countries outside of Europe will join the GSM partnership. . GSM networks operate in four different frequency ranges. Most GSM networks operate in the 900 MHz or 1800 MHz bands. Some countries in the Americas (including Canada and the United States) use the 850 MHz and 1900 MHz bands because the 900 and 1800 MHz frequencyThere are five different cell sizes in a GSM networkmacro, micro, pico, femto and umbrella cells. The coverage area of each cell varies according to the implementation environment.','','-','Sanjeev Uppal','93-100','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(215,'Application of Turing Machine for Simplification of Password or Secret Key Code','In this paper we trying to solve the tractable and non tractable problem using Turing if the problem is tractable then it can solve very feasible but if the problem is non tractable like to find the password which is not locked by any authentication algorithms like RSA or any another, then such type of problem can be solve using turning. As we know the application of turning machine to scan the input symbol and give the output symbol ,and also machine give its actual value tacking these feature of turning machine we solve the non tractable problem.','','-','Y.N.Prajapati, Jitendra Singh and Varsha Gupta','101-105','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(216,'Uttarakhand Education Scenario: An Empirical Study','Knowledge is the greatest gift one can give, for knowledge is imperishable. Even if we light a thousand lamps from one flame, the luster of the first lamp never diminishes. By sharing knowledge and experiences, we can prevent the flower that is this world from ever wilting and ensure that it remains eternally beautiful. By bringing together diverse streams of knowledge, we can create a magnificent river. May this great river of knowledge flow to caress the countries and communities of the world!\r\nUttarakhand is the twenty seventh state of India. The state was created on 9th November 2000. The population of Uttarakhand is 8479562 according to 2001 census. The population density is 195 per square kilometer. Out of which the males constitute 4316401 and females 4163161 of the total population. In the rural areas the population is about 6309317. The decadal increase in the year 1991-2001 is 19.2 and the population density is 159 per sq km (data given in Table 1). The sex ratio is 964 per thousand. The per capita income of the state is Rs12,000 per year. The infant mortality rate is 52.4. \r\nLiteracy is the first and foremost factor contributing directly to human resource development and quality of life, Uttarakhand has 14th position in the country. With the help of various government interventions there has been significant progress in the field of education in Uttarakhand. Literacy percentage of the state is 71.6 against all India average of 65.38. Male and female literacy rates are 83.3 percent and 59.6 percent against the all India figures of 75.85 percent and 54.16 percent respectively. Census data of 2001 shows that the gender gap is still an issue to be addressed in Uttarakhand, wherein focused interventions are required especially in the Cities and farthest habitations. This paper will to help to understand the condition and quality of education in state of Uttarakhand and the projects and government initiatives to upgrade the quality of education.','','-','Kamal Ghanshla and Manish Pandey','107-115','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(217,'Chromatography Analysis for Carotenoids in Maize (Zea mays L.)','Carotenoids are derived from the isoprenoid biosynthetic pathway and are precursors of the plant hormone abscisic acid and of other apo-carotenoids. The first committed step of this pathway is formation of phytoene from geranylgeranyl diphosphate by phytoene synthase (y1/psy1). Maize exhibit considerable natural variation for kernel carotenoids, with some lines accumulating as much as 66.0 ?g/g (Harjes et al. 2008). However, most yellow maize grown and consumed throughout the world has only 0.5 to 1.5 ?g/g ?-carotene. In this experiment, the carotenoid content range from 23.01 to 33.56 g/gm. The highest content of carotenoid is observed in Gaurav (33.56 g/gm) and the lowest content of carotenoid is observed in Tarun (23.01 g/gm).D-765, Amar, Pragati, Navin and Surya contain carotenoid 31.67, 31.61, 29.31, 26.87 and 23.02 respectively. All the treatments are significantly different from each other in the given trait.','','-','Atin Jaiswal, N. K. Singh, Moin Akhtar, J. P. Jaiswal  and G. S. Sekhawat','117-122','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(218,'Analytical Design of a Dielectric Optical Filter','The design of a dielectric filter in the visible region of the electromagnetic spectrum based on dielectric multilayered structure (generally known as photonic crystal) is presented in this paper. The theory of the design of the filter is based on a theory analogous to the Kronig-Penney model in the band theory of solids. The periodic multilayered structure of dielectric materials in rectangular symmetry is considered as a design of our filter. The filter can also be used as an efficient monochromator by appropriate choice of the controlling parameters.','','-','Sushil Kumar and Vipin Kumar','123-127','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(219,'On  Legendre Polynomials of  Pseudo Two Variables  Suggested by S.F. Ragabs Laguerre Polynomials of Two Variables','The present paper deals with the study of Legendre Polynomials   of pseudo two variables suggested by S. F. Ragabs Laguerre polynomials of two variables  . The paper contains certain generating functions, recurrence relations, Rodrigues type formula, orthogonality relation, hypergeometric forms, Laplaces first integral form, expansion of polynomials and its relationship with Legendre polynomials of one variable  .','','-','Mumtaz Ahmad Khan  and Shakeel Ahmed','129-139','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(220,'Design of a Single Channel Filter Using Nonlinearity in One Dimensional Photonic Crystal','Theoretical studies on the reflection properties of one-dimensional GaP/AlGaAs nonlinear photonic crystal have been investigated. Reflectance of these periodic multilayered structures is calculated for different intensities by solving Maxwells electromagnetic equations and using the standard transfer matrix method. The study of reflectance bands of the proposed structures shows that reflectance depends on the intensity of the beam and this property can be exploited in the design of an optically induced single channel filter.','','-','Arun Kumar, Kh. S. Singh and S. P. Ojha','141-147','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(221,'On a Two Variable Analogue of Generalized Heat Polynomials Pn,lema,nue (x, y; u)','The present paper deals with the study of two variable analogue of generalized heat polynomials Pn,?,??(x, y; u). The paper contains certain generating function, a finite sum property, integral representation, Schlaflis contour integral, fractional integral and derivatives, Laplace transform for this polynomials.','','-','Mumtaz Ahmad Khan, Abdul Hakim Khan and Manoj Singh','149-159','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(222,'A Note on Einstein Manifold in P- Sasakian Manifold','In the present paper, we have defined and studied ?-Einstein manifold in the p-sasakian manifold and several theorems have been derived.','','-','R.C.Dimri, T.S.Chauhan, I.S. Chauhan and V.K. Srivastava','161-164','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(223,'Ordering Policy of an Inventory Model for Perishable Items with Linear Trend Stock Dependent Demand and Partial Backlogging','In this paper, we have developed an inventory model over a finite horizon, where demand is taken to be linear function of time and is affected by stock on display for a short known period at the beginning of the cycle. Deterioration rate is assumed to be constant; shortages are allowed and partially backlogged. The backlogging rate is dependent on the duration of waiting time up to the arrival of next lot. For the last period shortages are not allowed. The aim of the model is to determine the optimal number of orders to be placed and the optimal lot sizes for different periods. The model is solved numerically to obtain the optimal solution of the problem.','','-','Bindu Vaish and Sudesh Kumar Garg','165-179','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(224,'Synthesis and Characterization of an Inorganic Ion Exchanger based on Tin(IV)','A new inorganic ion exchanger Tin(IV)tungstosilicate was synthesized. Stannic chloride solution, sodium tungstate solution and sodium metasilicate solution were mixed in different ratios to get different samples. One of the samples was selected on the basis of ion exchange capacity as determined by column method. Ion exchange capacity has also been determined by pH titration method. The material was characterized using IR spectrum, XRD pattern and TGA Curve. Chemical stability of the product was checked in various acidic and basic media. The effect of temperature on ion exchange capacity was studied. The distribution behaviour of the exchanger towards several metal ions like Ca2+, Mg2+, Zn2+, Cu2+, Mn2+, Co2+, Ni2+, Pb2+, Bi3+, Cd2+ was also studied.','','-','Subhash Chand, Seema, Teena and Manju','181-190','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(225,'VoIP over the 802.11 WLAN Network','With fast deployment of wireless local area networks (WLANs), the ability of WLAN to support real time services with stringent quality of service (QoS) is attracting ever-increasing research interest. If QoS service constrained are satisfied and a number of VoIP calls can be supported by a WLAN. Distributed Coordination Function (DCF) and Point Coordination Function (PCF) are two MAC protocols specified in the IEEE 802.11 standard. Upper bound for number of VoIP connections supported in DCF mode is 12 and in PCF mode this number rises to 20. We have proposed an access media mechanism in which voice is transmitted in PCF mode and best-effort traffic in DCF mode. In our access media mechanism polling list arrangement is done dynamically so that only those stations are polled which have voice packets to transmit. We have proposed a multi-queued MAC architecture for the access point. Voice traffic is considered in CBR mode. Our simulation shows that the maximum number of VoIP calls supported by 802.11b is 26 when inter arrival time for voice packets is 20ms and the maximum number of VoIP calls supported by 802.11b is 14 when inter arrival time for voice packets is 10ms.','','-','Niranjan Lal, Mrityunjay Singh','191-200','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','13','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(226,'Generalizations of a Theorem on Appells F4 Function','The present paper contains certain generalizations of a theorem on Appells F4 function given in the form of Theorem 83 in E.D. Rainvilles book (Rainville, 1971). It is hoped many fruitful results will be derived as an outcome of these generalizations.','','-','Mumtaz Ahmad Khan and Bahman Alidad','1-11','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(227,'A Stability Result in Generalized Metric Spaces','In this note we establish a fixed point stability result of a multi-valued mappings in the setting of  b- metric spaces. Several results are also derived as special cases.','','-','Bhagwati Prasad','13-18','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(228,'Common Fixed Point Theorems for Mappings Satisfying the Mann Type Iterations in Banach Spaces','In this paper, we prove that a sequence in C defined by Mann-type iterations converges to a unique common fixed point of four mappings on C satisfying some conditions. Our results extend and improve some results of Cho et al. (1998), Gornicki and Rhoades (1996), Rhoades and Soltuz (2003) and others.','','-','Amit Singh and R. C. Dimri','19-26','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(229,'Prediction of Manpower Wastage in Tamil Nadu Software Industry Using Coxs Regression Approach','In manpower planning, one of the most important variables is completed length of service on leaving a job, since it enables us to predict staff turnover. It is a common phenomenon that some personnel leave an organization after completing a certain period of services in that organization either voluntarily or due to death, retirement or termination, known as turnover or wastage. Wastage creates vacancies to be filled up either by promotion from the lower cadres or by direct recruitment or by a combination of both. The propensity of leaving the job is quantified based on CLS only and it sometimes leads to unrealistic prediction of manpower attrition. In addition to CLS, at the micro level, other factors such as socio-economics indicators or personal and/or familial factors influence the propensity to leave the job. Tamilnadu has been in an enviable position regarding the quality and quantity of manpower in its software industry. In this paper the suitable model is developed, to analyze and predict the pattern of manpower wastage in Tamilnadu software industries using Coxs regression model.','','-','E. Susiganeshkumar and R. Elangovan','27-44','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(230,'Intrusion Tolerant Enhanced Secured Architectural Database System','In this paper, proposes four architectures for Intrusion-Tolerant Database Systems. While traditional secure database systems rely on prevention controls, an intrusion-tolerant database system can operate through attacks in such a way that the system can continue delivering essential services in the face of attacks. With a focus on attacks by malicious transactions, Architecture I can detect intrusions, and locate and repair the damage caused by the intrusions. Architecture II enhances Architecture I with the ability to isolate attacks so that the database can be immunized from the damage caused by a lot of attacks. Architecture III enhances Architecture I with the ability to dynamically contain the damage in such a way that no damage will leak out during the attack recovery process. Architecture IV enhances Architectures II and III with the ability to adapt the intrusion-tolerance controls to the changing environment so that a stabilized level of trustworthiness can be maintained. Architecture V enhances Architecture IV.','','-','P.V.S. Lakshmi Jagadamba and P. Krishna Subba Rao','45-53','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(231,'An Improved Non-Recursive Algorithm for Postorder Tree Traversal and its Implementation in C Language for Binary Search Tree','This paper presents a new non-recursive algorithm and implementation of post order tree traversal of Binary search tree, since we hardly found non recursive solution and its implementation in C language. As we know that in computer science, tree-traversal refers to the process of visiting (examining and/or updating) each node in a tree data structure, exactly once, in a systematic way. Such traversals are classified by the order in which the nodes are visited. There are two ways to visit a Binary search tree: recursively and non-recursively. Most references introduce tree traversal using recursion only. Our literature survey indicated that most references only show the implementations of the recursive algorithms, and only few references address the issue of non recursive algorithms. In this paper, we have investigated and compare recursive and non recursive [Weiss, 2002] and non-recursive algorithm [Akram et al.] for post order, traversal. In this paper we propose a new non-recursive algorithm for postorder traversal of binary search trees that is both efficient and easy to understand. The implementation of this new algorithm was implemented in C language. Our algorithm was found very simple and faster than other non recursive algorithms due to its unique implementation.','','-','Upendra Singh Aswal, Ramesh S Rawat','55-60','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(232,'Estimation of Process Capability Index for Half Logistic Distribution','In this article point estimates of Process Capability Index as suggested by Clements (1989) are studied through simulation when the underlying distribution is Half Logistic distribution.  Moment estimate, maximum likelihood estimate (MLE) and best linear unbiased estimate (BLUE) are used.  A comparison about the performance of these methods is made with the help of the simulated sample characteristics.','','-','R. R. L. Kantam, K. Rosaiah and R. Subba Rao','61-66','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(233,'Secure Software Architectures Using Aspect Oriented Model','The security of a software system is an attribute that permeates the whole system. As such, any attempt to address security concerns in a software system must, of necessity, be global in nature, and security solutions must be applied consistently at every relevant location. One way of achieving these objectives is by separating out security concerns from the rest of the application issues, such that they can be addressed independently and applied globally. A methodology that would encompass these two high-level goals -- separation of security concerns and consistent implementation of security solutions- would pave the road towards secure applications. To implement such a methodology, we chose to use the Aspect-Oriented Programming (AOP) paradigm. AOP is a relatively new programming model that enables the separation of crosscutting concerns while remaining easy to use and integrating well with the development process. We describe a framework, based on the AOP model, for implementing security solutions in a globally consistent manner such that security concerns are modularized.','','-','P. Hari Krishna, A. Nagaraju and D. Sravan Kumar','67-72','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(234,'Binary Signed Digit Multiplier for High  Speed FFT and IFFT Processors','In this paper an attempt has been made to realize a high  speed Binary Signed Digit (BSD) multiplier which takes advantage of the benefits coming from Redundant Binary Signed Digit number system. The design implementation is depicted in high level VHDL code for different standard bit length. Area (A), time (T) and power consumption report is generated for a selected FPGA. Furthermore, the proposed multiplier has a regular cellular array structure similar to an array multiplier, which is suitable for VLSI implementation. The multiplier is excellent in both computational speed and regularity in layout.','','-','Manish Mishra, Vikash Tripathi, Himansu Pandey, Geetika Srivastava','73-79','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(235,'An ID-Based (u, m) Threshold Signcryption Scheme with     (t, n) Shared Unsigncryption','This paper presents an identity based (u, m) threshold signcryption scheme with (t, n) shared unsigncryption. In this scheme any u or more members of the signcrypter group can cooperatively signcrypt the message, but u - 1 or fewer members cannot. For unsigncryption, any third party can verify the validity of the signature, but to recover the message the cooperation of at least t members of the receivers group is required. The proposed scheme has the following advantages: it provides both public verifiability and forward security; the key management problem is simplified because of using ID-based cryptography.','','-','S R Singh, Tej Singh and K K Kanadia','81-91','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(236,'k-Splitting of traffic for minimization of delay, congestion control and optimum network utilization','The traditional routing scheme all traffic along a single shortest path, but k- splitting of traffic strategy split the traffic in several paths(at most k path) in order to reduce the congestion and to optimize network utilization. The model given in this paper shows that distribution of the traffic among several good paths instead of routing all traffic along a single best path is a better approach for minimisation of congestion and optimum network utilization','','-','Pant Durgesh. and Dimri Sushil Chandra','93-102','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(237,'A Two Dissimilar Unit Parallel System with Administrative Delay in Repair and Correlated Life Times','The paper analyses a two non-identical unit parallel system assuming that a delay occur in getting the repairman available with the system due to some administrative actions. The random variables denoting the life times of both the units working in parallel form are correlated having their joint distribution as bivariate exponential. The arrival time distribution of repairman is taken general whereas the repair time distributions of the units are taken exponential. Various important measures of system effectiveness are obtained by using regenerative point technique.','','-','Rakesh Gupta , C. K. Goel and Archana Tomer','103-112','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(238,'The Beta Inverse Weibull Distribution','In this article we introduce a new reliability model of Inverse weibull distribution referred to as the Beta Inverse weibull distribution generated from the logit of a beta random variable. We derive its complete comprehensive treatment of this newly developed reliability model. We also derive its rth moment, rth Inverse integer moment and maximum likelihood estimation. Some other properties such as mean, variance, coefficient of variation, coefficient of skewness and coefficient of kurtosis for Beta Inverse weibull distribution are presented mathematically.','','-','M. Shuaib Khan','113-119','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(239,'Some Common Fixed Point Theorems in 2-Metric Space','The purpose of this paper is to prove some common fixed point theorems in 2-metric space using the notion of compatible mappings introduced by Naidu and Prasad (1986) under Gregu type and  -type contractive conditions. We also prove some theorems using Iseki type contractive conditions. Our theorems improve and extend the results of Fisher et al. (1980), Fisher and Murthy (1987), Iseki (1975) and that of Naidu and Prasad (1986).','','-','L. Shambhu Singh and  L. Sharmeswar Singh','121-129','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(240,'Implementation of IEEE-754 Addition and Subtraction for Floating Point Arithmetic Logic Unit','The IEEE 754 working group has revised the IEEE 754-1985 Standard for Binary Floating-Point Arithmetic to include specifications for decimal floating-point arithmetic. As processor support for decimal floating-point arithmetic emerges, it is important to investigate efficient algorithms and hardware designs for common decimal floating-point arithmetic algorithms. This paper presents novel designs for a decimal floating-point addition and subtraction. We present an addition and subtraction for single precision floating point numbers in IEEE-754 format. They are fully synthesizable hardware descriptions in VHDL. Each one is presented for high speed computing.','','-','\"\"Subhash Kumar Shrama, Himanshu Pandey, Shailendra Sahni  ;\r\nand  Vishal Kumar Srivastava\"','131-140','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(241,'On the Least Absolute Error Estimation of Linear Regression Models with Auto-Correlated Errors','There is considerable evidence that many econometric models make use of variables which give rise to error term distributions characterized by fat-tails or infinite variance. Usually linear models are estimated by the Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) or Maximum Likelihood Estimator, (MLE) by assuming normality. When estimating linear models, where fat-tailed and serially dependent residuals appear, it is important to find robust alternatives to these estimators. This is especially true in the case of small sample estimation. An alternative to the OLS estimator is Least Absolute Error (LAE). In this Paper Least Absolute Error Estimation of Linear Regression Models with Auto Correlated errors are discussed and observed that least squares based on absolute errors are preferable over the methods, when the errors are normally distributed.','','-','S. Eakambaram and R. Elangovan','141-148','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(242,'Some Bi-Recurrent Properties of Kaehlerian Space','In the present paper we have studied bi-recurrent properties of holomorphically projective curvature tensor, Weyl Concircular curvature tensor and Weyl recurrent curvature tensor. The relation between these curvatures has been established. Also necessary and sufficient condition for these relations have been established.','','-','K. S. Rawat, Virendra Prasad and Girish Dhobal','149-154','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(243,'On Decomposition of Curvature Tensor Fields in a Tachibana Recurrent Space of First Order','Takano (1967) studied decomposition of curvature tensor in a recurrent space. Sinha and Singh (1970) studied on decomposition of recurrent curvature tensor field in a Finsler space. Further, Negi and Rawat (1995) studied decomposition of recurrent curvature tensor fields in a Kaehler space. Rawat and Dobhal (2008) studied decomposition of recurrent tensor field in a Kaehlerian recurrent space. In the present paper, we have studied on decomposition of curvature tensor fields in a Tachibana recurrent space of first order by considering the decomposition of curvature tensor field    in terms of a non- zero vector established and a tensor field. Also several theorems have been established and proved therein.','','-','K. S. Rawat  and Nitin Uniyal','155-160','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(244,'On Decomposition of Curvature Tensor Fields In A Kaehlerian Recurrent Space','Takano (1967) has studied decomposition of curvature tensor in a recurrent space; Sinha and Singh (1970) have studied on decomposition of recurrent curvature tensor fields in Finsler space. Further, Singh (1982) has studied on decomposition of recurrent curvature tensor fields in a Kaehlerian space. Singh and Samyal (2004) have studied on decomposition of curvature tensor fields in a Tachibana recurrent spaces. In the present paper, we have considered the decomposition of curvature tensor field Rhijk in terms of a vector field and two tensor fields and several other theorems have been derived.','','-','U S Negi , Kailash Gailor','161-165','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(245,'Some Multiple Hypergeometric Transformations','In this paper, we obtain five new transformations associated with multiple hypergeometric functions of Srivastava, Kamp de Friet and Srivastava-Daoust, using series rearrangement technique and some summation theorems.','','-','Chaudhary Wali Mohd., M. I. Qureshi, Kaleem A. Quraishi and M. P. Chaudhary','167-172','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(246,'Number of Lattice Points Within and On Some Standard Two and Three Dimensional Geometrical Figures.','In this paper, the number of lattice points within and on some two dimensional and three dimensional geometrical closed figures such as circle, ellipse, cardioid, square, rectangle, sphere, cuboid and rectangular parallelopiped etc. are obtained by considering their equations as Diophantine equations.','','-','Hari Kishan , Smiti Agarwal, Megha Rani','173-180','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(247,'Volume Flexible Supply Chain System with Uncertain Lead Time and Stochastic Deterioration','We have fabricated a supply chain inventory system for deteriorating items with uncertain lead time and multiple market demand. In affluent countries, people are more interested about the quality of an item irrespective to its price structure. Taking this fact into consideration, we have taken the rate of deterioration that depends upon both the quality level of an item and time duration for storages. The time related function for deterioration follows a two parameters Weibull distribution. The production rate depends on the quality level of the product with volume flexibility. Partially backlogged shortages are permitted in this model. The model has also been exemplified numerically with sensitivity analysis. The results of the sensitivity analysis have been plotted graphically also.','','-','Surbhi Singhal , S.R. Singh, P.K. Gupta','181-193','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','14','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(248,'Chemical Reaction in steady mixed Convection MHD Viscous Flow over Shrinking Sheet','Chemical reaction and mixed convection in magnetohydrodynamic flow over a shrinking sheet with viscous dissipation has been studied. The effects of chemical reaction, mixed convection and mass transfer on the temperature and concentration of flow have been included in the study. The system of non-linear partial differential equations has been obtained and finally transformed into a set of ordinary differential equations with the help of similarity transformations for the governing flow. This set of equations has been solved and results have carried out for different values of the various physical parameters. The results showing the effect of physical parameters on velocity profile, temperature profile and concentration have been obtained and represented graphically to discuss in detail. The concentration profile decreases with an increase in chemical reaction parameter, Schmidt number, and relative buoyancy parameter.','','-','Navneet joshi , Manoj Kumar and Priya Saxena','155-161','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','12','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(249,'Future of Ecotourism in the Valley of Flowers National Park  (Garhwal Himalaya)','The paper discusses the overall views related to Ecotourism in the valley of flowers. Focus has been given on drainage pattern, resources of Ecotourism in the locale, climatic attributes, and culture and related parameters of villages near the valley, and pilgrimage and social attractions. \r\nThe paper concludes that future of Ecotourism would be in the hands of the authorities serving their upon and the future planning to in situ conservation of valley resources for enjoying the nature in the present as well as in future for our forthcoming generations.','','-','Dr. Shashi K Tiwari,  Dr. Santosh Verma,    Dr. Indu Tiwari','1-28','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(250,'GLOBAL WARMING AND CLIMATE CHANGE: Broad Global impact and Indian scenario','Global warming and climate change refer to an increase in average global temperatures. Natural events and human activities are believed to be contributing to an increase in average global temperatures. This is caused primarily by increases in greenhouse gases such as Carbon Dioxide (CO2).Global warming is the increase in the average temperature of the Earth\'s near-surface air and oceans since the mid-20th century and its projected continuation. Global warming has emerged as one of the most important environmental issues ever to confront humanity. This concern arises from the fact that our everyday activities may be leading to changes in the earths atmosphere that have the potential to significantly alter the planets heat and radiation balance. It could lead to a warmer climate in the next century and thereafter, portending a potpourri of possible effects  mostly adverse.\r\nInternational efforts to address this problem have been ongoing for the last decade, with the Earth Summit at Rio in 1992 as an important launching point, and the Conference of Parties in Buenos Aires in 1998 as the most recent step. Although India as a developing country does not have any commitments or responsibilities at present for reducing the emissions of greenhouse gases such as carbon dioxide that lead to global warming, pressure is increasing on India and other large, rapidly developing countries such as China and Brazil to adopt a more pro-active role. At the same time, the developed countries of the North are trying to limit the extent of their commitments for emission reduction. In this situation, the public and policy makers need to be aware of the ramifications and implications of the global warming problem, even if it is a problem that may manifest itself only sometime in the next century.','','-','Dr (Mrs) Kanchan Singh, Dr M.P.Singh','29-46','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(251,'A PROBABILITY MODEL FOR COMMUTATION PATTERN','The main objective of this paper is to developed an inflated probability model for the commutation pattern from the household. The suitability of the model is tested through observed data.','','-','Himanshu Pandey, Rajendra Tiwari','47-52','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(252,'Strategic human resource management in commercial banks in india','This paper focus on aligning banks HRM (Human Resource Management) practice to corporate Strategy. In present scenario HRM function has undergone some most striking changes, in its increasing involvement in developing and implementing business strategy. The HRM has to perform four strategic functions i.e. acquisition, development, motivation and maintenance, In order to achieve its objective of striking best match between people and organization so as to contribute to the successful survival and growth of the organization and help the people in achieving satisfaction of their economic and other needs. Increasing dependence of banks on advance technology requires highly skilled workforce. HRM aims at developing a well trained workforce which is responsive to customers demand.','','-','Dr. Smt. Preeti Rani','53-58','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(253,'Trends of Disparities in Social Development A Study of District Pauri Garhwal','The present paper seeks to examine trends of disparities in social development in fifteen blocks of district Pauri Garhwal. To measure the trends of disparities in social development we have taken 7 indicators and methods which have been used are as follows-\r\nMethod of percent proportional standardized mean and composite index of development \r\nBalance ratio \r\nIndex of regional imbalance \r\nThe analysis of block wise composite index of development at two points of time suggests that some slight variations in the order of the ranking of blocks are quite perceptible. Moreover the absolute index values for all blocks have increased  except Khirsu and Bironkhal, where index value has decreased in social development. Imbalance has increased in most of the blocks of district Pauri Garhwal except Pauri, Khirsu, Dwarikhal and Jaiharikhal, where imbalance has declined between 1981-90 and 1991-2000.\r\nThe analysis made in the study suggests that there is high degree of imbalance in the social development of district Pauri Garhwal and its reduction demands for adoption of micro level or area based planning. Only area based planning would take proper care of the diversities of different areas and reduce them.','','-','Dr. Harsh singh, Prof. T.P Pant','59-66','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(254,'Geo-Political and Geo-Strategical Status of  South Asia:Refrence to the Himalayan Countries','Reference to the Indias National Security There had been security Problems to India through Nathula- pass and Myanmar even during the pre-independence of Burma. Sikkim of India holds a key position in the security of India against the Himalayan south Asian countries .Through Sikkim, china has straight approach to Chumbi valley of Indika .Incidentally the chain mentioned here is a part of Tibet occupied by China','','-','Vijay Mohan Gaur','67-70','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(255,'Creativity and Learning','Teaching is an art and the creative teacher can be placed in the category of artists. The creative teacher has the capacity of making even a dull topic interesting, while teaching, she is alert to the non-verbal cues from the students, and adjusts her teaching to their needs and level of understanding. But here we are not so much concerned with the overall quality of teaching as with its effect on the students in promoting creativity. We will consider that teaching to be creative which helps the students in the acquisition of problem solving and idea generation techniques and development of those personality traits and abilities that go to make them more creative.','','-','Malvika S. Kandpal','71-76','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(256,'Microfinance and Women Empowerment','Microfinance is now a proven strategy for the development and promotion of the poor. Acclaiming a wide recognition worldwide, microfinance programs have become an integral part of the development policy of almost every country in the world. Impact of microfinance programs have been assessed through many studies and its importance for  upliftment of the masses and women empowerment have been proved. In the past 30 years microfinance has carried many promises of social and economic transformation,  with the shift of targeting women being seen as a major strategic move, through which the promise of social development could be most effectively delivered .Women  empowerment remained the main concern of the microfinance programs, which is evident by the fact that majority of microfinance clients is women. The present work is a review paper examining the performance of the microfinance programs in the arena of women empowerment. Impact of microfinance has been tried to asses at economic, social and cultural, entrepreneurial and physical front. The present study shows that microfinance if implemented well with educating poor women, a fruitful strategy is fro women empowerment.','','-','Dr A.K. Pokhriyal, Vipin Ghildiyal','77-94','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(257,'Role of School Climate in The Academic Achievement of Students','The present study has tried to explore the effect of school climate on, academic achievement of the students. The subjects (75 boys and 75 girls) were taken from two different schools located at Haridwar, and SES was controlled during the selection of sample. School environment inventory by Dr. Karuna Shankar Mishra (1983) was administered on the students. Results revealed that school climate is a important pactor in the academic achievement of the students.','','-','Dr. Preeti Sharma','95-100','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(258,'vkradokn% foo kkfUr dks pqukSrh','ekuo ds iSjksa ds fukku bfrgkl ds vkbus esa ftrus iqjkus gSa] vkradokn dk bfrgkl Hkh mlls de iqjkuk ugha gSA vkfndky ls gh vkradoknh dk;ksZ ds vUrxZr gR;k] vigj.k vkSj funksZk yksxksa ij vusd izdkj ds vR;kpkj gksrs jgsa gSaA vkradokn dk bfrgkl dkQh iqjkuk ,oa mrkj&p<+ko ls izHkkfor jgk gSA foo bfrgkl esa lu~ 1966&67 esa fQfyLrhu ds thyV la?kkZ Zealat Struggle esa lf; *ljdkj* Sacarie uked ,d /kkfeZd lEiznk; }kjk loZizFke vkradokjh xfrfof/k;ksa ds lapkyu ds ,sfrgkfld izek.k feyrs gSA','','NA','Mk0 vorkj flag usxh','121-134','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','h',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(259,'mkjk[k.M ds fj;klrh jkT; fVgjh x<+oky dk HkkSxksfyd lkaLd`frd ,oa ,sfrgkfld ifjp;','NA','','NA','Mk0 t;Jh Fkify;ky','135-140','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','h',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(260,'iskkoj dk.M ,oa ohj pUnz flag x<+okyh','NA','','NA','MkW0vkj0lh0,l0dqaoj','141-150','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','h',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(261,'HkkSxksfydhdj.k dk ekuoh; ewY;ksa ij izHkko','NA','','NA','MkW0 Jherh fujatuk kekZ','151-154','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','19','15','2013-07-23 17:36:30','h',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(262,'izkx~,sfrgkfld ;qx esa vkink izcU/ku esa /keZ dh egRrk','vkink dk bfrgkl ekuo lH;rk ds fodkl ds lkFk izkjEHk gk