nique for computing the radiation pattern of reflection antenna has been presented. Attempts are made to determine theoretically, the approximate accounts on the antenna under several simplifying assumptions. A good agreement is found to be relatively more accurate and numerically coefficients.','','-','Surendra Kumar Roy and Prateek Raj','487-492','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','17','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(265,'A Note on Pseudo Two Variables Jacobi Polynomials','The present paper is a study on pseudo two variables Jacobi Polynomials which has been defined on the pattern of two variable Hermite polynomials due to M.A. Khan and G.S. Abukhammash. The paper contains generating functions, Rodrigues formula, recurrence relations, orthogonality, expansion of polynomials and integral representations for this polynomials.','','-','Mumtaz Ahmad Khan, Abdul Hakim Khan & Sayed Mohammad Abbas','499-508','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','17','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(266,'Production & Characterization of ?-amylase produced by Isolated Thermophillic Bacteria Isolated Stain of Bacillus Q 17','The amylase producer thermophillic bacillus species Q17 was isolated from hot compost soil samples & screening by starch ager plate method the log broth culture of isolated thermophillic bacteria, optimization of growth parameters for isolated thermophillic bacteria. Temperature stability of ? amylase was observed for 1 hours at different temp. (80 to 100C) it was found upto 90C, enzyme synthesis occurred at 65C to 100C with an optimum of 85C the pH 7.0.','','-','Sheetal Swaroop, Krishan Pal, M.P. Singh, Sangeeta','503-508','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','17','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(267,'Multi-Criteria Decision Making Using Fuzzy Logic Approach For Evaluating The Manufacturing Flexibility','Manufacturing flexibility is the ability of a manufacturing system to cope with environmental changes effectively and efficiently. Most operation managers cannot provide exact numerical values to express opinions based on human perception due to ill defined and ambiguity of flexibility assessment. However, fuzzy logic provides a useful tool to deal with problems in which the phenomena are imprecise and vague. The purpose of this study is to measure the flexibility of manufacturing system based on multi-criteria decision making using fuzzy logic approach. In this approach, the performance ratings and importance weights of different flexibility capabilities assessed by experts are expressed in linguistic terms. Fuzzy performance-importance index of each flexibility capability is also devised to help managers identify the main adverse factors and calls for managers to institute an appropriate action plan to improve the flexibility level. An example is also used to illustrate the approach developed.','','-','S.R. Ansari, P. K. Mittal, Ritu Chandna','509-522','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','17','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(268,'Present Status of Floristic Diversity of Golatappar Freshwater Swamp Forest','The present paper deals with the plant diversity of Golatappar freshwater swamp of Doon Valley lies between 30? 04? 30?? to 30? 05? 15?? N latitude and 78? 12? 00?? to 78? 12? 25?? E longitude at 340-560m altitude. Swamp forest is dominated by Shorea robusta, Diospyros malabarica, Pterospermum acerifolium and Syzygium cumini. Shrub layer is dominated by Adhatoda zeylanica, Murraya koenigii, Clerodendrum viscosum, Calamus tenuis, Ipomoea carnea and Ardisia solanacea while dominant herb species are Rorippa-nasturtium-aquaticum, Limnophila rugosa, Fimbristylis dichotoma. Total diversity of the study area is 260 species of which 162 species belong to shrubs, 55 species to trees and 89 herbs. Among herbaceous species dicot and monocot contributes 61.11% and 38.89% respectively. 95% of total shrubs belong to dicot and only 5% to monocot. Species of family Poaceae, Asteraceae, Cyperaceae, Leguminosae and Acanthaceae are most common. The study conducted that Golatappar freshwater swamp still retain its characteristic vegetation complex but as a result of increasing anthropogenic pressure more hardy and invasive species such as Lantana camara and Eupatorium adenophorum are invading the area.','','-','Smriti Sawan, Suman Lata Bisht, Prakriti Dobhal and S.P. Joshi','523-530','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','17','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(269,'Determinants of Saving Behaviour of the Rural Households in India - a Micro Econometric Perspective','Household saving is usually the largest component of domestic savings in developing economies, especially the lower income, predominantly agricultural LDCs. The ability, willingness, and opportunity of households to save overtime can therefore significantly influence the rate and sustainability of capital accumulation and economic growth in developing countries. A few studies (Muraleedharan, D., 2008, Loayza, R. 2000, Shetty S.L., 1990, Joshi V.H, 1970) have been concentrated on the saving behaviour of the households both rural and urban areas in India. But in reality, the saving behaviour of the rural households is quite different from the saving behaviour of developed urban areas in India, as this is based on rural economy. Hence this study itself addressed to study the saving behaviour of rural households in general and agricultural households in particular in the districts of Visakhapatnam and Vizianagaram in the state of Andhra Pradesh.For convenience this study is organized into three sections viz., Section-I which is introductory to the study, the Objective, Methodology and Profile of the study area have also been presented in the same section. Section-II, which analyses the Model specification, problems with Ordinary linear regression, importance of Odds ratio, etc., and Section-III deals with the empirical results of logistic regression for the saving behaviour of the rural households and Conclusions.','','-','Dr.Surya Prakasa Rao Gedela, Mr.Raju Paila','531-542','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','17','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(270,'Variation in Hall coefficient of vacuum evaporated ZnTe thin film with E-M field','Thin film of ZnTe was prepared by vacuum evoparation method. The variation in Hall coefficient RH of prepared thin film was recorded with electromagnetic field of different frequencies (2-20 MHz at 2 MHz steps) and of 5mV,and 10mV amplitudes. The statistical analysis of obtained data was done by R-software which showed that the value of Hall coefficient decreases significantly with increment in frequency of E-M field.','','-','Vaibhav Jain, Ruchi Agrawal, Abhijit Kulshrestha, A. K. Sharma','543-545','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','17','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(271,'Solar Activities and Their Effects on Space and Ground Based Systems','Solar energetic particles (SEPs) and geomagnetic storms are the two primary space weather consequences of coronal mass ejections (CMEs) and their interplanetary counterparts (ICMEs). Space weather can be described as the physical conditions in space that affects human technology in space and on the ground as well as life on Earth in a number of ways including satellite drag, satellite sensor degradation, effects of geomagnetically induced currents on the power grid and pipelines, radiation threat to crews of highflying aircraft and astronauts, high-frequency communication outages in the polar regions, long distance telecommuni