oups and Ramji Lal studied perfectly stable groups through right transversals.','','-','Nirbhay Mathur, Swapnil Srivastava','281-285','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','18','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(286,'A Two Non-Identical Unit Cold Standby System with Random Change, Imperfect Switching Device & Correleted Failure & Repair of Units','The present paper deals with the analysis of two non-identical units (unit-1 and unit-2) cold standby system with random change, imperfect switching device and correlated failure and repair of units. Initially unit-1 is operative and unit-2 kept as cold standby. The operative and standby units are interchanged with constant rates after a random amount of time. This process is automatic for which no switching device is required. The switching device, used to detect the failed unit and to switch the standby unit into operation, may be found fail at the time of need with fixed known probability. A single repair facility is available with the system to repair the failed units and failed switching device with priority given to switching device. The failure and repair times of both the units are assumed to be correlated random variables having Bivariate exponential with different parameters.','','-','Rakesh Gupta, S.C. Sharma and Vikas Saxena','287-296','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','18','18','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(287,'On Ageing Properties of Semi-Markov System and Total Time on Test Transforms','Ageing properties of first passage time of semi-Markov performance process of a multistate system are considered. The lifetime of the multistate system is the first passage time from up states to the down state. We give the method of identification of the failure rate model of the life distribution based on the transition probability functions.',