here is no significant relationship between Adjustment and Value pattern of Higher Secondary students.','','-','Sangeeta Srivastava , Meenu Choudhary','260-267','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','21','27','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(412,'NA','NA','','-','Neelam sharma','268-270','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','21','27','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(413,'Dr A.P.J Abdul Kalam & Meaning of Education','Dr. Kalam trusts that education is a pillar of a developed and a powerful country. Education is the most important element for growth and prosperity of a nation. He trusts that education is the most important area of service sector and it provides required knowledge and skill to do any work. On the basis of past experience of his student life, he suggested that real teaching is giving theoretical lessons coupled with practical examples available in nature. He has provided that learning needs freedom to think and freedom to imagine and both have to be facilitated by the teacher and the education system.','','-','Payal Govil, Trilok Chandra','271-273','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','21','27','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(414,'A Tribute to Tagore on his 150th Birth Anniversary from Sensuousness to Mysticism : A Perspective on Select Songs of Rabindranath Tagore, Embodying the East-West Synthesis','Gurudev Rabindranath Tagore, rightly called a Vishwa Manav, is indeed a luminous example of the happy synthesis of the East and the West. Steeped in the divine mystic tradition of the Vedas and the Upanishads and profoundly influenced by the Ramayana, the Mahabharata, the mystic Kabir and the Bauls of Bengal, Tagore also assimilated the Western thought through Rousseau and others. Many of his songs exemplify this merging of two cultures.\r\nThe objective of this paper is two-fold : to reveal the transition from sensuousness to mysticism in the songs of Tagore and to explore the presence of this dual strain in the poems of Wordsworth, Shelley and Keats','','-','MadhuD Singh','274-279','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','21','27','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(415,'MHD Visco-Elastic Boundary Layer Flow Through Porous Medium with Free Convection Past a Continuous Moving Surface with Heat Source','In the present paper the behavior of free convective boundary layer flow of an electrically conducting visco-elastic, incompressible fluid through porous medium over a continuously moving flat surface in the presence of uniform magnetic field with heat source and constant suction is studied. A uniform magnetic field is assumed to be applied perpendicular to the moving flat surface. The velocity, temperature and concentration field are obtained. The effect of various parameters on the velocity, temperature and concentration profile as discussed graphically.','','-','Ajay Kumar Sharma,  U. R. Singh,  Rajeev Jha','163-170','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(416,'Stability Of Incompressible Dusty Flow Between Two Rotating Cylinders in Presence of Magnetic Field','In this Paper, we discuss the hydromagnetic stability of incompressible Dusty flow between two rotating Cylinders. Here we derived the equations of motion for clean fluid and then for dust particles. The effect of dust is explained by two parameters ; the concentration of dust and a relaxation time  .  The linearized Perturbation Equations of dust particles are explained under the assumption that the relaxation time  is small and obtained  the analytical results','','-','Gurpreet Kaur, Shivdeep Singh Patial,Arun Kumar','171-179','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(417,'Theoretical Investigation of Non-Linear Visco-Elastic Phenomena By Methods of Irreversible Thermodynamics','The paper deals with the theoretical investigation of non-linear visco-elastic phenomena by the method of irreversible thermodynamics. The simplest visco-elastic media are considered. The temperature of the medium T and some symmetric tensor aij characterizing recoverable shear deformation of the system are introduced as the thermodynamic parameters which are the arguments in the expression for the specific free energy f. The tensor aij is chosen as a basic parameter because it is assumed that at local thermodynamic equilibrium a fluid particle exhibits elastic properties. A non-equilibrium state develops through the fact that in elasto-viscous fluids unrecoverable shear rate deformation appears to be due to dissipative processes. For internally isotropic (isotropic at rest) fluids, the relation, \r\n                                                                f  =  f (T, A1, A2, A3, )  is valid.\r\n where Ak are basics invariants of the tensor aij (using Euler co-ordinate system ).','','-','Prabir Kumar Shrivastava, Praveen Kumar , Deepika Sonal,Pankaj Kumar','181-186','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(418,'A Study of Vorticity of Hydromagnetic Free Convection\r\nFlow past an infinite Vertical Plate','The present paper deals with the study of vorticity of hydromagnetic free convection flow past an infinite vertical plate. The vorticity of the flow has been found for different values of Prandtl number (P ), magnetic parameter (M), permeability parameter ( ), and Grashof number ( ). Some important conclusions have been drown on the effect of Prandtl number, magnetic parameter, permeability parameter and Grashof number over the vorticity of the flow.','','-','P.K. Mittal, Yuv Raj Sharma, Ajay Sharma','187-192','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(419,'MHD Flow of a Visco-Elastic (Walters Liquid Model-B) Fluid Through Porous Medium With Heat Source','An analysis of unsteady flow of a visco-elastic (WALTERS LIQUID MODEL-B) fluid through porous medium with heat source in presence of a uniform magnetic field is presented. The effect of Hartmann number M, porosity parameter K and visco-elastic coefficient E, Prandtl number Pr, Schmidt number Sc, heat source parameter S and time t on the velocity, temperature and concentration distribution are discussed graphically.','','-','Bhagwat Swarup, Kuldeep','193-198','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(420,'Flow of an Elastico-Viscous Second-Grade Fluid Due to a Rotating Disc With Uniform High Suction','The present paper deals with the problem of the effects of uniform high suction on the flow of an elastico-viscous second-grade fluid due to a rotating disc. Solution for the governing non-linear equations has been obtained by series solution as well as numerical methods. Effects of suction and elastico-viscosity on the velocity field have been studied in detail and shown graphically.','','-','H. G. Sharma, Parul Chaddha,  P. Pradhan','203-213','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(421,'A Common Fixed Point Theorem for a Pair of Weakly Compatible Maps Satisfying a Contractive Condition of Integral Type in a Cone Metric Space','In this paper we establish a fixed point theorem for a pair of weakly compatible maps satisfying a contractive condition of integral type in a cone metric space. Our result generalizes and extends the results of K. Jha [1], A. Branciari [4] and various well known similar results.','','-','R.K. Saini, Pardeep Kr. Rana, Sunil Kumar','605-608','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(422,'An Inventory Model for Deteriorating Items with Time and Stock-Dependent Consumption Rate and Shortages Under Inflation and Time Discounting','In this paper we successfully provide a rigorous and efficient method to derive the optimal solution for the inventory models with deteriorating items and multi dependent consumption rate. We have taken a more realistic demand rate that depends on two factors, one is time, and the other is the stock level. The stock level in itself obviously gets depleted due to the customers demand. As a result, what we witness here is a circle in which the customers demand is being influenced by the level of stocks available, while the stock levels are getting depleted due to the customers demands. This assumption takes the customers interests as well as the market forces into account. The demand rate is such that as the inventory level increases, it helps to increase the demand for the inventory under consideration. While as the time passes, demand is depends upon the various factors. The competitive nature of the market has been accounted for by taking partial, time dependent, backlogging into consideration. An optimal replenishment policy is derived when the present valve of total cost is minimized. A numerical example is considered to illustrate the procedure. In addition the sensitivity analysis of the optimal solution with respect to the parameters is carried out. The mathematical models of an inventory problem are based on the  following assumptions and notations.  The consumption rate D(t) at any time t is assumed to be ? + ? I(t) + ? t-ds, where ? is a positive constant, ? is the stock-dependent demand rate parameter, 0 ? ?, ?  ? 1, and I(t) is the inventory level at time t. The replenishment rate is infinite and lead time is zero. The planning horizon is finite. Shortages are backlogged at the rate of e?t where 0 < ? <1 and t is the waiting time for next replenishment. The deterioration rate is a + b t; a, b > 0. Product transactions are followed by instantaneous cash flow..','','-','Vikash, S. Yadav, S. R. Singh','609-620','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(423,'An Inventory Model for Decaying Items with Inflation under Permissible Delay in Payments','This paper present an inventory model for deteriorating items with multivariate demand rate under inflationary environment. We have taken a more realistic demand rate that depends on two factors, one is time, and the second is the stock level available. The stock level in itself obviously gets depleted due to the customers demand. As a result, what we witness here is a circle in which the customers demand is being influenced by the level of stocks available, while the stock levels are getting depleted due to the customers demands. This assumption takes the customers interests as well as the market forces into account. The demand rate is such that as the inventory level increases, it helps to increase the demand for the inventory under consideration. While as the time passes, demand is depends upon the various factors. The competitive nature of the market has been accounted for by taking permissible delay in payments into consideration. Finally, the results have been illustrated with the help of numerical examples. Also, the effects of changes of different parameters are studied graphically.','','-','Ajay Kumar Saini, A. P. Singh, S. R. Singh','621-630','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(424,'Effect of Cadmium Toxicity on the Yield of Different Plant Species in Sandy Loam and Sewage Water Irrigated Soil','Cd phytoextraction is a promising and environment friendly approach for soil decontamination. Plant potential for Cd extracting generally depends on shoot Cd concentration and shoot biomass yield. In the present experiments, this technology has been tested by six plant species in pot experiments. During this study, different Cd concentrations were given to different pots. The results indicated that there was increase in the biomass yield in the sewage water irrigated soil, over the sandy loam soil. In this study, the response of different plant species, in the sandy loam soil and sewage water irrigated soil has been observed.','','-','A K Sharma, Pushpendra','631-638','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(425,'Effect of Azimuthal Magnatic Field on Strong Shock in Real Gas Atmosphere','Effect of azimuthal magnetic field on strong shock propagating in non-uniform real gas atmosphere is investigated by Whitham method. Neglecting the effect of overtaking disturbances, analytical expressions for shock velocity and shock strength are obtained. Their dependence on propagation distance, adiabatic index, density parameter and magnetic field are discussed with help of computed results. The results obtained here are compared with those for ideal gases.','','-','R. P. Yadav, Satyendra Kumar, Amita Rani, T.V.S Yadav','639-650','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(426,'Proline Biosynthesis and Accumulation in Plants: A Review','Abiotic stresses such as excess of salt, low temperature and water deficit influence the normal metabolic and biochemical constituents of plant cells. Oxidative damage to cell membranes by active oxygen species is the prominent consequence of the adverse effect of abiotic stresses. Proline (Pro) accumulation is a common physiological response in many plants in response to a wide range of biotic and abiotic stresses. Controversy has surrounded the possible role(s) of proline accumulation. In this review, knowledge on the regulation of Pro metabolism during development and stress, results of genetic manipulation of Pro metabolism, biosynthesis and current debate on Pro toxicity in plants are presented.','','-','Atin Jaiswal, NK Singh, GS Shekhawat, Moin Aktar, JP Jaiswal','651-660','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(427,'A Note on the Vorticity in Effect of Thermal Diffusion on Steady Laminar Free Convective Flow Along a Moving Porous Hot Vertical Plate in the Presence of Heat Source with Mass Tansfer','The purpose of the present problem is to investigate the vorticity in effect of thermal diffusion on steady laminar free convective flow through porous medium along a moving porous hot vertical plate in the presence of heat source with mass transfer. The vorticity profiles Gr >0 (flow on a heated plate) are depicted graphically and discussed in detail. The skin friction coefficient is also obtained in this paper.','','-','S..K. Shakya,Shri Prakash','211-214','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(428,'On Radio Bursts and Their Relation to the Coronal Mass Ejections','Radio burst in the interplanetary medium are caused due to energetic electrons from the Sun .In this article We have described the basic facts for understanding type I,II,III,IV,V, and U bursts in the contest of white light observation, and their relation with the coronal mass ejections and solar flares. We have shown the association of flares and CMEs with the type II, and III, radio bursts, which occur predominately with all other types of bursts. It is concluded that the radio bursts can provide useful information about solar sources and. We interpreted that the burst were produced by electron beam accelerated in blast wave shocks and injected along open magnetic field lines (Gopalswamy et al., 2005).','','-','Joginder Sharma, Anshu Gupta, Nishant Mittal , Udit Narain','661-670','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(429,'Impact of Demographic Factors on Female Purchasing Decisions (A study on rural areas of Distt. Muzaffarnagar, U.P.)','The objective of this research is to investigate the effect of demographic variables on the purchase decision among females in the rural parts of Uttar Pradesh. The total of 300 females is the sample size. Villages are from district Muzaffarnagar. Structured questionnaires were used to interview females. The major findings wereFemales are found to play a more positive role; factors infusing were education, income level, and occupation location of the village etc.','','-','Babita tyagi and Raju Tyagi','671-678','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(430,'Graph Theory and Schemes like NREGS','Under the scheme of National Rural Employment Guarantee Scheme (NREGS), all those who are willing to work at the minimum wage are offered work for a minimum period of 100 days. Those seeking employment are to report in those rural areas where the employment programmed is being launched. Through the scheme Government wishes to construct transportation network connecting all the villages which are of lack of easy accessibility. The paper tries to determine the road network of minimal cost of villages. The paper aim at explaining concept of graph which may be utilized to define relations between different situations and to find optimal solutions.','','-','Sanjeev Kumar, B. K. Singh, Nisha Agarwal','679-684','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(431,'Dispersion and its Management in Single Mode Optical Fibres at High Speed Optical Networks','This paper deals with the dispersion in single mode optical fibre at high speed optical networks. Dispersion takes place at all speeds, and becomes predominant at high data rate. However, pulse spreading caused by chromatic dispersion, particularly, needs to be taken care of more seriously. Another type of dispersion, i.e. polarization mode dispersion (PMD) also causes the pulse to spread and this puts a limit on fibre bandwidth. Therefore, it is essential to manage the dispersion by way of dispersion compensation methods. Efforts have been made to elaborate the effects of chromatic dispersion and PMD at high data rates in single mode fibres and compensate them. The magnitude of chromatic dispersion is larger but easy to manage. However, PMD is smaller, but harder to compensate.','','-','R.L.Sharma','685-694','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(432,'Insertion Reaction of Organo-tin Compounds','In this paper, the compound (R)3SnN3 has been found to react with phenylisothiocyanate in absence of solvent , in the presence of N2 atmosphere forms Tetrazole-5-thione (I) where R={p-ClC6H4,p-FC6H4, p-CH3C6H4}. (R)3SnN3 undergo Cyclization reaction with phenylisocynate form cyclic products. The behavior of Tin-Nitrogen bond is different as compared to other group14 and 15 organometal azide as they give unstable cyclic thiatriazoline-thione (v) derivatives. (R)3SnN3 has cyclic structure which has been derived by IR Spectroscopic dated by IR Spectroscopic data.','','-','Neha goel, Rekha Khara','695-698','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(433,'A Mssbauer Spectroscopic study of the Mahadevpur Meteorite','Mssbauer studies of the Mahadevpur meteorite fell on February 21, 2007 in Arunachal Pradesh and Tinsukia District of Assam, show that the main iron minerals in it are Fe-Ni (Kamacite/taenite), troilite, olivine and pyroxene. These provide characteristic signatures of ordinary chondrites. Mssbauer absorption areas corresponding to different phases favour its classification as H ordinary chondrites.','','-','Abhijit Kulshreshtha, Neeraj Bijlani, H.S. Singh, Vaibhav Jain','699-702','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(434,'Analysis of Management Information System Report Through Electronic Equipment','Information is an important resource in the effective management of any organization. Information is any fact or set of facts, which is useful in making a specific decision among alternative courses of action. The information potential of data is enhanced by refinement, which involves selection, processing, sorting, and re-organizing the data into a usable form and transmission to the appropriate end-users.\r\nThe available MIS report is not utilized according to the prescribed roles of employees and senior administrative staff between the organization and the outside world.\r\nThis might not be unconnected with organization being better funded than the state organization. MIS functions must stay close to the pulse of the business so that their key issues, problems and opportunities are deeply understood.','','-','Nirmal Sharma','703-708','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(435,'Specific Absorption Rate Calculation and Rate of Temperature Change in Tissues Due to Radio Antenna','The induced electric field, specific absorption rate (SAR) and resulting temperature change at various distances in different tissues are evaluated. The change in temperature can heat the tissues with passage of time. Though the change of temperature can be limited by the thermoregulatory system of the biological body to some extent, extra stress caused to tissues may result into some kind of irregularity in the body. Therefore, the minimum distance of the transmitters from the populated area must be recommended and should be followed strictly.','','-','P.P. Pathak, Hemendra Tripathiand and Vijay Kumar','709-716','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(436,'A Two Warehouse Inventory Model For A Deteriorating Item With Exponential Demand Rate, Partially Backlogged Shortages','In this study the motion of Viscoelastic fluid has been analyzed analytically by using linear stability theory. The Darcys of is used to explain the fluid motion and the motion of the fluid is taken without applied magnetic field. The linear and non linear stability analyses of initially quiescent, horizontal porous layer which are saturated with Viscoelastic fluids are conducted. The effect of relaxation parameter on the variation of Rayleigh Darcy number is also investigated','','-','Ajay Kumar Singh and S.R. Singh','717-734','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(437,'A Deteriorating Inventory Model for Shortages and Trapezoidal Type Demand Rate','It is observed that demand of seasonal product fruits, eg. Mango, Orange etc over the entire time horizon is three folded. At the beginning of the season it increases, in the mid of the season it decreases and becomes asymptotic. In the literature of inventory after the development of classical economic order quantity (EOQ) model researchers extensively studied several aspects of inventory modeling by assuming constant demand rate. But in a real market demand of a product is always in dynamic state due to the variability of time, price or even of the instantaneous level of inventory displayed in retail shop.\r\nTrapezoidal type demand pattern is generally seen in the case of any fad or seasonal goods coming to market. The demand rate for such items increases with the time up to certain time and then ultimately stabilizes and becomes constant, and finally the demand rate approximately decreases to a constant, and finally the demand rate approximately decreases to a constant or zero, and the begins the next replenishment cycle. We think that such type of demand rate is quite realistic and a useful inventory replenishment policy for such type of inventory model is also proposed.','','-','Renu Chaudhary, S. R. Singh','735-750','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(438,'Synthesis and Characterization of Thorium Selective a New Inorganic Ion Exchanger','Bismuth(III)tungustophosphate, a new inorganic cation exchanger, was synthesized. Its ion exchange capacity for Na+ was found to be 1.0 meq/g-1. The ion exchanger was characterized by XRD, FTIR, TGA and some other studies. By the analysis of the exchanger it was found that all the expected components are present in the ion exchanger. The state of the exchanger is found to be semicrystalline. The ion exchanger is found to be stable against some acidic & basic solutions of different concentration. Distribution studies was done & kd values were calculated. The exchanger has the maximum Kd value for thorium and minimum for cadmium ions. Thermal & chemical studies were also performed.','','-','Subhash Chand, Seema, Brajesh Pal, Rekha','751-760','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(439,'Synthesis and Characterization of Antimony(III) molybdophosphate and Its Use As A Pb(II) Selective Inorganic Ion-Exchanger','A three component inorganic cation exchanger [Antimony(III) molybdophosphate] was prepared by mixing the solutions of 0.1M antimony trichloride, 0.1M sodium molybdate and 0.1M orthophosphoric acid in 1:1:2 ratio respectively. This cation exchanger was found to possess 0.58 meq/g ion exchange capacity for Na+ ions.  The chemical stability of the exchanger has been checked in neutral, acidic and basic media to characterize the exchanger. The exchanger was also characterized on the basis of thermal stability, XRD, SEM, FTIR, distribution coefficient and TGA analysis. Thermal studies showed that the IEC of the exchanger decreases with increase in temperature. The X-Ray Diffraction study and SEM showed the amorphous nature of the exchanger. FTIR confirmed the presence of all the expected components in the ion exchanger. Distribution coefficients (Kd) for ten metal ions were calculated. On the basis of distribution studies, the exchanger was found to be highly selective for Pb++. Separation of Pb++ from other metal ions has been successfully achieved. TGA analysis exhibited weight loss of the exchanger on increasing the temperature to an extent.','','-','Subhash Chand, Seema, Arti, Chandra Vijay Chahal','761-770','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(440,'Two Storage inventory model for deteriorating items with exponential demand and shortages','In this paper, the two warehouse inventory problem for deteriorating items with exponential demand, shortages is considered. Holding cost is linear increasing function of time. We assume that the inventory costs in RW are higher than those in OW. In addition, shortages are allowed in the owned warehouse and the backlogging rate of unsatisfied demand is assumed to be a decreasing function of the waiting time. The objective of this study is to find the optimal inventory policies with profit maximization technique.','','-','S R Singh, Vipin Kumar','771-784','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(441,'A Study on Robustness of Sequential Normal Testing Procedure','Several studies deals with the non- robust character of various types of acceptance plans. Many such studies also analyze the robust character of sequential testing procedures when the underlying failure time distribution has a monotone failure rate. A vast literature on the life testing plans in the Bayesian framework is also available where updating prior with experimental data has been the main concern. Highlighting the point that the basic normal lifetime distribution can be updated in respect of prior variations in its mean, the present study deals with the analysis of  the robust character of sequential normal testing procedures(SNTP) when the mean of the basic normal distribution is considered as a random variable. The robust character of the consistency of the random variable  n, in view of prior variations, is also analyzed','','-','Abha Chandra, K.K. Sharma, Birjesh Kumar','785-796','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(442,'Design of Nodes in Wireless Sensor Network Using RF Module','In many situations a communication link between to devices becomes essential. This communication can be wired or wireless. If two devices are close to each other (like a MCU and a Memory) a wired link is preferred. However in many situations two devices are reasonably far apart. The data transmission can be achieved using Infrared (IR) and radio frequency (RF). IR requires line of sight (LOS) path between the transmitter and receiver and hence is not used frequently. Instead, RF is used in wireless sensor network as it implements a wireless link in which the waves can penetrate a limited number of walls. In that case a wireless link is preferred. Two popular wireless communication technologies are\r\n1.	IR Communications \r\n	Used in IrDA, and Remote controls\r\n	Short Range\r\n	Requires two devices to be in line of sight.\r\n	There should be no Opaque Obstacle in between the devices.\r\n	Easy and low cost to implement\r\n2.	RF Communication \r\n	Widely used, including Bluetooth,Radios,Cell phones, Satellite etc\r\n	Wide range, from few meters to millions of kilometers (Can be Used to control Robots in Mars)','','-','Sanjay Singh, Sukumar Ray Chaudhuri, Rajesh singh','795-806','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(443,'An Inventory Model for Decaying Items with Time and Stock Dependent Demand Rate Under the Effect of Inflation','In this paper, an inventory model is developed for decaying items with time and stock dependent demand rate. The effect of life time and the effect of inflation are also considered in this study. The competitive nature of the market has been accounted for by taking permissible delay in payments into consideration. The deterioration rate is taken as two parameter Weibull distribution function of time. The model is developed to determine optimal replenishment policy by minimizing total system running cost of entire season. Numerical examples reveal that our optimization procedure is very accurate and rapid.','','-','Pawan Kumar, N. K. Gaur','807-820','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(444,'Security Issues & Policy in E-Governance','-','','-','Sumit Kumar Kapoor, Shastri Rama Krishnan J','821-824','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(445,'The Structural Studies and Characterisation of Copper(I) and Copper(II) Complexes with N,N,N\',N\',N\"-pentakis     (4-methyl, benzimidazol-2-yl-methyl) diethylene triamine Multidentate Ligand','The Copper complexes with formula [Cu(C49H53N13)X3]X.7H2O have been synthesized and isolated by N,N,N\',N\',N\"-pentakis(4-methyl, benzimidazol-2-yl-methyl) diethylene triamine multidentate ligand and X is an exogenous anionic ligand (X=  ,  ,  , NCS, etc.) Their structures have been established on the basis of chemical analysis molar conductance, magnetic measurement 1HNMR, EPR, cyclic voltammetry, IR spectroscopy and electronic spectral studies, ligand have light coordinating sites viz., five pendant benzimidazolyl arms (five azomethine nitrogen atom) and three tertiary amine nitrogen via methylene bridge. Cu(II) complexes are binucleating EPR - studies provide support for a weak magnetic exchange interaction between the two copper(II) ions via the ligand bridge. Both CuA and CuB have different stereochemistry as revealed by physical studies.','','-','Megh Raj Singh','825-832','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(446,'MATHEMATICAL MODELLING OF THE TRANSIENT HEAT MIGRATION IN HUMAN SKIN AND SUBCUTANEOUS USING LAPLACE TRANSFORMATION TECHNIQUE','In this paper, we study transient temperature distribution in SST taking into account heat conduction, heat carried by perfusion of blood in the capillary beds and metabolic heat generation in the tissues. We assume that the outer surface of the skin is exposed to a dry and cool environment with perspiration. The physical quantities are assumed to have different values in all the three regions depending on the physiology of (SST). Our chief interest in the present study is to obtain interface temperature in the SST for the transient case for various values of the skin surface temperature.','','-','M.S. Bisht H.M.Pandey, A.P. Singh and Amit singh Negi','833-840','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(447,'On Class of Estimators for the Product of Two Population Means Using Auxiliary Character in Presence of Non-response','Two classes of estimators for estimating the product of two population means using an auxiliary character in presence of non response are considered and the expressions for the bias and mean square error of the suggested estimators to the first degree of approximation are derived. Conditions for attaining minimum mean square error of the proposed class of estimators are obtained. An empirical study is carried out in support of the problem.','','-','B. B. Khare and R. R. Sinha','841-846','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(448,'Construction of Chain Sampling Plan (0,1) indexed through the convex combination of AOQL and MAAOQ','The Average Outgoing Quality Limit (AOQL) is the average quality that the consumer will receive in the long run when the defective items are replaced by non-defective items. The construction of sampling plans based on AOQL is largely consumer oriented. The Maximum Allowable Average Outgoing Quality (MAAOQ) is a producer oriented concept which is the average outgoing quality at Maximum allowable percent defective (MAPD). MAPD is the inflection point of the OC curve.  Many authors in the past have constructed sampling plans indexed through AOQL, MAPD, and MAAOQ.  The chain sampling plan ChSP(0,1)  developed by Dodge and Stephens (1966) is a generalization of Dodges (1955) chain sampling plan. This paper introduces a new concept AOQcc which is the convex combination of AOQL and MAAOQ with the gain parameter?. This plan may safeguard the interests of both producer as well as consumer by properly choosing a right combination using the gain parameter ?. Tables are presented for the construction of Chain sampling plan (0,1)','','-','R.Radhakrishnan and M.Mallika','1-6','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(449,'An approach for Software Reliability Growth Model Selectiion and Deciding Software Release','Software reliability is one of the most important attribute of software quality. Developing reliable software is the difficult problem which software industry facing. It is also very hard problem to know whether or not the software being delivered is reliable .There exist a large no of software reliability growth models for reliability prediction. There does not exist a single model which can be universally recommended or can be used (fitted) in all cases. Therefore, recent works have been focused on selecting of software reliability model which is appropriate for the cumulative failure data. We proposed an algorithm for selection of most appropriate software reliability growth model according to the failure data. If the Software reliability Growth model pass the proposed criteria they may be used to make the release decision. We eliminate some weaknesses in previously published algorithm strigfellow, 2002 and add some useful part to the algorithm.. The algorithm is tested with publically available data set and we analysis the performance of the algorithm.','','-','Amit Bindal, Gurpreet Singh','7-16','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(450,'Application of Graph in Educational Sector','The great challenge for the Government and private technical Institutions in India is to impart quality education to generate industry competent professionals. In last ten years, a number of educational institutions came into existence. If we analyze the net outcome, we find  (i) Passing out students are semitrained (ii) Institutes are facing acute shortage of experienced faculty (iii) Employees turnover rate is alarmingly high in these institutions. (iv) The prevailing situation is chronic and it is very much possible that institutions which were born in geometric progression may vanish at much faster rate. Now, a time has come to examine the strategies and tactics with the intention of efficient allocation of scare resources to strengthen educational sector in India. In this competitive world of advanced technology where the changes and development run together, enough infrastructures has been developed in the sector and the private sector is ever willing to inject much more. The paper investigates an efficient and effective mechanism to identify resources and their allocation through graph for rigid quality assurance in Educational Sector.','','-','Sanjeev Kumar, B. K. Singh, Nisha Agarwal,','17-24','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(451,'Security Metrics: Needs and Myths','In the growing area of interconnected computer, security is very essential task. Security in its most basic meaning is the protection from intruders. Therefore the issue of security metrics has seen considerable activity in recent times, and there are numerous approaches to monitoring and measuring \"security\" available. However, the majority of these efforts generally apply to subsections of technical, or IT, security with a few notable exceptions. While these technical metrics are in many cases very effective at the specific task for which they were designed, they say little about the overall security, or safety, of the organization and provide little guidance for effective management. Measuring the state of \"safety\" of an organization is vastly broader than knowing how many packets a firewall dropped and is typically well beyond the scope of IT, or for that matter, information security.','','-','Arun Bakshi, Khaleel Ahmad, Nitesh Kumar','25-34','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(452,'Digital Watermarking with Hopfield Neural Networks','Digital watermarking has been proposed as a method to enhance data security, confidentiality and integrity. The rapid development of digital media provides a great convenience for adopting, using, modifying the information. The development in computer network communications make information transmission relatively simple and quick but, there can also be chances of attacks on the digital media that is being transmitted. In this paper we proposed a Digital watermarking technique with the Hopfield Neural network for the authentication and copyright protection of audio, video and still images. Different from the traditional methods, the watermark is embedded in the synapses of Hopfield Neural Network rather than the cover image. Hence the quality of the watermarked image is almost same as the original cover image. In addition, the quality of the extracted watermark image does not degrade after most attacks, because the watermark is stored in the synapses.','','-','V.K. Katiyar, Vinod Kumar','35-42','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(453,'A Psychological Study of Socio-Economic Status and Well-Being','The present study focuses at the understanding of Socio-economic status and well being with the special reference of age groups and areas.\r\nThe study was planned as following the strength of socio-economic status (SES)2 (high SES, low SES) x area 2  (urban, rural) x age groups 2 (younger Ss, older Ss) factorial design was used and the well-being was tested. In each treatment condition 20 Ss were placed. The socio-economic status was measured by poverty scale developed by Sharma Krishna (2008). This is the reliable and valid measure of socio-economic status. The well being measure was developed by Nagpal & Sel (1968). The obtained results clearly display the differential influecene of high SES vs Low SES, urban vs rural, younger Ss vs older Ss on well-being measure.','','-','Krishna Sharma  and P.S.N. Tiwari','201-208','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Allied Sciences','22','24','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',7,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(454,'Poverty and approval motive: A psychological study','The present study focuses at the understanding of  approval motive with the special reference of poverty level and age groups.\r\nThe study was planned as following the poverty level2 (W.S. vs. S.S.) x age groups (youth vs. adult) factorial design, was used and approval motive was tested. In each treatment condition 20 Ss were placed. The poverty seals (P.S.) was developed by Sharma Krishna & Tiwari P.S.N. (2008). This is the reliable and valid measure of poverty. The approval motive scale was developed by N.K.M. Tripathi (1978). The obtained results clearly display the differential influence of W.S vs. S.S., youth vs. adult on approval motive.','','-','Krishna Sharma and P.S.N. Tiwari','847-852','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','17','28','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(455,'Modeling of an Inventory Model with Shortages Exponential Demand Under Capacity Constraint','Inventory may be considered as an accumulation of a product that would be used to satisfy future demands for that product. In this paper an inventory model with two warehouses for deteriorating items with shortages is developed. We took the exponential demand and linear deterioration rate of inventory items in OW and RW. A number of structural property of the inventory system studied analytically.','','-','Virpal Singh, Punam Sharma','119-128','NO','-','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','23','25','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(456,'MHD Oscillatory Flow of a Micropolar Fluid Over a Semi-Infinite Vertical Moving Porous Plate Through a Porous Medium in The Presence of Thermal Radiation','This paper investigates the influence radiation on the problem of the oscillatory two-dimensional laminar flow of a viscous incompressible electrically conducting micropolar fluid past a semi-infinite vertical moving porous plate embedded in a porous medium and subjected to a uniform transverse magnetic field in the presence of thermal radiation effects. The plate moves with constant velocity in the longitudinal direction. The Rosseland approximation is used to describe radiative heat transfer in the limit of optically thick fluids. Numerical results of velocity profiles of micropolar fluids are compared with the corresponding flow problems for a Newtonian fluid. It is observed that, when the radiation parameter increases the velocity and temperature decrease in the boundary layer, whereas when Grashof number increases the velocity increases. The results also show that there exists completely oscillatory behavior in the velocity distribution.','','-','T. Sankar Reddy, P. Roja, N. Bhaskar Reddy','215-230','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(457,'A Study of Vorticity of Unsteady Hydromagnetic Free Convective Flow of Stratified Viscous Fluid Past a Porous Vertical Plate','This paper deals with the study of the vorticity of unsteady hydromagnetic free convection of an incompressible electrically conducting viscous stratified liquid in a porous medium past a vertical plate, the flow is considered under the influence of transversely applied uniform magnetic field. It is assumed that the magnetic Reynolds number is very small so that the induced magnetic field is negligible. The effect of change in Grashoff number , Magnetic parameter (M) and Prandtl number  on the vorticity of the flow has been studied and graphically represented.','','-','Ritu Arora, P.K. Shukla,   Sonal Agarwal','231-234','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(458,'Solution of ReactionDiffusion Equations by using Homotopy Perturbation Method','This work presents a homotopy perturbation method (HPM) to develop solution of the linear and nonlinear reactiondiffusion equations (KolmogorovPetrovslyPiskunov Equations). Reactiondiffusion equations have special importance in engineering and sciences, and constitute a good model for many systems in various fields. One of the newest analytical methods to solve linear and nonlinear equations is the application of homotopy perturbation techniques. The HPM deforms a difficult problem into a simple problem which can be easily solved. The results are compared with Matlab solutions.','','-','Sanjeev Kumar, Ravendra Singh','235-244','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(459,'Heat Transfer Fluid Flow With or Without Porous Medium Under The Influence of Magnetic Field','In the present paper we have investigated Heat transfer fluid flow with or without porous medium under the Influence of Magnetic Field. We have investigated temperature, velocity potential, stream function complex potential, stream line, path lines.','','-','Shammi Agrawal, M.P. Singh','245-252','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(460,'Spatial Stability of Spiral Flows','In this paper, the spatial stability of spiral flows has been discussed. The spectrum of eigen values for   has been obtained. Some necessary conditions of instability and sufficient conditions for stability have been established.  Some results obtained by Kochar (1979) and Awasthi (1998) have been improved.','','-','Ruchi Goel, Hari Kishan, Shweta Chaudhary','253-260','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(461,'Spatial Stability of Stratified Compressible Shear Flows','In this paper, the spatial stability of stratified compressible shear flows has been discussed. An inviscid, stratified compressible fluid flow has been considered confined between two infinite horizontal rigid boundaries situated at  and  .vertical temperature gradient has also been considered. The necessary conditions of instability and sufficient conditions of stability have been obtained for general compressibility as well as weak compressibility. The spectrum of eigen values have been obtained.','','-','Ruchi Goel, Hari Kishan, Neena Gupta','261-268','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(462,'Vorticity Of MHD Visco-Elastic Boundary Layer Flowthrough Porous Medium With Free Convection   Past a Continuous Moving Surface','In the present paper the behavior of free convective boundary layer flow of an electrically conducting visco-elastic, incompressible fluid through porous medium over a continuous moving flat surface in the presence of uniform magnetic field with constant suction has been studied. A uniform magnetic field is assumed to be applied perpendicular to the moving flat surface. The vorticity field is obtained and the effect of Reynolds Number (R), Hartman Number (M), Grashoff Number (G) and permeability parameter (K) on Vorticity field has also been discussed with the help of graph.','','-','Anu Agarwal , M. P. Singh','269-272','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(463,'Boimagnetic fluid flow in a Magnetohydrodynamics Pump','An analytical approach has been carried out of the flow of incompressible Non-Newtonian biomagnetic fluid (blood) in magnetohydrodynamics (MHD) pump. In MHD pump the magnetic field creates dynamic electromotive force (emf) that moves the fluid forward. The purpose of this study is to numerically investigate the flow of blood as a Non-Newtonian fluid in a magnetohydrodynamics (MHD) pump. To solve the non-linear governing momentum and Maxwells equations, a computational fluid dynamics (CFD) finite difference method is utilized. The Variation of velocity with channel radius shows that the velocity is maximum at centre of duct and zero at walls and also the velocity increasing with magnetic field.','','-','Seema Saini, S.K. Shakya, M.P. Singh','273-278','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(464,'A Study of Sectionally Related Dispersion and Chemical Reaction Effects Through a Porous Medium','The present theoretical investigation is aimed at finding the influence of the cross-section on the equivalent dispersion coefficient of a solute in a non-Newtonian medium through a channel containing a porous medium by considering the Power law and Bingham plastic models of the fluids. It has been noted in both the cases, there is a steep rise in equivalent dispersion coefficient with the increase of width of the channel. Further the effect of a porous medium is seen in reduction of equivalent dispersion coefficient all through the region in case of Power law models, while reverse effect is seen in case of Bingham plastic model.','','-','Mukesh Gupta, Parveen','279-286','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(465,'Thermal Instability of A Incompressible Stratified Fluid Layer in Porous Medium in The Presence of Vertical  Magnetic Field','We have examined the stability of incompressible stratified fluid layer, when heated from below in porous medium and also examined this configuration in the presence of the magnetic field and we find a dispersion relation after using the normal mode technique. We found that the principle of exchange of stability (PES) is not valid for this system and for oscillatory modes, the marginal state does not exist and non oscillatory modes are unstable. Further we examined the nature of (dR_0)/(dQ_1 )  and (  dR_0)/(dB_1 )  of stationary convection and finally, We establish the variational  principle of Rayleigh number.','','-','Sapna,  Paramjeet Singh, Arun Kumar Tomer','287-294','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(466,'Stability of Superposed Walters B Visco Elastic Fluids Immersed in Horizontal Magnetic Field','The stability of the interface separating two superposed Walters B visco - elastic fluids immersed in a horizontal magnetic field. Employing the normal mode technique, the linearized perturbation equations have been solved and the dispersion relationhas beenderived. Foe several values of physical parameter involved, the dispersion relation has been solved numerically. It is found that the viscosity and magnetic field have stabilizing influence, while the viscoelastisity has destabilizing influence on the unstable configuration.','','-','Pardeep Singh, Ravi Prakash Mathur','295-302','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(467,'Effects of Thermal Radiation Diffusion on MHD Free Convection Flow past a Vertical Porous Plate','In this paper is to study the effects of thermal radiation diffusion on Magnetohydrodynamics (MHD) free convective heat and mass transfer flow past a vertical porous plate taking Viscous and Darcy resistance terms into account and the constant permeability of the medium numerically. The governing nonlinear partial differential equations are solved by closed analytical method. The results are obtained for velocity, temperature and concentration profiles. The numerical results are presented graphically for different values of the parameters entering into the problem.','','-','Venkata Ramana Reddy.G, Madana Mohana Rao.A, SriHari Babu.V','303-310','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(468,'Flow of a Viscous Incompressible Fluid between Two Parallel Plates','An analysis is presented in the paper for the flow of a viscous incompressible fluid between two parallel plats, one in uniform motion and other at rest with uniform suctions. The Navier Stokes equations with appropriate boundary conditions reduce to  second  and third order non-linear differential equations. An exact solution has been obtained by using perturbation method.','','-','Kapil Dave , Rakesh Dube','311-318','NO','-','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(469,'Two Summation Formulae Involving Contiguous Relation\r\nand Associated to Recurrence Relation','The main object of present paper is to establish two summation formulae of half argument using Contiguous relation[1] and the formula derived from [2].','','-','Salahuddin, Naresh Kumar Dua','43-46','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(470,'Effect of Hall Current on Mhd Visco-Elastic Boundary Layer Flow Through Porous Medium With Free Convection Past A Continuous Moving Surface With Heat Source/Sink   ','In the present paper we study of effect of hall current on free convective\r\nboundary layer flow of an electrically conducting visco-elastic, incompressible\r\nfluid through porous medium over a continuously moving flat surface in the\r\npresence of uniform magnetic field with heat source/sink and constant suction is\r\nstudied. A uniform magnetic field is assumed to be applied perpendicular to the\r\nmoving flat surface. The velocity, temperature and concentration field are\r\nobtained. The effect of various parameters on the velocity, temperature and\r\nconcentration profile as discussed graphically.  ','','Magneto hydrodynamics, visco-elastic, porous media, boundary layer\r\nflow, free convection, heat and mass transfer, heat source.  ',' Vinod Kumar, Rajesh Johri and Rajeev Jha  ','319-330      ','YES','Vinod Paper.pdf','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','16','26','2026-02-17 16:47:49','e',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(471,'Multifrequency Bioelectrical Impedance Analysis (Bia) for Assessing TBW and FFM of Indian Females','Background:  The Bioelectrical Impedance analysis is an easy, applicable method for assessing Total Body water and Fat Free Mass of various groups of people. It has many advantages over other methods and is safe, rapid, portable, easy to perform and require minimum operator training. It has been used extensively for developing specific prediction equation for different ethnicity, age, gender, level of body fatness and physical activity. Regression equations play great role to estimate the body density and fatness specific to the owing to methodological and biological factors. \r\nThe purpose of the study was to investigate the utility of multifrequency BIA for the estimation of TBW and FFM of Indian females at different frequencies. Earlier scientists have measured various parameters of body composition of Indian population using MALTRON-II. However, literature shows that prediction equations have not been developed for Indian females. In the present research paper, an attempt has been made to develop BIA equations using data taken from PhD thesis (1).\r\nData of reference (1) included vital information about body composition of 60 Indian females  such as age, TBW, FFM, height, weight, impedance and phase at 5KHz., 50KHz., 100KHz. and 200 KHz.. This data was then used to calculate the impedance index i.e. ( height2/impedance) at the respective frequencies. This method uses multiple regression analysis to drive prediction equation of Indian females at frequencies of 5KHz.,50KHz.,100KHz.,200KHz., wherein the main aim is to predict one variable which is called dependent variable from 1 or more independent variable also called as predictor variable. Here in this study we used TBW and FFM as dependent variable and Weight of females and Impedance index i.e.(height2/impedance) as independent variable at different frequencies of 5 KHz.,50KHz.,100KHz.,200KHz respectively. Data was fed then into R software, an integrated suite of software facilities used for data manipulation, ca','','-','Ghazala Perveen Khan , Munna khan , Shabana Mehfuz','47-64','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(472,'Locally-Closed Sets and LCR-Continuous Functions','Singal and Singal [5] introduced almost continuous mappings Ganster and Reilly introduced and studied LC-continuous mappings. Our purpose  is to investigate and study another weaker form of continuous functions LCR-continuous functions, which turns out to be another even weaker than the form of almost continuous functions of Signal and Signal.','','-','Vinshu , Bhopal Singh Sharma','65-70','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(473,'Analysis of Management Information System Report\r\nThrough Electronic Equipment','Information is an important resource in the effective management of any organization. Information is any fact or set of facts, which is useful in making a specific decision among alternative courses of action. The information potential of data is enhanced by refinement, which involves selection, processing, sorting, and re-organizing the data into a usable form and transmission to the appropriate end-users.\r\nThe available MIS report is not utilized according to the prescribed roles of employees and senior administrative staff between the organization  and the outside world.\r\nThis might not be unconnected with organization being better funded than the state organization. MIS functions must stay close to the pulse of the business so that their key issues, problems and opportunities are deeply understood.','','-','Nirmal Sharma','71-76','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(474,'Impact of ICT on Society','Globalization has been one of the most frequently used expressions in socio-economic and political discourse over the last two decades. The rapid development of information and communication technology (ICT) has transformed the entire society. ICT has brought considerable changes in the attitudes and institutions in Indian sphere. Present paper deals with how ICT has brought some desirable or undesirable changes in attitudes as well as caste, marriage and family institutions in India','','-','Geetali Padiyar, Manikant Shah','280-284','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','21','27','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(475,'CARVAKA-THE ANCIENT INDIAN REBELL NATURALISTIC PHILOSOPHY','This revolutionary philosophy of the Carvakas put an end to the age of the Vedas and the Upanishads. It weakened the hold of the Brahmans on the mind of India, and left in Hindu society a vacuum which almost compelled the growth of a new religion. But the materialists had done their work so thoroughly that both of the new religions which arose to replace the old Vedic faith were, anomalous though it may sound atheistic religions, devotions without a god. Both belonged to the Nastika or Nihilistic movement; and both were originated not by the Brahman priests but by members of the Kshatriyas warrior caste in a reaction against sacerdotal ceremonialism and theology. With the coming of Jainism and Buddhism a new epoch began in the history of India.','','-','Saroj Agarwal,Abhinav Goel, V.K. Maheshwari','285-292','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','21','27','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(476,'ROLE PLAYING An Interactive teaching strategy','Role playing is one of the most mis-used and under-used techniques available to the child and youth care worker. This is because it is also one of the least understood of techniques. While we have all seen it, and even experienced it, in our training, we have seldom had the opportunity to really dissect it: to tear it apart and analyze it so that we come to know its value, power and usefulness. As a result we end up using role play when were stuck, bored or desperate rather than using it because it is appropriate for this client, in this state, at this time. It is an essentiality to understand some of the \"how,\" \"why,\" and \"when\" of role play in a manner that is simple and clear.','','-','Pallavi Singh,Abhinav Goel, V.K. Maheshwari','293-309','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','21','27','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(477,'A Study of The Functioning of Teacher Centers in Aligarh District','Capacity building of teacher becomes imperative to keep them abreast of the newer developments that take place in the fields of education. There would enable them to improve the quality of classroom delivery. The centers (of the state of Uttar Pradesh) serve as centers for professional development of teachers. This study conducted to find out the facilities and functioning of teacher centers reveals that the centers need to be equipped professionally.','','-','Suraksha Bansal, Avdesh Pratap Singh','310-314','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','21','27','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(478,'Perishable Model with Inflation Induced Demand under Progressive Credit Period','The effect of deterioration of physical goods can not be disregarded in many inventory systems. Deterioration is defined as decay, damage or spoilage. Food items, photographic films, drugs, chemicals, electronic components and radioactive substances are some examples of items in which sufficient deterioration may occur during the normal storage period of the units and consequently this loss must be taken into account while analyzing the inventory system.','','-','Ajay Kumar Saini,A. P. Singh, S. R. Singh','1-12','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','30','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(479,'Relation between Emotional Intelligence, Self-Concept and Personality of Propective Secondary School Teachers','This study aimed at studying the relationship between emotional intelligence, self-concept and personality of prospective secondary school teachers by using emotional intelligence scale, self-concept and personality questionnaire from 312 prospective teachers of two government and two private colleges of Punjab and Chandigarh, which were e