 paper begins by linking the growth of English to the growth and widespread availability of technology. It briefly examines the ways in which computers have historically contributed to ELT with both pedagogical applications and understanding the nature of the language. The paper presents different programs like, Corpora, Speech Synthesis, Speech Recognition, Artificial Intelligence and Parsing that have been helping the learners. The paper also reviews the ways in which the Computer Aided Language Learning (CALL) has/had been impacting the language teaching. The paper also examines the impacts of Web and Internet on learners and teachers. At the end, the paper considers the implications for language teaching pedagogy and argues for a shift away from traditional notions of curriculum and syllabus. The paper also reviews the impacts of technology on teachers and how they should cope with the changing environment by blending the technology in their teaching.','','-','Manoj Kumar Garg','95-100','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Allied Sciences','27','34','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',7,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(483,'A Comparative Study of Teaching Competancy of B.T.C. and Special B.T.C. Primary Teachers','Teachers acquire commitment, dedication, love and other essential competency, and if they are enabled and empowered to perform multiple tasks in the classroom, school as well as in the community is a genuinely professional manner, then a chain reaction can begin starting with a sound teacher in students in cognitive, affective and psychomotor area of development. Keeping in view the importance of the teacher in the system of Education on idea came into the mind of the investigator that she shoved study the teaching competency, attitude of B.T.C. & Special B.T.C. Primary teacher.','','-','Rekha Sharma and Dal Chand','101-106','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Allied Sciences','27','34','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',7,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(484,'E- Learning in higher Education: Need & Importance','The education is one of the most important inputs that influence the all round development of any nations economic, physical, social, cultural, ethical and spiritual. The new technology if exploited and implemented effectively can bring a sea change in teaching learning process. E-learning is capable to transform the boring classes to the interesting. With the use of communication and technology the classes can become more interesting. 	E-learning has the potential to motivate, develop confidence and self-esteem, overcome many barriers that learners encounter, widen access and improve the learning experience.','','-','Shiv Kumar Bhardwaj, Narendra Singh and Hari Shankar Singh Kharayat','107-112','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Allied Sciences','27','34','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',7,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(485,'A study of relationship of adjustment level and value pattern of Higher       Secondary students in District Muzaffarnagar Uttar Pradesh.','The formal channel of making students capable of meeting out the challenges is the educational institutions. The educational institutions control and direct the society in a desirable direction. If we imagine a society without an educational institution, it looks like a chaos and undisciplined. Schools are the best source of socialization and acculturation to cater to the intellectual, social, moral and professional needs. In the present scenario the researchers felt that it is the time of conflict between mind and heart, under such cut throat competitive age values of a person are being affected by other traits of personality also, so it is justified to study relation of value pattern with adjustment of high secondary students. A survey type research method was applied and adequate sample of 400 higher secondary students was selected through stratified random sampling techinique.The main conclusions of the present study, obtained after testing the research hypothesis is that there is no significant relationship between Adjustment and Value pattern of Higher Secondary students.','','-','Sangeeta Srivastava  and Meenu Choudhary','113-120','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Allied Sciences','27','34','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',7,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(486,'Affective Dimension of Learning Styles of Prospective Secondary Teachers: A Study of Main and Interaction Effects of Teaching Aptitude and Self-Esteem','ABSTRACT\r\n	The present study was carried out to ascertain the impact of academic achievement, locus of control and self-esteem on study approaches of distance learners with the help of three tools: (1) The Approaches to studying Questionnaire (by John, T. E. Richardson), (ii) Self - Esteem Inventory (by M. Rosenberg), and (iii) Rotters Internal - External Locus of Control Scale. The sample consisted of 424 M.Ed. Students of second semester enrolled with ICDEOL, H. P. University, Shimla, which was drawn by random cluster method.\r\n	The analysis of the data revealed that academic achievement and locus of control had significant impact on surface approach to studying while self-esteem influenced significantly both the approaches of distance learners -- i.e. deep approach and surface approach.  \r\nI','','-','Surender Sharma  &  Surender Thakur','121-126','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Allied Sciences','27','34','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',7,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(487,'Value and Present Senario','-','','-','Amzad Hussain Mazumder','127-130','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Allied Sciences','27','34','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',7,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(488,'Development of Reading Habits: an Action Research','-','','-','Geeta Rai','131-136','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Allied Sciences','