L HUMANITARIAN LAW','This paper is based on contemporary humanitarian issues cropping up due to certain types of armed conflicts in India such as those of Naxilism in Andhra Pradesh and that of militancy in state of Jammu and Kashmir. These conflicts have great detrimental effect on large cross sections of the people directly or indirectly.  The purpose of this paper is to synthesize existing legal tools which are coherent and consistent with Constitution of India so that law enforcement will take recourse to certain humane principles while dealing with situations of law and order problem at higher extent.','','-','Mohd. Yousuf  Bhat','1-12','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','36','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(498,'Georgian Poetry','The poetry of the 20th century was characterized by traditional as well as experimental poetry. Traditional poetry roughly includes the Edwardian, Georgian, War poetry and so on. It was based on pastoral or homespun themes and followed a combined trend of the romantics and neo-classicists. Experimental poetry includes Imagist poetry; Neo-Metaphysical Poetry, Surrealist Movement and Neo-Romanticism.','','-','S. K. Singh','13-16','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','36','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(499,'Feminism in Alice Walkers Theoretical Writing','Alice Malsenior Walker is born on February 9, 1944 as the eighth child of Willie Lee Walker and Minnie Tallulah Grant Walker. Growing up in a sharecropper family in Eatonton, Georgia, Walker experiences first-hand the southern atmosphere in which the black vernacular [is] prominent and the stamp of slavery and oppression [are] still present1 and which will shape many of her future works. This paper focuses on one such group: black women. Being doubly marginalized (Ward & Herndl, 1997: 741) as both black and female, these women not only question mainstream society, but the challenges to this society by other minority groups (the Afro-Americans on the one hand, the feminists on the other) as well. Without trying to offer an exhaustive overview of the ways in which they have done (and still do) so, this paper will focus on one of the best-known approaches to the issue, Alice Walkers Womanism.In this paper  Walkers own definition of the concept Womanism will be analyzed in detail.','','-','Sonal Singh','17-20','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','36','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(500,'NEED FOR GUIDANCE PROGRAMME AND GUIDANCE PERSSONEL','Some hold the view that guidance is not possible without professional  training .One cant deny  the need for professional service to help the child to solve some of their more intricate personal- social problems peculiar to the child. However one can visualize the role of guidance oriented teachers can play in furthering growth and development of children in areas such as academic, vocational maturity, personal and social development of the student.','','-','Kirtima Upadhyay & M.S.Gusain','21-24','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','36','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(501,'Poverty and approval motive: A psychological study','The present study focuses at the understanding of approval motive with the special reference of poverty level and age groups.\r\n	The study was planned as following the poverty level 2 (W.S. vs. S.S.) x age groups (youth vs. adult) factorial design and approval motive was tested. In each treatment condition 20 Ss were placed. The poverty seals (P.S.) was developed by Sharma Krishna & Tiwari P.S.N. (2008). This is the reliable and valid measure of poverty. The approval motive scale was developed by N.K.M. Tripathi (1978). The obtained results clearly display the differential influence of W.S vs. S.S., youth vs. adult on approval motive.','','-','\"\"Krishna Sharma  ;\r\nP.S.N. Tiwari\"','25-30','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','36','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(502,'A STUDY OF THE FUNCTIONING OF TEACHER CENTERS IN ALIGARH DISTRICT','Capacity building of teacher becomes imperative to keep them abreast of the newer developments that take place in the fields of education. The is would enable them to improve the quality of classroom delivery. The centres(of the state of Uttar Pradesh) serves as centres for professional development of teachers. This study conducted to find out the facilities and functioning of teacher centres reveals that the centres need to be equipped professionally.','','-','\"\"Suraksha Bansal ;\r\nAvdesh Pratap Singh\"','31-34','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','36','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(503,'Philosophy of Swami RamTirth The Practical Vedanta','Swami RamTirth (1873-1906) a great intellectual , scientist and mathematician and possessing the true knowledge in spirituality ,was brimming with intense desire for renunciation from his early life,all the time he taught at the forman Christian college ,Lahore as a professor of Mathematics.Purity of life ,purity of action ,purity of thought ,purity of mutual behavior and attitude ,purity of dealing .whatever in short , one does must be in a spirit of purity and then alone the result will be pure and happy. This is what the Vedanta teaches.','','-','Prashant Bhatt','35-38','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','36','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(504,'ECONOMICS OF PRODUCTION SYSTEM OF PIGEONPEA','Pigeonpea on account of their vital role in nutritional security and soil ameliorative properties have been an integral part of sustainable agriculture since ages. However the production of pigeonpea  in Uttarakhand has drastically came down in the period, 1990-91 to 2007-08.  The pigeonpea data of Government of Uttarakhand, directorate of Agriculture, 2008, shows that the pigeonpea area almost static, its area increase only 24 ha during the period 1990-91 to 2006-08.  The Production has declined up to 280 metric tonnes. The productivity has declined   -1.66 qt/ha. Most of the farmers are economically inefficient in producing pulses in the region. The reasons for declining the pigeonpea production were farmers to limit the adoption of modern package of practices for its cultivation. The researcher has made an effort to find out the out the economics and benefit of pigeonpea in the state of Uttarakhand. The sample farmers reported at large that the rotation of pigeon pea reduces the use of chemical fertilizers and also enhances the output of wheat significantly. \r\nThe entire Assn Valley which is the part of Doon valley of Uttarakhand was selected for the study. The sample was randomly taken of 275 cultivars producing or not producing pulses. Participatory Rural Appraisal (PRA) approach was chosen as research method and was completed by household interviews based on a semi-structured questionnaire. The study is conducted with the help of unstructured qualitative questionnaire and followed by a structured questionnaire. The adoption of various technologies will certainly enhance the socio economic life of farmers of Uttarakhand.','','-','\"\"Sunit Kumar,  ;\r\n V.A. Bourai, 	;\r\nSujata Slathia\"','39-46','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','36','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(505,'vk/kqfud Hkkjr esa kSf{kd iqu:RFkku ds egku iSxEcj johUnz ukFk VSxksj dk fpUru','johUnz ukFk VSxksj cgqeq[kh izfrHkk ds /kuh O;fDrRo okys O;fDr FksA mUgkasus vius ys[kksa] 