ed that the burst were produced by electron beam accelerated in blast wave shocks and injected along open magnetic field lines (Gopalswamy et al., 2005).','','-','Joginder Sharma, Anshu Gupta, Nishant Mittal , Udit Narain','149-158','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','30','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(539,'Dominant Aspergillus spp. in Aeromycoflora','Fungi play a significant role in our daily life. They are our greatest friends as well as foes. They are present all the time in air that we breathe. The members of Aspergillaceae are commonly known as blue-green or black mould. Aspergillus causes Aspergillosis in animals and human beings. It is responsible for spoilage of food stuffs, paper documents, leather articles textile etc. and produce aflatoxin. The common aeromycoflora spp. of Aspergillus is A. niger, A. fumigatus, A. flavus, A. candidus etc. \r\nThe incidence of fungi is widely variable depending on season, temperature, relative humidity, time of the day, presence of human activity and artificial climate control. \r\nThe control measures of airborne spores depend on the mechanisms of dispersal, deposition of spores and the application of suitable plant protection measures. Among them, the most frequently used are fungicides.','','-','P. Sharma, S. Saxena, S. Guleri','159-165','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','30','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(540,'Bayes Estimator of a generalized gamma type model /Reliability and Hazard function','Bayes estimator of a generalized gamma type model are obtained for various priors. Here the proposed prior, Bayes estimator of ? for given p and k=1 coincides with MLE of ? if c=2, whereas Bayes estimator of hazard rate function of ? given p and k coincides with its MLE. Bayes estimators of reliability and hazard rate function have also been obtained','','-','D. K. Pandey , Anusheel Mishra','165-174','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(541,'An inventory model with time value of money for decaying items with trade credits','In the present paper an inventory model under permissible delay in payments for deteriorating items with time value of money has been developed. Permissible delay in payments is provided to the customers to attract them and boost up the demand. Shortages are not permitted in this study. The associated cost minimization is illustrated by numerical example and also carried out by using MATHEMATICA  5.2 for the feasibility and applicability of the models.','','-','S K Shon,  Anubha Goyal','175-184','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(542,'Thermodynamic and Biological Studies of Some Bivalent Metal Complexes with 2  Hydroxy  4  Methoxy Butyrophenone Oxime (HMBOX)','The 2  hydroxy  4 - methoxy butyrophenone oxime (HMBOX) behaved as monoprotic acid and proton was replaced by the metal ion during complex formation and two type of complexes viz 1:1 and 1:2 in the system. The stability constant of HMBOX with bivalent metal ion was calculated. The order of stability constant was in the order Cu(II)>Ni(II)>Mn(II) which is in the agreement with the Irving Williams order. The values of change in free energy (?G), enthalpy (?H) and entropy (?S) for ligand were calculated at different temperature.\r\nThe effect of ionic strength and temperature on stability constant was also studied. \r\nThe antifungal activity and antibacterial activity of different concentration of test compounds were measured by determining the growth of test fungi by dry weight increase method and by agar diffusion method against Alternaria alternate and E.coli. The order of antimicrobial effect was observed are as follows Cu(II)>Ni(II)>Mn(II).','','-','Subhash Chand, F.Rehman,  Hina Rahat','185-190','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(543,'Synthesis, Characterization and Analytical Application of Antimony(III) Tungstosilicate an Inorganic Ion Exchanger','In the present work , the ion exchange capacity is found to be more than the reported ion exchanger based on antimony(iii) . Antimony(iii) tungstosilicate synthesized under varying ratios of 0.1 M antimony tri chloride , 0.05 M sodium tungstate and 0.05 M sodium meta silicate solutions . The synthesized exchanger shows ion exchange capacity 0.76 meq/g. for Na+ ions . The exchanger is also characterized on the basis of TGA , XRD and IR . The chemical stability of the material is determined in acids and basis solutions of different concentration. The thermal stability of the exchanger is also determined at different temperatures. Distribution studies exhibit maximum Kd value for Ni++ and minimum for Pb++. Important binary separation were carried out. The separation performed on the ion exchanger column is very important for the environmentalists, since the mixture analysed are Ni-Zn, Ni-Pb, Pb-Zn and Pb-Mg.','','-','Subhash Chand , Seema, Vijayata and Rekha Rani','191-198','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(544,'Synthesis, Spectral and Electrochemical Studies on Manganese (Ii) Complexes with a Multidentate Ligand Carrying Pentadent Benzamidazole Group','Manganese(II) complexes with formula [Mn(BMBES)X2] have been synthesized and characterized utilizing a multidentate ligand. 1,5-bis(4-methyl,benzimidazol-2-yl)-3-thiapentane (BMBES) with anionic ligand like Cl?, NCS?, HCOO?. The EPR spectroscopy shows a strong single centered at   for Mn(II) complexes prove that non-cubic crystalline electric field are weak. Zero field splitting parameter   has also been calculated.','','-','Meghraj Singh','199-210','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(545,'Theoretical Analysis of Thermal instability of Viscoelastic Fluids in porous medium','In this study the motion of Viscoelastic fluid has been analyzed analytically by using linear stability theory. The Darcys of is used to explain the fluid motion and the motion of the fluid is taken without applied magnetic field. The linear and non linear stability analyses of initially quiescent, horizontal porous layer which are saturated with Viscoelastic fluids are conducted. The effect of relaxation parameter on the variation of Rayleigh Darcy number is also investigated','','-','Seema Saini, S.K.Shakya, M.P.Singh','211-220','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(546,'Service Quality Perceptions: A Case Study of Banking Services','In the past, banking was concerned only with borrowing and lending activities. But at present, banking is catering to the entire requirement of individual customers and is emerging as a potential sector for the consistent growth of business. Customers retention is one of the top priority of the banks. Many customers are not wanting but are expecting better services. Customers have started demanding variety in banking services and their preference for delivery channels are changing. It is true that technology has provided a unique competitive advantage to some banks in India, as these banks have taken a lead in the use of technology for introducing special products and services viz. Cash management, credit cards, ATMs, Electronic Fund Transfer(EFT), Real Time Gross Settlement(RTGS), debit cards etc. But as far as this study is concerned it is more focused on the services in the bank premises. When banks are providing so many and adopting new techniques to satisfy their customers, they should also try to find out whether the customers are really satisfied with their customers, they should also try to find out whether the customers are really satisfied with their services or not. Issues such as offering a proper reception at the counter, consideration for their time, updating of their passbooks, speedy collection of their cheques and drafts are considered to be of the prime importance to the most of the customers. Realizing this, the present study has undertaken to assess the quality of services being rendered to the customers by public and private sector banks. The main aim of this research paper is to assess and re-assess how customers perceive banking services, what are the emerging customers expectations and to study customers satisfaction level with banking services provided by the public and private sector banks.','','-','Somprabh Dubey','221-236','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(547,'Development of A Deterministic Inventory Model for Deteriorating Items Taking Account of Price Dependent Demand and Time Value of Money','In this paper, we use two parameter weibull distribution to represent the time of deteriorating item where demand is price dependent and shortage is allowed. The time value of money is considered for a finite planning horizon. Optimal production and pricing policies are derived. So that the total present worth net profit is maximized.','','-','Anjali, Ramesh Chand and Arun Kumar Tomer','237-250','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(548,'Reliability Analysis of n-policy, K-out-of-n: g Machining System with Warm and Cold Spares','The present investigation deals with a Markov model for analyzing the reliability of N- policy, K- out of  N: G Machining system with warm and cold spares, which are provided to replace the failed machines. The machines are assumed to fail in M-modes. We have considered two cases for reliability analysis, with repair and without repair. An inverse Laplace transform is used to solve the simultaneous differential equations for nonrepairable case. A generalized analytic function for system reliability is obtained. We have used Runge- Kutta Method to analyze the reliability of repairable system. Mean time to failure and mean time between failure are also derived. The approach and solutions are very helpful to system engineer and reliability analysts.','','-','Rekha Rani','251-260','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(549,'A Meir-Keeler Type Fixed Point Theorems in Fuzzy Metric Space','The aim of the present paper is to obtain a common fixed point theorem using a new type of contractive condition which is independent of the known contractive notions. In the following pages we prove a common fixed point theorem using an (?,?) contractive condition, without either imposing any additional condition on  ?  or assuming a ? - contractive condition together with. Instead of  a   ? - contractive condition we assume the Lipschitz type analogue of a plane contractive condition which is independent of the ? -contractive condition. Our theorem improves and generalizes a number of Meir-Keeler type theorems including the results of Pant [ 17 , ( Theorem 1 ) ], Pant and Pant and Pant etal','','-','Sanjay Padaliya,  Achin Jain, Anand Chauhan','261-268','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(550,'orZeku o izkphu Hkkjrh; f\'k{k.k&O;oLFkk ds mn~ns\';ksa dk rqyukRed v/;;u','fk{kk fdlh Hkh lekt dk niZ.k gksrk gSA izR;sd jk\"V  dh mUufr mldh fk{kk O;oLFkk ij fuHkZj jgrh gSA ftl jk\"V e