upply Chain Inventory Model for Decaying Items with Selling Price Dependent Demand Rate','The goal of this paper is to develop a two warehouse Supply chain inventory model with partially backordered shortages, in which units are, deteriorate with constant rates in both the warehouses and the demand rate is taken as selling price dependent. The supplier experiences the problem of lead time at his end. The lead time of the supplier was a probability density function of his managing cost. The more the supplier was ready to spend as managing expenses, smaller will be the lead time and vice versa. Numerical examples are presented to demonstrate the developed model and the solution procedure','','-','R K Pandey, Sachin Gupta','291-300','NO','-','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','31','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(553,'Some Results on Self Complementary Chordal Graphs','A graph G is self-complementary (sc) if it is isomorphic to its complement. G is perfect if for all induced subgraphs H of G, the chromatic number of H is equal to the number of vertices in the largest clique in H. A sc graph which is also perfect is known as a sc perfect graph. The class of sc chordal graphs is a subclass of sc perfect graphs. In this paper we study a sc chordal graph and obtain various results. We also show that a sc chordal graph with n = 4k or 4k + 1 vertices and star cp ?* is comparability if and only if its bipartite transformation has no induced subgraphs isomorphic to C6 or P7.','','-','S.A.K.Kirmani, Merajuddin, Madhukar Sharma, Parvez Ali','77-86','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(554,'Automatic  Meter  Reading  In  WSN  Using 2.4ghz\r\nTranceiver With  Matlab  Data Logger','This paper proposes a new network communication system for energy meter reading by integrating communication technology and software system along with the existing meters. A wireless or wired communication system will be integrated with electronic energy meter to have remote access over the usage of electricity. Even though they are two different modules, energy meter deliver the reading details as on when it demands by the communication system. The communication system is further connected with electricity regional/sub-regional office, which will rather act as a base station. Instead of creating a separate communication system and backbone, any of the secure existing communication service infrastructures may also be utilized to avoid any initial investments. The communication channel is identified by the consumer\'s number and it is secured by any cryptographic standards. Base office can verify the energy meters performance by checking the day to day consumption of energy. This will also help to avoid any tampering or break down of energy meter.This system applies ZigBee communication protocol and uses the IC-CC2500, 2.4GHz(ISM) as RF Transceiver. It has the characteristics of low power consumption, low cost, flexible structure and accurate measurement, and it can achieve the long-distance Energy meter monitoring of the bus bar junction in real time. The wireless Energy meter sensor node senses and transmits the variations in the local Energy meter to the central computing unit placed within the range. The central computing unit receives the data and displays the data continuously on MATLAB data logger on PC through USB to serial cable.','','-','Sanjay Singh, Rajesh Singh and Vivek Kaundal','87-94','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(555,'A Fuzzy Adaptive Resonance Theory Based Classification\r\nof Diabetes Disease Diagnosis','Artificial Neural Networks is widely used to solve many healthcare problems. A patient is treated number of times on the basis of various metrics and symptoms. Diabetes is a disease where the bodys cells cannot use glucose properly for lack of or resistance to the hormone insulin, produced by the pancreas. The most common implementation of a neural network  come across is the one where each neuron is modeled as an object and the neural network stores all these objects. Particularly in case of  Artificial neural network a accurate dataset is required for an accurate classification. In this paper the classification accuracy is improved.  Symptoms are taken as inputs and targets are identfication of patient which is devided into two classes infected and non-infected. The targets for the neural network will be identified  with 1\'s as infected and will be identified with 0\'s as non-infected. In this study, to diagnosed disease the data is obtained from UCI Machine Learning Repository and the results are obtained  using Fuzzy ART neural networks. The experimental results achieves classification accuracy of 98%.','','-','Divakar Singh , V.K.Katiyar','95-102','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(556,'A Vacation Model For Threshold Policy Of Machine Repair\r\nProblem With Setup&Degraded Failure','This investigation deals with the study of Optimal threshold policy for machine repair problem with R heterogeneous removable repairmen. The first repairman turns on for repair only when K1 failed units are accumulated and starts repair after a setup time, which is assumed to be exponentially distributed. The first repairman leaves for vacation, as soon as system becomes empty, and returns only when the number of failed units reaches a thresholds value. The ith repairman (i = 1, 2, .. R) turns on when there are Ki failed units in the system, and leaves for vacations if the number of failed units drops below Ki. The life time and repair time of failed units are assumed to be exponentially distributed. To obtain steady state queue-size distribution, recursive technique is used. Various performance measures are established using steady-state probabilities. A cost function is also deduced.','','-','Rekha Rani','103-112','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(557,'Damped Vibrations of Exponentially Non-Homogeneous Isotropic\r\nElastic Rectangular Plates of Parabolically Varying Thickness\r\nResting On Elastic Foundation','In this paper, the damped vibrations of an isotropic exponentially non-homogeneous rectangular plate of finite length and breadth with parabolically variable thickness resting on elastic foundation have been studied. Here thickness of the plate varies parabolically in one direction (along x-axis). The two edges parallel to the x-axis (y=0, y=b) are considered to be simply supported. Different sets of boundary conditions have been applied at the other two edges. In this paper generalized eigenvalue problem is obtained by method of series solution. The values of frequency parameter and the corresponding mode of vibration, for specific values of various parameters are obtained.','','-','Manu Gupta, Ajendra Kumar , Babita Rani','113-122','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(558,'Weighted Goal Programming Model Formulation and \r\nCalculation of Diet Planning','In this paper, we present a goal programming model through an example. The formulation and solution procedure is applied through a weighted goal programming approach. The use of this approach is to select diets to meet specific nutritional requirements frequently resulting in an over-supply of certain nutrients. The weighted goal programming is presented as a method of achieving nutritional balance in selected diets. This approach is followed by a report of an application to the selection of food raw materials to satisfy the daily nutritional requirements.','','-','A.K.Bhargava, Divya Bansal, A.B.Chandramouli, Arun Kumar','123-132','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(559,'Periodic Orbits of Collision in the Plane Circular \r\nProblem of Four Bodies with Dissipation','We perform an analysis of the dynamics of circular restricted four body problem under the effect of different kinds of dissipation (linear drag, stokes drag and Poynting-Robertson effect). The effect of dissipation is often to decrease the semi-major axis as a consequence the infinitesimal body collides with one of the primaries. In general it is quite difficult to find non-collision orbits using random initial conditions. Thus investigation provides information on the different regions, showing both collision and non-collision orbits. Moreover we have found the periodic orbits and also periodic orbits of collision for the case of linear drag, stokes drag and Pointing-Robertson effect. According to the periodic orbits, we have observed that as we increase the effect of dissipation, the shape of the periodic orbits shrink.','','-','Abdullah','133-142','NO','-','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','29','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(560,'Inventory Model of Deteriorating Products Under\r\nSuppliers Partial Trade Credit Policy','In this paper, the retailers inventory policy of deteriorating products has been discussed under the suppliers trade credit policy. The demand rate has been considered as linear function of time and the deterioration rate has been taken constant. It is assumed that the supplier offers a partial trade credit. Different cases have been discussed depending upon the partial trade 