as of Eighth Grader Studying in Open School and Public School of Meerut City in U.P.','This research gives an idea that which is the effective teaching place or where the students can become more self confident and courageous in open school or in public school. From these two places which one is the better pace for a student to take education? Where the children are given more stress in a public school or in an open school. Studying the above data one can well understand about the teaching technique to be applied from the open school students so they can also get an opportunity to make their future well by taking good academic knowledge','','-','Ritu Bharadwaj and Boski Kumar','27-32','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','26','32','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(566,'Vivekananda- Method or Procedure of teaching','Knowledge is inherent in every mans soul. What we mean when we say that a man knows is only what he discovers by taking the cover off his own soul. Consequently, he draws our attention to the fact that the task of the teacher is only to help the child to manifest its knowledge by removing the obstacles in its way.','','-','Pallavi Singh and V.K. Maheshwari','33-40','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','26','32','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(567,'Success Factors for Developing a Software Project','A large software project may involve hundreds of peoples and span many years. A project of this dimension can easily turn into chaos if proper management controls are not imposed. The goal of any software development project is to produce a product that is delivered on time, within the allocated budget, and with the capabilities expected by the customer and unfortunately, this goal is rarely achieved. In this paper we provide an introduction to four project success factors, a properly managed project, a competent project manager, a proper testing process and a mature software engineering environment','','-','Bindu Sharma','41-48','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','26','32','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(568,'Teaching Psychological Type','Psychological type is a way of understanding ourselves and each other.  It describes four dichotomies, each of which has two opposite preference poles. The four dichotomies encompass opposite ways of (1) using energy, (2) gathering information, (3) coming to conclusions, and relating to the outside world. In the type approach to personality, we each experience one pole of each dichotomy as more comfortable and natural than its opposite, and therefore tend to use it more and enjoy its use. It is the interplay of our four preferred poles that makes up our individual, distinctive personalities.','','-','Rakhi Maheshwari','49-54','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','26','32','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(569,'Tk;kadj izlkn d`r dkek;uh esa lkoZHkkSehdj.k dh ladYiuk ','lkoZHkkSehdj.k dk kkfCnd vFkZ gS foo ls lEcfU/kr djukA tks fopkj&fl)kUr] dk;Z&O;ogkj ,oa vuqlU/kku vkfn O;fDr] lekt] tkfr vFkok nsk&foks\"k dh ladqfpr lhek rd fleVs gq, gSa] mUgSa foo&Ik;ZUr O;kIr dj nsuk gh lkoZHkkSehdj.k gSA vk/kqfud lUnHkksZa esa ;g fodflr fgUnh lkfgR; ds Nk;kokn dky ds vU;re~ egkdkO; ^dkek;uh* esa ekuo l`f\"V dh vkfn ekrk J)k ds g`n; dh og vej okRlY;lq/kkj l/kkj gS] tks Lusg lfyy ds vHkko esa la=kl&rki ls >qylrs gq, ekuo dks izk.k&iYyo dks lgt khryrk iznku djrh gS] euq\";rk ds eaxy iFk dks vo:) djus okyh ccZj Ikkqrk dh dVhyh >kfM+;ksa dk lewy mUewyu djrh gS vkSj {kqnz ladh.kZrk ds kq\"d fldrkd.kksa dks fojkV lkxj dk foLrkj iznku djrh gSA bl dkO; xzUFk esa egkdfo izlkn us ekuork dks fotf;uh cukus okys mu lr~ fl)kUrksa ,oa drZO;kpkj.kksa dks vuqHkwfr dk fo\"k; cukdj lekfgr dj 