al growth (Peter Salovey and John Mayer). This Paper throws light on how Emotional Intelligence can be a gateway to effective Teacher Education..','','-','Aditi Jain','79-86','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','26','32','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(572,'ICT in Teaching-Learning Process','During the past few decades or so, various changes have been taken place in the sphere of learning.  Adoption of hardware in like Radio, T.V., Computers, Multimedia systems, fax etc. has made educationists more enthusiastic to maximally utilize the technologies.  Objective has been to find ways and means to press into the learning minds as much information as possibly by creating information highways. 21st century is the age of Information and Communication Technology (ICT) All over the world, there is a trend to use ICT in the teaching-learning process.  There is rapid shift of educational technologies to shape the structure of system of education across the globe. ICT is an important instrument to make teaching effective and learning permanent.  It is essential for the teacher to determine the best use of ICT in the context of culture, need and economic-social conditions. The emergence of the knowledge-based society is changing the global status of education.  It is high time to develop a new knowledge based global society.','','-','Ruchi Sharma','87-92','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','26','32','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(573,'Ukofu;qDr fk{kdksa dh izfk{k.k izkFkfedrk,W','vktdy gekjs lkekftd ifjosk ij oSohdj.k] mnkjhdj.k vkSj futhdj dk izHkko Li\"V :Ik ls fn[kkbZ ns jgk gSa fk{kk dk {ks= Hkh blls vNwr ugh gS Hkkjrh; izkS|ksfxdh laLFkku dh rwrh iwjs lalkj es cksyrh gS vS fofHkUu fonskh foofo|ky; gekjs nsk es viuh \'kk[kk [kksyus dks rS;kj ftlls Hkkjrh; Nk=kas dks fonskh f\'k{kk izkIr dk volj izkIr gksx