-10','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','45','2013-07-23 17:36:30','h',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(785,'Awareness of Environmental Education amongst Secondary School Students: The Indian Scenario','Environmental Education will make us aware about the environmental problems that are looming over our heads and will equip us with knowledge to overcome these problems. Children, who are the future of tomorrow, have a critical role to play in making this world a better place to live in. the problems of environment also arise from everyday actions of all human beings so it is an urgent requirement to create awareness for environment protection among the people at various levels. They can act only if they understand why environmental problems arise and how they should be tackled. In this paper we have attempted to look at the influence, the environment play in our life and its awareness amongst a sample of 121 (56 Male & 65 Female) secondary schools students. The Results revealed that the male secondary students had significantly higher level of awareness towards environmental education as compared to their female counterparts.','','-','Shivani Yadav, Savita Sharma','11-16','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','45','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(786,'Environmental Awareness among Secondary School Students as Function of Type of School and Gender','The study was conducted with an aim to see the effect of type of school and gender on environmental awareness of secondary school students. The hypotheses were (i) Type of school is not a significant factor in determining the environmental awareness of the students at secondary level and (ii) Gender is not a significant factor in determining the environmental awareness of the secondary school students. In order to test the hypotheses Environmental Awareness Ability Measure (EAAM) developed by Dr. Jha was administered on 200 Secondary School Students of Haldwani (Nainital). Results show that both type of school and gender are significant factors in the determination of environmental awareness of secondary school students and the students of CBSE affiliated schools and especially girls are keener towards environmental awareness.','','-','Apara Goyal, Amit Shukla','17-22','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','45','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(787,'ekuo \'kjhj ij ;ksx dk izHkko','euq\"; ds thou dk y{; vkRelk{kkRdkj djkuk gSA ;ksx vkRelk{kkRdkj djkrk gSA ;ksxh lalkj dh {k.keaxqjrk dks le>rk gqvk lalkj ds deksZ dks c[kwch fuHkkrk gqvk Hkh Hkhrj ls fyIr ugha gksrkA ;ksx ls \'kfDr] Kku ls eqfDr] izse ls HkfDr o lsok ls eqfDr feyrh gSA vkjksX;] fuHkZ;rk] lq[k] \'kkfUr] lqj{kk] lfg\".kqrk] izse] d:.k] /kS;Z] foosd] vkst] rst] e`R;qta; ;ksx ds gh ifj.kke gSA ;ksx oSKkfud Hkh gS o izkekf.kd HkhA ;ksx ru o vkRek dh \'kqf) ek= dk fufeRr ugha oju~ ekuoh; vkSj bZ\'ojh; laca/kksa dks iz\'kLr djus dk ekxZ gSA','','NA','vo/ks\'k \'kekZ, lksgu jkt rkrsM','23-26','NO','-','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','45','2013-07-23 17:36:30','h',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(788,'/;ku LoLFk lQy thou dh izf;k','vgadkj] vfHkeku] fpM+fpM+kiu] ftn~nh jktfld Hkko] fEkF;kpkj ;s lc /;ku dh ck/kk,W gSA ;s eu esa lw{e :Ik ls fNih jgrh gSA ftl izdkj yEcs le; rd cUn dejs dh lQkbZ djus ij /kwy ij mBrh gSa] mlh izdkj ;ksx vkSj /;kuH;kl ds izHkko ls eu dh xUnxh izdV gksus yxrh gSA lk/kd dks eu ij lrdZ n`fV j[kuh pkfg,A vgadkj dh tM+s xgjh gksrh gSaA /;ku ds vH;klks dks viuk LoHkko e/kqj vkSj lkSE; cukdj vuqdwyukhyrk dk xq.k vftZr djuk pkfg,A /;ku ,d vkoj.k dh HkkWfr lkeus vk tkrk gS vkSj ekufld n`fV dks /kqW/kyk cuk nsrk gSA izxfrkhy O;fDr dks vius nqxqZ.ksa dks Lohdkj djds nwj djuk pkfg,A','','NA','lfOkrk, lksgu jkt rkrsM','0','NO'