ttitude which denotes that computer has made a tremendous influence in the field of education','','-','\"\"Geeta Rai ;\r\nAradhana Sharma\"','73-80','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','46','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(793,'Determinents Of Income And Employment Of Women In Urban Informal Sector  A Study In Visakhapatnam City','In recent years the informal sector has acquired great significance over the years as a source of employment and livelihood for an increasing number of people, especially women, in both urban and rural areas of the developing world. The reason for this may be that the informal sector activities are characterised by easy entry, reliance on indigenous resources, negligible capital investment, labour intensiveness and highly competitive unregulated markets. So far, considerable numbers of studies have been undertaken for analyzing the socio-economic characteristics, income and employment in the informal sector of rural areas but not much light thrown on the urban informal sector. This study made an attempt to fill this gap and concluded that the poverty levels and the employment levels are low among petty trading households. Since the migration is the main cause for the overcrowding of urban labour market, the government has to formulate and adopt the policies which are useful to reduce the migration from rural areas to urban areas and implement the Programmes to improve the technical skills among women who have already settled in the urban informal sector, because the lack of skill is the main cause for low levels of income and employment in urban informal sector.','','-','D.Narayana Rao','81-88','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','46','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(794,'Strategic Management Of Merger Decision And Swap Ratio Valuation:\r\n (Case Study Of Bank Of Rajasthan (Bor) Merger With ICICI Bank)','Mergers may be synergy based to derive economies of scale or market driven mergers between banks and financial institutions in the interests of furthering universal banking. Since 1997, ICICI Bank has acquired smaller banks to increase its reach. Recent takeovers include Sangli Bank in 2007, ITC Classic Finance and Anagram Finance in the years 1997 and 1998 respectively. In 2000, the bank merged with the Bank of Madura and in 2005, it acquired Russias IvestitsionnoKreditny Bank.The merger of ICICI Bank and Jaipur-based BoR came into effect from 12 August after the Reserve Bank of India notified it. After the bank received permission for the merger in August 12, 2010, it said that it has successfully integrated the operations of the BoR with the ICICI Bank. The acquisition of Bank of Rajasthan by ICICI bank is the first consolidation of country\'s crowded banking sector since 2008. ICICI, the country\'s largest private sector lender, is offering the smaller bank\'s controlling shareholders 25 shares in ICICI for 118 shares of Bank of Rajasthan.The deal, which will give ICICI a sizeable presence in the northwestern desert state of Rajasthan, values the small bank at about 2.9 times its book value, compared with an Indian banking sector average of 1.84. Post-merger, ICICI Bank\'s branch network would go up to 2,463.  Keeping in view the most recent concern about banking sector the present paper is an attempt to understand the trends of Merger and Acquisition in Indian banks. Some important issues have been discussed. It also identifies the motives and associated risks of M&As with special reference to an Indian perspective. The study gives conclusion and some suggestions too.','','-','S. K. SHARMA','89-96','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','46','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(795,'CHANGING ROLE OF THE TEACHER IN 21st CENTURY','In the fast changing world of the early 21st century, public education is also changing. As part of the changes, the role of schools and education will also be different both in the educational system and in the society. Together with them, the role of teachers will also change. It is clear that the teachers role must be redefined to meet the needs and demands of todays culture.','','-','SURINDER SINGH THAKUR','97-102','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','46','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(796,'Women Empowerment: Pathway Towards National Development','The root cause of the ailing state of the world today is crisis of faith, peoples ignorance of the powers of the innerself, and the lack of righteous altitude. Man and woman are complementary to each other. Both together form the family and thus contribute to the making of the society, nation and the world as a whole. Gain or loss of one in any form is that of the other too. The orthodox, egotist or selfish men, who consider women as the weaker sex must understand that the rise and amelioration of womens status is going to be of greater help to men as well. \r\nWomen have been weakened by long years of neglect, injustice, oppression and exploitation. No system can survive with a sick vital component. The international women year has set the ball in motion. The present paper highlights how women empowerment through education can help in national development.','','-','\"\"Sudarshana Rana  ;\r\nPrabha Jishtu\"','103-108','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','46','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(797,'Effect Of Integrated Syntax Of Advance Organizer Model And Inductive Thinking Model On Achievement And Retention Of Class IX Students In Mathematics','The present study aims to investigate the effect of Integrated Syntax of Advance Organizer Model and Inductive Thinking Model on achievement and retention of class IX students in mathematics. For this purpose a sample of 60 students is drawn from IX class students from a school at Kurukshetra (Haryana) affiliated to CBSE. Two groups of students each comprising 30 students were formed and were labelled as Experimental Group (A1), and control group (A2). Both the groups were equated on intelligence using Ravens Progressive Matrices Test. Lesson plans on Integrated Syntax (AOM and ITM) were prepared and  implemented after pre-testing on Achievement Test. After completion of the instructional treatment achievement test was administered twice as post test-I and post test-II (Retention Test) to students of Experimental group and Control group both. Three-Way ANOVA was used to arrive at the following conclusions: (i) Experimental Group was found to attain significantly higher achievement scores as compared to Control Group;(ii) Experimental Group also was found to attain significantly higher retention  scores as compared to Control Group.','','-','Puneet Walia','109-118','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','46','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(798,'A Study Of Aggression Among Senior Secondary School Students In Relation To Their Self Esteem, Institution Type And Stream Of Studies','Aggression is defined as behaviour intended to cause harm or pain either directly or indirectly. These days aggressive behavior has become a topic of vital importance and a major concern in most societies.. Violence is disturbingly common in most parts of the world and it is undoubtedly creating chaos and disturbing the world peace and harmony. The researches told many factors which are responsible for the production of aggression. Self esteem is the feeling or affective part of our picture of ourselves. It refers to the evaluation a person makes and customarily maintains with regard to him or herself. Self esteem expresses an attitude of approval or disapproval and indicates the extent to which a person believes him or herself capable, significant, successful and worthy. A sample consisted of 473 students was drawn by using multistage stratified random sampling technique to study the aggression among senior secondary school students in relation to their self esteem, institution type and stream of studies. In order to collect the requisite data, Aggression Scale by Dr. G.P. Mathur & Dr. Raj Kumari Bhatnagar  and Self Esteem Inventory by M.S. Prasad and G.P. Thakur were administered on the selected school students. The results revealed that senior secondary school students studying in Science stream have significantly higher level of aggression in comparison to Arts stream students. Further, it was found that students studying in private institutions were found more aggressive in comparison to students studying in government institutions.','','-','\"\"Rajesh Kumar ;\r\nAnup Kumar\"','119-126','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','46','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(799,'A Comparative Study Of Professional Commitment Of B.T.C. And Special B.T.C. Primary Teachers','Professional Commitment plays a decisive role in effective teaching.  The more a tacher is committed, more he would acquire competencies and more he would tend to be performing teacher. Professional committed teachers are required in in order to increase the quality of primary education. This promoted the investigator to compare teaching professional commitment between B.T.C. and special B.T.C. teachers.','','-','Rekha Sharma','127-132','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','46','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(800,'Shgs - Bank Linkage Programme: Issues And Challenges','Micro finance, a concept that is helping the poor to avail of and create economic growth opportunities. In India, micro finance has fueled the efforts at rural development, women empowerment and wealth generation by providing small-scale savings, credit, insurance and any other financial service to poor and low-income households. In India, micro finance scene is dominated by Self Help Groups (SHGs)-Bank linkage programme, aimed at providing mechanism for providing financial services to the unreached poor. The ultimate aim of SHGs-Bank linkage is to attain social and economic empowerment of poor people. Direct credit from banks and government is available to potentials SHGs, at this movement has became a powerful instrument for poverty alleviation by providing a cost effective mechanism of  credit service to unreached poor. Nevertheless it is not a panacea to all the problems of poverty, but it is indeed a catalyst to a great extent in facilitating a better quality of life for the low-income population. This paper attempts to study of SHGs- Bank linkage programme as its significant progress and focuses on some issues and challenges also.','','-','A.B. Thapliyal','133-136','NO','-','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','28','46','2013-07-23 17:36:30','e',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(801,'orZeku o izkphu f\'k{k.k O;oLFkk dh f\'k{k.k fof/k;ksa dk rqyukRed v/;;u','\'k{kk fdlh Hkh lekt dk niZ.k gksrk gSA izR;sd jk\"V  dh mUufr mldh f\'k{kk O;oLFkk ij fuHkZj jgrh gSA ftl jk\"V esa tSlh f\'k{kk O;oLFkk gksxh oSlk gh og jk\"V rFkk oSls gh mlds ukxfjd gksxsaA bl fo\"k; esa gekjk Hkkjr ns\'k lkSHkkX;\'kkyh gSA izkphu dky ls gh Hkkjrh; f\'k{k.k O;oLFkk dh f\'k{k.k fof/k;ka mPp dksfV dh jgh gS rFkk f\'k{kk dk ekxZ vklku djrh jgh gS ijUrq vkt Hkkjr esa izpfyr f\'k{kk O;oLFkk dh f\'k{k.k fof/k;kasa esa vkewy pwd ifjorZu vk x;sa gSA tSls tSls tul[;ka c<+h f\'k{kk laLFkkvksa dk Lo:i cnyk rFkk f\'k{k.k fof/k;ks esa Hkh ifjorZu vk;s rFkk f\'k{k.k fof/k;ksa dks mn~ns\';ksa ls lEcfU/kr djrs gq, mudks f\'k{k.k O;w