gate the supply chain that consists of suppliers, manufacturers, distributors and retailers. Each one of them holds inventory in some form to support the requirement of the customer at the end of the chain. In supply chain many problems still need a careful consideration regarding solution procedure to support respective systems. \r\n','','Deteriorating inventory, in general, is defined as decay, damaged, spoilage, evaporation, obsolescence, pilferage, Loss of marginal value of a commodity',' Sudhakar Singh, S.R. Singh',' 95-108','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','34','50','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(840,'  A Partially Lost Sales Production Inventory Model with Ramp Type Demand Rate with Variable Holding Cost ','In this paper  a production inventory model is proposed for non-instantaneous deteriorating items with ramp type demand rate. Production rate is taken as demand dependent. Deterioration is taken as Weibull distribution. Shortages are allowed and partially backlogged. Also it is assumed that the supplier offered a price discount to the customers during the decaying period by which demand increases, moreover the inventory level fall down rapidly by which loss due to deterioration becomes least. In this model two cases are considered: (1) deterioration starts during the production period (2) deterioration starts after the production has been stopped. Holding cost is taken as time dependent. Numerical experiment is provided and sensitivity analysis with respect to system parameters is also carried out. ','','Not Available ','  V K Sharma, Sadhna Singh ',' 109-120  ','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','34','50','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(843,'  Some Well Known Elliptic Type Integrals and their Hypergeometric Forms','Hypergeometric forms of different  elliptic-type integrals have