osmical flight aerodynamics, plasma physics, Glass production and furnace engineering. Velocity of the flow has been presented for various parameters. In this study velocity of fluid increases with the increase in Gm (Grashof number), but it decreases with the increase in H (Hartmann number) and Sc (Schmidt number).','','Rivlin-Ericksen fluid, Magnetic field, Mass transfer,  An arbitrary inclined plane','Manoj Nagaich, Virendra Prasad and N. K. Varshney','103-108','NO','','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','36','55','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(941,' An EPQ Model under Permissible Delay in Payments with Stock Dependent Demand for decaying Items','Trade credit is the most succeeding economic phenomenon which is used by the supplier for encouraging the retailers to buy more quantity. In this paper a mathematical model with stock dependent demand with deterioration is developed to investigate the retailers optimal inventory policy under the scheme of permissible delay in payment. The objective is to minimize the total average cost of the system. To exemplify hypothesis of the proposed model numerical examples and sensitivity analysis are provided.','','-','Satyender Shon, Pankaj Singh','137-146','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','54','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(942,'EOQ Model for Decaying Items with Trade Credit and Exponential Demand Under Inflation','In this paper we have discussed the situation when the retailer has some  money available to him in the beginning of the transaction, but still wants to avail the facility of credit period offered by the supplier. In this study, we have taken  exponential demand rate. To make our study more suitable to present day market, we have done our research in an inflationary environment. The theory has been exemplified in the end with numerical results and sensitivity analysis for managerial insights.','','-','Satyender Shon, Pankaj Singh',' 147-156','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','56','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(947,' Social and Psychological Correlates of well-being ','The present paper examines how well-being is shaped by various social and psychological influences. Well-being is a dynamic concept that includes subjective, social, and psychological dimensions as well as health-related behaviours that leads to differing assumptions. Traditionally, well-being has been identified with a single objective dimension: material progress measured by income or GDP. However, it is now widely accepted that the concept of well-being cannot be captured solely by GDP.  Subjective measures: asking people to report on their happiness and life satisfaction. Recently this conventional view has been changed. Currently well-being is reorganized with host variables such as actualization of human potential on ones true nature, self esteem, emotion, physical health, social class, wealth, attachment and relatedness etc. It is hoped that the article will draw attention to related concept of well-being in more precise terms. This contribute to individuals overall well-being.   ','','Well-Being ','  Krishna Sharma,  P. S. N. Tiwari   ',' 169-180  ','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(948,' Educational Research in Malaysia-A Critical Review','Educational research has attended a pivotal position in the knowledge society. However the challenges are numerous in Malaysian educational system where priority is given to education in budget allocation. For creative and innovative education, importance is given to Educational research in various phases. This paper focused various research issues as well as new fields of research in education. Further it also emphasized research directions for future and recommendations for better Educational research in Malaysia. ','','Educational research, Research issues, Research trends',' Gyanendra Kumar Rout','181-188','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(949,' Effect of Advertisement on Buying Behavior of Consumers of Durable Product  (A Study of Bike Segment in Kanpur Region)','Marketing in India is growing in an indefinable phase. In addition to this, it is the changing role of customers from the Karta of the family to the kid especially in making purchase decision and the way in which the new generation Indian customers behaves. Many new upcoming trends have been seen in the twenty first century, the pattern of consumption of two wheelers has undergone a sea change. A traditional family in India is different from a western family. The behavioral attitude and decision making process for purchase of durables is quite elaborate as the characteristics of Indian families are changing under the influence of external factors such as liberalization and media explosion.\r\nToday advertisement plays a major role in purchase decision of actual and potential; customers. It is an important marketing function. It is true that customers are very much influenced through advertisement. Just like fire, advertisement can be used for both positive and negative marketing. When fire is used in controlled way it produces beneficial results. If fire is use without any control it creates destruction. Advertisement has the same effect. It is the powerful tool of consumer marketing. In the modern business world advertising plays a vital role in pushing up the sales. Its main purpose is to bring the product in the knowledge of consumers and persuade them to buy the product. Society is deeply affected by the great shell of advertising.','','Difference of family status, Advertisement',' Neha Gupta,  Ruchi Thakur',' 189-198','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(950,' Insecurity of Women in Society Promoting Stereotype Gender Values','In the present time the issue of gender has increasingly been recognized as an important variable in development discourse both in the national and international arena. The Population of Uttarakhand has always had a greater balance in sex ratio than found among other states. Given that the sex ratio is a fairly good index of gender inequalities and discrimination in a society, the more balanced sex ratio in the population of Uttarakhand is indicative of more balanced gender relations and less discrimination as compared to other states. Experience has shown that womens stereotype gender values at the micro level with a view to involving them in their own development has more meaning for these people in Uttarakhand. The policy-makers at national or State-level should assure the participation of different weaker sections of society at micro-level in preparation of different policies.','','Sex Ratio, Type of Gender',' Pradeep Kumar,  R. K. Saini,  Hemlata Saini',' 199-204','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(951,' A Study of Academic Achievements of Secondary Students of C.B.S.E. & U.P. Board Schools in Meerut as per their Study Habits','The Present study finds out a Study of Academic Achievements of Secondary Students of C.B.S.E. and U.P. Board Schools in Meerut as per their study Habits students from U.P. Board & 100 students from C.B.S.E. board were randomly selected from ten schools of U.P. Board and 10 school from C.B.S.E. board of Meerut district on the basis of their scores on Academic Achievements scale developed by Self constructed tool viz. is to obtain a reliable & valid measures of the Academic Achievement of Secondary Students. The significance of the present study is not less important from both points of views; Psychologist and educationalists have correlated the Academic Achievement with the various Psychological Independent and Sociological Independent variables of the Secondary Students. Research finding of such studies can also develop some theories about the psychological factors of teachers and these theories may be utilized in developing the personality of Secondary Students.','','Study Habits, different tests, academic activities',' Arun Kumar,  Rachna Tyagi',' 205-216','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(952,' Maslows hierarchy of needs and Yoga Chakras in Applied Psychology','Yoga means to unite or joint the aspects of ourselves which were never really divide in the first place. It also means to yoke or engage ourselves in a self-training programme. Yoga means working with each of the levels or aspects of our being individually, and then unifying all of those in to their original whole.  It shows connection or bond between yoga and Maslow need hierarchy model of psychology that has become extremely well known not only in the field of psychology, but also in management and other human sciences. It describes five developmental stages, which are based on what Maslow calls human needs.The comparison of the stages of yoga psychology to the stages off Maslows need hierarchy is being presented here as a way of explaining nature of yoga as a process of developmental self awareness or enfoldment  which reaches still higher levels of human development or experience.','','descriptive and analytical approach',' Shubha Maheshwari',' 217-225','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(953,' Programmes through Marketing Strategies of Dabur India Limited','Dabur India Limited, a fast moving consumer goods company, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the production, sourcing, and marketing of personal care, health care, home care, consumer health care, and food products. The companys personal care products comprise herbal and ayurvedic products for hair care and skin care, including hair oils, shampoos, facial kits, body bleaches, hair removal creams, anti-ageing products, face scrubs and washes, face masks and creams, and skin repair creams; and oral care products, such as toothpastes, toothpowders, and gels. It has home care products as well as food products and consumer health care products. The company also operates specialized beauty retail stores under the New U brand name merchandizing a range of beauty care products. It offers its products primarily under the Dabur, Vatika, Hajmola, Ral, and Fem brand names. The company sells its products through agents, distributors, and retail outlets in India. It also serves customers in the Middle East, Africa, the United States, and south Asia.','','Survay on different goods, all type of care',' Anil Kumar',' 227-239','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(954,' A Comprehensive Study of Marketing Charges in Jewellery Industry in Meerut District','In modern marketing system, the marketing area of a product becomes so wide that the commodity reaches in the hands of ultimate consumers passing through different marketing channels. This is also done in case of Jewellery. In case of Jewellery the marketing cost starts from manufacturer\'s/wholesaler\'s level and ends at the point when the Jewellery reaches in the hands of the buyers. These marketing channels have their eminent importance but it is a bare fact that each and every marketing channel, used for physical distribution of a product has its own cost. So it becomes inevitable to go through all the expenses at different levels of marketing, so that it may clearly be judged whether these expenses are justified, and every marketing channel is getting its share in a justified manner. In the present research paper the marketing charges involved in Jewellery industry of Meerut has been taken into consideration. It is believed that the conclusion drawn at the end of the research will through light on various marketing charges and help in reducing the undue charges if any.','','Jewellery Market, Different type of Expenses',' S. K. Agarwal,  Amit Kansal','241-252','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(955,' Role Conflict in Relation to Professional Commitment of the School Teachers','In this study looked in to the relationship between role conflict and professional commitment of school teachers of Meerut region. A cluster sampling method was used with 400 (rural and urban) school teachers. Date was measured by the role conflict scale (Gupta, S.P.) and Professional Commitment (Sharma Aryendra). Statistical finding of study, total role conflict of rural and urban school teachers is significantly related with their professional commitment and total role conflict rural and urban school teachers are significantly related with their total role conflict and professional commitment.','','Role conflict, \r\nDiffusiveness Conflict,\r\nMarginal Conflict, Commitment Conflict,\r\nProfessional commitment',' Sharad Kumar Agarwal ',' 253-258','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(956,' Marketing Strategies of the Companies for Customer Care','When a customer visits a local retailer to buy furniture. They are able to benefit in some cases from the additional service of having the furniture installed for them. At the same time hopefully they will get a good \'service\' from the retailer, who will be happy to help them with advice about the properties of different types of furniture, repayment terms, delivery etc. If an oil company assumed that the function of its retail network was simply to sell petrol and lubricants it would quickly lose business to competitors. Its real function is to supply a \'customer service\' in its case the service of enjoyable, trouble-free motoring. Customer service is one of the most important ingredients of the marketing mix for products and services. High quality customer service helps to create customer loyalty. Customers today are not only interested in the product they are being offered but all the additional elements of service that they receive from the greeting they receive when they enter a retail outlet, to the refund and help that they receive when they have a complaint about a faulty product that they have paid for.','','Customers, Product, Selling Machanishm',' Babinder Gupta','259-268','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(957,' Non Banking Financial Companies in India: Problems and Suggestions','In India considerable growth has taken place in the non-banking financial sector in recent years. Over a period of time they are successful in rendering a wide range of services. Initially intended to cater to the needs of savers and investors, NBFCs later on developed into institutions that can provide services similar to banks. In India several factors have contributed to the growth of NBFCs. This article focuses on the problems faced by the NBFCs and also suggests solutions for these problems.','','Non Banking Financial Companies, Risk, Need',' Lokesh Goel,  Shailendra Bhushan Sharma',' 269-274','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(958,' Gandhian Philosophy-Todays Need','A Gandhian can mean either an individual who follows, or a specific philosophy which is attributed to Gandhism. Gandhism is not a systematic position in metaphysics or in political philosophy. Rather it is a political creed, an economic doctrine, a religious outlook, a moral percept, and especially a humanitarian world view. It is an effort, not to systemize wisdom but to transform society and is based on an undying faith in the goodness of human nature. In this tumultuous and strife-torn world, the ideas and teachings of Gandhiji have become all the more important. It is a fitting tribute to the Light of the world that United Nations has declared 2nd October, the birthday of Mahatma, as the International Day of Non-Violence from 2007 onwards.\r\nPresident of United States, Barack Obama in an address to joint session of the Parliament of India 2010, said that: I am mindful that i might not be standing in front of you today, as President of United States, had it not been for Gandhi and the message he shared with America and the world. On September 2009, he said that his biggest inspiration came from Mahatma Gandhi. His reply was in response to the question: Who was the one person, dead or alive, that you would chose to dine with? He continued that, He is somebody i find a lot of inspiration in. He inspired Dr. King with his message of non-violence. He ended up doing so much and changed the world just by the power of his ethics.','','Solely, Constitute, Revolt, Self-Reliant, Rejoice, Incessant, Fiery, Irksome',' Mahima Gupta','275-278','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(959,' Xykscy okfeZax ds] d`fk ,oa lkekftd&vkfFkZd flLVe ij nq\"izHkkoksa o blls jkgr ds mik;ksa dk v/;;u % esjB e.My] fokskdj tuin cqyUnkgj esa','Xykscy okfeZa