ess of value runs through the life of all individuals. The senses communicate, the value operate, the person feels, experiences decides and acts. These are all value judgments which covers the entire contagion of human activities.','','Humen Behaviour, Values',' Seema Rani','315-319','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(965,' SWM through GIS: A Brif Study of Saharanpur City','This paper describes a method for deriving a build up urban area for large urban regions using GIS based Spatial set up for the urban problems i.e. Sewer & Solid Waste many. Our main impulse on the solid waste management. The purpose was to develop a method that could be used to delineate a consolidated built up urban area in any urban region. Although the method described within is specific to time, place and software it should be adaptable to other circumstances. The consolidated built up urban area data set was to be used to examine residential intensification trends \"A methodology for estimating the rate of residential intensification between two master plan\'s of Saharanpur city between 1985-2001 & 2001 to 2022 i.e. the proposed purposed master plan. And we used to these data in the preparation on of GIS based management plan of solid waste management.','','GIS Model, Trends, Industories',' Arvind Kumar Arora',' 321-327','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(966,' GIS as Future Trend of E-goverence: A Process Developed in ULB\'s ','Local self government is one of the largest application areas for GIS as it is one of the largest users of spatial information. All areas of a local authority may benefit from GIS may be used in land research and planning control, replacing exisiting paper records, local authorities may also use GIS for properly and 