ge boy who from the state of extreme penury sets on a journey of self exploration.  The protagonist Jagat Ram is prototype of those who struggle hard out of their obscurities and strive hard for self actualization. In this sense the story is both contemporary and universal in appeal. The authors lofty language and inimitable style at once matches with his postmodern concerns of ontology.\r\nThe novel is accessible to all by ordering on pothi.com which a Bangalore based company is offering a print on demand.','','English Novel, Fiction, Languages',' Rekha Narula',' 379-385','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1004,' Impact of Media on Sales Promotion Activities In India after Globalisation','Consumer promotion is an important component of a small business\'s overall marketing strategy, along with advertising, public relations, and personal selling. The American Marketing Association (AMA) defines consumer promotion as \"media and non-media marketing pressure applied for a predetermined, limited period of time in order to stimulate sale, increase consumer demand, or improve product quality.\" But this definition does not capture all the elements of modern sales promotion. Effective consumer promotion increases the basic value of product for a limited time and directly stimulates consumer purchasing, selling effectiveness, or the effort of the sales force. It can be used to inform, persuade, and remind target customers about the business and its marketing mix. Some common types of consumer promotion include samples, coupons, sweepstakes, contests, in-store displays, trade shows, price-off deals, premiums, and rebates.','','AMA, Consumers, Demand',' Anil Kumar Mittra, Dharm Bir Singh',' 387-396','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1005,' A Note on New Bilinear Multiple Generating Function   ','The object of this paper is to obtain a Bilinear multiple generating functions and its generalization form   ','','Multiple generating functions, fractional derivative operators, bilinear generating function.   ','   A.H. Khan and A.A.L. Atash   ','173-178      ','YES','16 ITMSC.11.docx','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1006,' A Note on Generating Functions Involving Laguerre, Legendre and Gegenbauer Polynomials  ','The main object of this paper is to obtain a general class of generating function for Laguerre, Legendre and Gegenbauer polynomials with the help of Weisners group theoretic method.\r\nActually, we have extended the results given by Majundar and Kar and Basu to new general theorem on general class of generating functions.\r\n  ','','Generating functions, weirners group theoretic method, LAGUERRE, LEGENDRE AND GEGENDAUER Polynomials.  ','  A.H. Khan and A.A.L. Atash  ','179-186    ','YES','17 ITMSC.11.docx','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1007,' On Obtaing Double generating functions of F3 (x,y,z) ','Many generating function involving (known and new) Appell is double hypergeometric function F2 and Kampe de Feriet function of two variable  which are used to obtain our main results. ','','generating functions, Appell is double hypergeometric functions and Kampe de Feriet functions.  ',' A.H. Khan and A.A.L. Atash ','187-191  ','YES','18 ITMSC.11.docx','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1008,'A Short Note on Laguerre Polynomials of Several Variables ','In this paper we have established some double generation function involving general triple hypergeometric series F3 [x,y,z] by using the generating functions. ','','Generating function, triple hypergeometric functions, Laguerre polynomials ',' A.H. Khan and A.A.L. Atash ','193-198  ','YES','19 ITMSC.11.docx','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','1','1','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1009,' The Study of the effects of Solar Flares on Radio- Communication through F2 layer','Solar radiations and other solar activities affect the total electron content of the ionosphere and also affect various radio frequencies used in radio- Communications.  This paper aims to study the effect of   solar flare of 4 Nov. 2003 of 23rd solar cycle , on the critical frequencies of ionospheric  F2 layer over Athens (38N-24E) . The result of this study will provide information for weather casting and also enable radio-communication industries to make predictions and necessary adjustment to maximize their operational frequencies and thus achieve optimum result.','','-','Rachna Sharma, Pooja Gupta and Udit Narain','305-312','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','34','51','2013-07-23 17:36:30','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1010,' Reliability and Mean Time to System Failure (MTSF) Evaluation of a Complex System by Using Algebraic Method   ','The reliability and MTFS of a complex system has been calculated when failure rate follow the exponential or Weibull distribution by using algebraic method. This algorithm is based on the well known theorem of expansion of the algebra of logic in conformity. A graphical behavior of this complex system has been discussed with respect to reliability and MTFS to observe the effect of system performance.   ','','Complex System, Reliability, MTFS, Algebraic method.   ',' Pawan Sharma, R.K. Sharma   ',' 313-322      ','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','34','51','2013-09-19 03:09:31','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1011,' fd\'kksjkoLFkk esa vkgkjh; vknrksa ij QkLV QwM lsou dk nq\"izHkko','-','','-',' iwue oekZ',' 397-404','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-07-23 17:36:30','H',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1012,' An Indepth Study of Individual and Group Incentives at HAIER ','In the present sub point, the researcher presents the actual incentive systems prevailing at Haier Appliances India Pvt. Ltd. and various units/branches of the company. Haier believes in individual as-well-as group incentives. Such group incentives promote morale as-well-as productivity resulting in higher production both in quality as-well-as quantity. The researcher examined carefully various sections of the company both at office and works. It was found by the researcher that group incentives are available in the works but not at the offices which is also needed to raise the morale of office people in the company. ','','Haier, carefully, incentives. ','Rajat ','405-408  ','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-09-04 13:08:41','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1013,' Physical Outline of National Level Power Lifters ','Education contributes to the development, advancement and Perfection of the nations culture. It is often described as a process that strives to produce desirable changes in the behavior of individual. The Modern education is concerned with the development of an individual through at integrated approach that is to shape the individual to fit in the society, which maintains advances social order. ','','Perfection, Education, Social order ','Reema Tyagi ','409-412  ','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-09-04 13:08:41','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1015,'Human Factor in Motivation and Individual VS Group Incentives','There are two important principles of motivation participation and communication. An essential condition for participation is association f sub-ordinates in all matters related to their jobs. Without a true mutual interest, there can be no serious application and little chance for concerted and effective effort. Everyone, emphasised Charles P. Mc Cormick as early as 1932, likes to be a contributing member of a group. His effort is utmost when his sense of belonging is deepest. An essential condition for participation is association of sub-ordinates in all matters related to their jobs.','','Principles, Mutual interest, Participation','Rajat','413-416','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-09-04 15:18:02','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1016,' A production inventory model for deteriorating items with shortages and time dependent exponentially decreasing demand','In this paper, a production-inventory model for deteriorating items is developed over a finite planning horizon where the demand decreasing exponentially with time. The production rate is assumed to be finite and constant. Shortages in inventory are allowed and are completely backlogged. Deterioration rate is constant. As a result, we establish a model to find the optimum values of time and inventory level by minimizing the average cost.','','Production inventory, time-dependent demand, deteriorating item, shortages.',' Balvinder Singh Sandhu , Arun Kumar Tomer ',' 243-252','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','32','48','2013-09-17 12:47:31','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1017,' Analysis of Flexibility and Reliability for Production System with Impatient Customers','The classical production inventory models assume that items produced by perfectly reliable production process with a fixed set-up cost. It is fact that the reliability of the production process cannot be reduced without investment in flexibility improvement. In this paper, an optimal production run time model with flexibility and reliability (of production process) and with shortages under limited storage capacity is developed. Profit function is optimized by using constraint signomial modified geometric programming to determine optimal decision for the decision makers (DM). A numerical example has been considered to illustrate the model.','','Imperfect production system, Reliability, Shortages, Geometric Programming, Limited Storage Capacity',' Pawan Sharma, R.K. Sharma',' 253-270','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','32','48','2013-09-17 12:49:43','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1018,'Variable Selection for the Accelerated Failure Time Model as an Alternative to the Cox Proportional Hazards Model','The Cox proportional hazards model has become the model of choice in the analysis of time to event data in survival analysis. If the effects of treatment are to accelerate (or delay) the event of interest rather than having a longer term impact, in the context of the trial duration, on the occurrence of the event, then the accelerated failure time model should replace the proportional hazards model as the model of choice. In this paper a brief review of some variable selection procedures based on Accelerated Failure Time (AFT) model for the analysis of censored data. The application of variable selection for the AFT model to the survival analysis has also been discussed with real-life examples.','','Cox Proportional Hazards model, Censored data, Accelerated Failure Time Model, Buckley  James estimator, Millers estimator.','R. Elangovan and A. Lokeshmaran',' 271-28','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','32','48','2013-11-21 16:16:02','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1019,' Supply Chain Model for Oil Refinery','This paper concentrates on supply chain problem in oil refinery. A mathematical model for the oil refinery supply chain is characterized by complete horizontal integration of systems from crude oil purchase through to product distribution. The study assume that the configuration of the integrated refinery network already exist, therefore the decision variables that are discrete or binary in nature are avoided by establishing them prior and making them parameters in the LP model.','','Oil Refinery, Supply Chain, Crude Supply Constraints, Refining Process Constraints, Product Distribution Constraints, Linking Constraints',' Quse .M.H. Shihab and V.H. Bajaj','01-14','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','39','61','2013-09-17 12:55:43','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1020,' A Production Model with Ramp Type Time Dependent Demand on Damageable Items in Volume Flexible Environment','This paper hypothesizes a production inventory system with time dependent ramp type function over the entire season. Inventory model is developed here with damageable items which get damaged due to stress of stocked items. The stress function is taken to both cases linear and non-linear. The unit production cost is a function of finite production rate which is treated as decision variable. The solution process is illustrated with the help of numerical examples. ','','Volume flexibility, damageable items, exponential ramp type demand',' S.R. Singh, Urvashi',' 15-30','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','39','61','2013-09-17 12:57:28','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1021,' A Stochastic Model to Determine the Expected Time to Seroconversion of HIV Infected Due to Antigenic Diversity or Virulence','In HIV infection and its progression to AIDS, the expected time to seroconversion is an important aspect. This is a vital issue because antiretroviral therapy (ART) can be suitably introduced so that the time to seroconversion can be prolonged. The antigenic diversity threshold and the expected time to cross the same due to the increase in antigenic diversity in successive contacts has been discussed by using Stochastic models by several authors. In this paper the concept of virulence is also taken into consideration. There is contribution to virulence also due to successive contacts. The expected time to seroconversion by taking into consideration both antigenic diversity threshold and virulence threshold is discussed, and the expected time to seroconversion is obtained. Numerical illustration is also provided.','','Seroconversion, Antiretroviral Therapy, Antigenic Diversity Threshold, Virulence Threshold',' U. Niyamathulla, R. Elangovan and R. Sathiyamoorthi',' 31-40','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','','','2013-09-17 12:58:38','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1023,' Study of Software Improvement Models for Small Organization Development','Software Development is the process to illustrate the overall mechanism involved in the progress of software during different stages of development. To moderate the computational efficiency of earlier and later phases of development often occurred in small scale software developing organization we have proposed a new software development model for small organization. Through this model we can elicit the software requirement and we can also compute the functionality and risk in each and every phase of the software development.','','Software Model, Elicitation Techniques, Function Point, Software Risk',' Anoop Sharma  Mukesh Yadav',' 417-426','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','2','','2013-09-18 06:36:06','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1026,' Infrared and Ultraviolet Spectral Studies of a Few Complicated Organic and Complex Molecules','In this paper Infrared and Ultraviolet Studies of a few complicated organic and complex molecules primarily aims at the elucidation of their structures.Vibrational data collected in the range 200 cm.-1 to 4000 cm.-1 have been interpreted to ascertain different functional groups. Atom and coordination sites in the organic ligands.','','I.R. Spectroscopy, Buckner funnel, Vacuum desiccators, Perkin Elmer-580 spectrophotometer, 4- Hydroxy 1- naphthylglyoxal solution',' Sushil Kumar and Divya Hans',' 733-742','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','30','53','2013-09-19 01:57:38','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1027,' Parameters of Non Destructive Evaluation and Testing via Ultrasonics: An Overview','The present paper makes an attempt to view the literature about the parameters affecting Ultrasonic testing. Presently the ultrasonic has emerged as a valuable tool both in the field of medicine and industry. While in medicine field it is applied extensively for detection of abnormalities in human body, in the industrial sector, it ensures the safety and reliability of welds, components and plants.The reliability of any NDT technique depends on the judicious understanding of the parameters that affect Ultrasonic testing and the proper application of the technique','','Ultrasonic testing, Sound Velocity, Acoustic Attenuation,Impedance',' Jatinder Chhabra and Brajesh Tripathi',' 743-756','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','30','53','2013-09-19 01:59:04','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1028,' Review on the effect of substitution in basic lithium ferrites','Lithium ferrite has emerged in recent years as a material that shows significant technological application, the properties being dependent on substitution to a large extent. This review article provides a summary of fundamental theoretical aspects of lithium ferrite and the effect of substitution','','Lithium Ferrites, Dielectric constant, DC resistivity, Curie temperature, Saturation-magnetization, Initial permeability',' Ibetombi Soibam',' 757-761','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','30','53','2013-09-19 02:00:30','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1029,' A warehouse production model with linear demand and decaying items under the inflationary environment','In this chapter, we developed a production model with time dependent demand and deterioration.  Shortages are allowed and completely backlogged. Inflation is also taken in this chapter. A single item deterministic inventory model with two separate warehouses called owned warehouse/show-room (OW) and rented warehouse (RW) is developed. The stocks of RW are shipped to OW under continuous release pattern. We discuss different scenarios of the proposed model to address relative size of stock. The capacity of owned warehouse is limited and capacity of rented warehouse is unlimited. The proposed model of the paper is also examined using some numerical examples and sensitivity analysis is performed','','Warehouse production model, time dependent demand, shortages, inflation',' Ruby Bhardwaj, D. Singh, and A.P. Singh',' 763-776','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','30','53','2013-09-19 02:01:30','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1030,' On effects of space Weather on Technologies','Space Weather effects on technology are manifold and can be experienced in deep space as well as on the surface of the earth, Space weather effects are linked to the conditions in space environment, which largely are controlled by the Sun. In this article we have described the basic facts for understanding processes responsible for space weather effects on (i) satellites, (ii) power systems, (iii) radio propagation, (iv)  communication cables and various others .All the events under our study are associated with CME\'s, flares, particle radiations and plasmas','','-',' Rachna Sharma, Pooja Gupta and Udit Narain',' 157-172','NO','','International Transactions in App