que. Finally, numerical examples together with sensitivities analysis have been discussed to illustrate the procedure of solving the model and concluding remarks are provided.','','Two warehouse, exponential demand, permissible delay.',' S. R. Singh, P. K. Saini',' 273-284','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','56','2013-09-19 02:41:54','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1042,' Simulation of Bed Profile of Bhakra Reservoir using Artificial Neural Network','In this paper, the development of an ANN model for simulation of sediment bed profile of Bhakra dam has been carried out by taking the inputs as inflow, outflow, rainfall, average rainfall intensity, sediment inflow, sediment outflow, trap efficiency and bed profiles observed by the hydro graphic survey. The performance of the ANN models has been analysed using statistical indices such as coefficient of correlation and Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) during the calibration and validation. It is observed from the results that the performance of the ANN model in simulating the bed profile was getting improved with increase in neurons in the hidden layer during calibration. The same trend was also observed in the performance of the model during the validation.  It is determined that from the result that the ANN models with the considered inputs give good performance in simulating the bed profile in the reservoir','','Artificial Neural Network, Simulation, Coefficient of correlation and Root Mean Squared Error',' Rajesh Kumar Chandrawat, Padmakar Pandey, Varun Joshi',' 285-300','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','56','2013-09-19 02:42:58','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1043,' A Green Technology for Control of Pollution and Recovery of Metal','Phytoextraction is an emerging and environment friendly green technology that uses plants to clean up the organic and inorganic pollutants. The technique was first adapted to co