e range 200 cm.-1 to 4000 cm.-1 have been interpreted to ascertain different functional groups. Atom and coordination sites in the organic ligands.','','I.R. Spectroscopy, Buckner funnel, Vacuum desiccators, Perkin Elmer-580 spectrophotometer, 4- Hydroxy 1- naphthylglyoxal solution',' Sushil Kumar and Divya Hans',' 389-398','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','62','2013-09-19 03:00:15','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1055,' Studies on Decolourization of Reactive Black 5 dye using Pseudomonas Aeruginosa','In the present study, P.Aeruginosa was used for decolorization study of Reactive Black 5 dye. The following operating parameters namely pH, inoculums concentration, temperature and initial concentration of dye solution are studied to evaluate its effects on % decolorization of reactive black 5 by P.Aeruginosa. These parameters are optimized based on the maximum percentage decolorization of dye. These optimized values are used to study the % decolorization of dyes in packed bed column for continuous treatment. In continuous mode, the maximum % decolorization of dye is investigated by varying the two parameters namely flow rate of dye solution and height of packed bed. The flow rate of dye solution and height of packed bed are optimized based on the maximum % decolorization. Also response surface methodology (RSM) was used to optimize the batch operation.','','-',' B.Manikandan, T.Kannadasan, K.Kannan, G.Sanjay Kumar',' 399-414','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','','','2013-09-19 03:01:13','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1056,' Studies on Decolourization of Reactive Black 5 dye using Pseudomonas Aeruginosa','In the present study, P.Aeruginosa was used for decolorization study of Reactive Black 5 dye. The following operating parameters namely pH, inoculums concentration, temperature and initial concentration of dye solution are studied to evaluate its effects on % dec