infinite. In the secondary shop, the defective units are continuously transferred from the primary shop with variable rates. The researcher considered three situations for dealing with defective units depending upon the coincidence of the time periods at two shops. Feasibility and applicability of the developed models has been illustrated with the help of numerical example.','','-',' Aditya Shastri, S. R. Singh, Shalley Gupta',' 11-30','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','63','2013-09-19 03:12:49','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1059,' Optimal ordering policy for decaying items with stock dependent demand under progressive payment scheme and fuzzy cost','In progressive payment scheme, a supplier suggests two different offers to increase the amount of purchasing. Firstly, if the order quantity is greater than or equal to a predetermined quantity, the buyer obtains a longer permissible delay in payments otherwise buyer gets a cash discount with a shorter permissible delay in payments. In this paper, we developed an economic order quantity inventory model with stock dependent demand in which the seller provides the buyer offers a permissible delay in payments. The effect of deterioration and delay in payment are discussed as well. We assumed that the holding cost and the purchasing cost as triangular fuzzy numbers.  The theoretical results reflected in this paper are also studied through numerical examples and sensitivity analysis.','','Economic order quantity, permissible delay, decaying items, shortages.',' Ruby Bhardwaj, D. Singh, A.P. Singh',' 31-42','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','63','2013-09-19 03:14:22','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1060,' Exact Solutions for Certain Nonlinear PDEs by Sine-Hyperbolic Function Method  ','In this Letter, Sine-hyperbolic function method is used to obtain exact travelling wave solutions of nonlinear partial differential equations. The method is used to obtain the exact solutions for two different types of nonlinear partial differential equations such as, modified equal width wave equation and modified regularized long wave equation, which are the important soliton equations. The results reveal that the implemented technique is very effective and convenient for solving nonlinear partial differential equations arising in mathematical physics.  ','','Soliton solution, Sine-hyperbolic function Method, Modified Equal Width Wave, Modified Regularized Long Wave Equation.  ',' Amit Tomar, Soshal  ','43-47    ','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','63','2014-04-16 10:53:20','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1061,' A  Strong Pairing-Free Identity Based Authentication Key Agreement Protocol Based on ECC','Deniable authentication is an important security requirement for secure communications. However, all well-known identity-based deniable authentication protocols are requiring of correct security proof which is enormously important for cryptographic protocol design. In this paper, we propose a superior identity based mutual authentication scheme for two parties in crypto-environment. Moreover, this paper present security analysis of the protocol which shows that the proposed protocol supports perfect secret mutual authentication such that parties can establish secure session.','','Elliptic Curve Cryptography, Pairing-free Identity based Cryptosystem, Mutual Authentication and Security',' Vinod Kumar',' 49-53','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','63','2013-09-19 03:16:16','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1062,' HCI  and  Designing for  Mobile Learning','The enhanced communications and connectivity afforded by digital technology enable a more immediate response to learning needs which in turn challenges the existing roles and competencies of instructional designers. You cannot just simply push traditional web content to a mobile device. One has to look at the affordances of the device and build to them.  The differences between computer-based learning and mobile learning is the base factor of the hardware, usage patterns and approaches for designing learning environments. Simple issues like limited screen space dictate the terms when designing for mobiles. Moreover, there are a plethora of technology options to choose from.','','-',' Sonymol Koshy, Hemlata Vasishtha',' 55-62','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','63','2013-09-19 03:17:21','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1063,' An integrated inventory model for deteriorating item with time dependent demand and permissible delay in payment','cloud computing is emerging as one of the most significant shifts in information technology where on demand services are required. Cloud computing use are reaching the point where computing functions as a utility has great potential and flexibility which we cant imagine right now. However with these advantages in future we are facing some serious threats to data and code residing on the service provider premises. In this paper we are going to analysis the security issues so far occurred and at last we add some conclusion and purpose some new threats to the cloud computing. General Terms: security, risk, vulnerability.','','Cloud computing, security, privacy, assets, threats',' Sarvpreet Kaur, D. Singh, A. P. Singh',' 425-436','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','38','2013-09-19 03:23:23','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1064,' ERP Involves the Seamless Integration in Educational Sector','ERP systems include several configurable modules that integrate core business activities into a single environment based on an integrated, shared database.  Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems have been recognized as the most important development in the corporate use of information technology in the 1990s (Davenport, 1998), promising seamless integration of all the information flows throughout a firm. This applies to ERP system applications, which are seen as key in supporting business processes in many organizations.  ERP involves the seamless integration of processes across functional areas such as finance, human resources, manufacturing and logistics.  They support improved workflow, standardization of business practices, and improved capabilities.     Implementation of enterprise resource planning (ERP) systems improves corporate performance.  But implementing an ERP system is a costly and time-consuming task and these costs are due mainly to the short supply of professionals with ERP skills. This paper discusses about the demand of ERP professionals in the industry, ERP education Scenario in Indian context requiring integration of Business Schools with industries. \r\nThis paper reveals a clear view of education ERP, as education industry is one of the prime industries in India. Its importance in commercial value is less appreciated but its contribution to nation building is well known. With the surprising growth of the education sector, education institutes are becoming complex organizations. This paper discloses the impact of Education ERP over education participants, i.e. how; they will be beneficial after having this solution in their Colleges/Universities.\r\n','','ERP, EERP.ASP and HRM',' Ashok Kumar, Vinit Kumar Sharma, Padmveer Malik',' 437-448','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','38','2013-09-19 03:24:45','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1065,' Critical Success Factors in ERP Implementation in India','ERP is one the latest technologies that many organizations have undertaken. Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems are software packages composed of several modules, such as human resources, sales, finance and production, providing cross-organizational integration of transaction-based data management throughout imbedded business processes support. These software packages can be customized up to a certain limit to the specific needs of each organization. ERP was characterized as the most important development in the corporate use of technology in the 1990s. Unfortunately, many ERP projects have not been effective enough and hence have been unable to achieve all the results envisaged. As the cost of an ERP implementation project is very high, it is critical for an organization to make the project a success and start obtaining benefits out of it as fast as possible. Enterprise resource planning (ERP) systems are highly complex information systems. The implementation of these systems is a difficult and high cost proposition that places tremendous demands on corporate time and resources. Many ERP implementations have been classified as failures because they did not achieve predetermined corporate goals.','','ERP, Merits, Demerits, Success factors',' Ashok Kumar, Padmveer Malik',' 449-458','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','38','2013-09-19 03:25:47','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1066,' A Production Model with Variable Holding Cost, Backlogging and Inflation','In this paper, we develop a production model for an item with time dependent demand rate and deterioration in an inflationary environment. In this model, production rate is greater than the demand rate. Backlogging rate is also taken as time dependent. Finally, numerical examples are found in both crisp and fuzzy sense. Sensitivity analysis is also shown.','','Production model, variable holding cost, shortages, inflation',' Ruby Bhardwaj, D. Singh, A.P. Singh',' 459-468','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','24','38','2013-09-19 03:26:56','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1067,' A Model for Deteriorating Items with Time Dependent Demand and Deterioration with Inflation and Shortages','This article contains production inventory models for deteriorating items with time dependent demand. The finite production rate is proportional to the demand rate and the deterioration is time proportional. We have investigated inventory-production system where the deteriorating items follow two parameters Weibull deterioration. The objective of the model is to develop an optimal policy that minimizes the total average cost. Numerical examples are used to illustrate the two developed models. Sensitivity analysis of the optimal solution with respect to major parameters is carried out.','','Production model, weibull distribution, shortages, inflation',' D. Singh, Ruby Bhardwaj, A.P. Singh',' 377-390','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','15','20','2013-09-19 03:30:55','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1068,' An Order Quantity Model with Time Dependent Rates under Shortages and Inflation','In this chapter, we have proposed an economic order quantity model for deteriorating items having time dependent demand (whose demand varies with the time) under the effect of inflation. Deterioration rate is taken as weibull distribution. Shortages are allowed and partially backlogged. In most of the earlier inventory models, effect of inflation has been ignored, which plays a very important role in the inventory model. Inflation is also considered.  The total cost per time unit is minimized. A numerical example is given to illustrate the model. Sensitivity analysis is carried out to study the changes in the decision variables and total cost of an inventory system.','','Order model, weibull distribution, shortages, inflation',' Ruby Bhardwaj, D. Singh, A.P. Singh',' 295-706','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','3','10','2013-09-19 03:32:51'