, 190&ndash;198.</div>\r\n','Reliability, Flexibility, m-measure, Genetic Algorithm   ','1 Kamlesh A Patel and 2 Hardik N Soni   ','201-220      ','YES','03 IJICM(SI).pdf','International Journal of Inventory Control and Management','41','68','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',5,'kapatel007@yahoo.in','1 Shri U. P. Arts & Smt. M. G. Panchal Science & Shri V. L. Shah Commerce College, Mathematics Depar',' https://doi.org/10.58517/IJICM.2012.2203 ','pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1086,'Vendor-Buyer Deteriorating Inventory Model When Two-Level Trade Credit Policy Is Offered During Recession     ','<p>\r\n	In this paper, an integrated inventory model for deteriorating items is analyzed when buyer&rsquo;s demand decreases with time and price. The supply chain considers the two-level trade credit policy in the vendor-buyer and buyer-customer setup. A simple algorithm is outlined for the joint models to determine the buyer&rsquo;s optimal pricing and production/ordering strategy. The total profit of the chain increases but that of buyer decreases. To compensate the buyer&rsquo;s loss due to the cooperative relationship, a negotiation factor is introduced to distribute the profit increase to the vendor and buyer. A numerical example and sensitivity analysis are provided to illustrate the developed model. The result depicts that the total profit of the supply chain increases, although a price discount is offered to the buyer.</p>\r\n','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Abad, P. L. and Jaggi, C. K., 2003. A joint approach for setting unit price and the length of the credit period for seller when end demand is price sensitive. International Journal of Production Economics, 83, 115-122.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Aggarwal, S. P. and Jaggi, C. K., 1995. Ordering policies of deteriorated items under permissible delay in payments. Journal of the Operational Research Society, 46, 658-662.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Banerjee, A., 1986. A joint economic lot-size model for purchaser and vendor. Decision sciences, 17, 292-31