o do work. It is measured that total amount of work that the body can do. Energy is the key input to drive and improve the life cycle. Primarily it is the gift of nature to the mankind in various forms. The consumption of energy is directly proportional to the progress of mankind. With ever growing population, improvement in living standard of humanity, industrialization of developing countries, the global demand for energy is expected to increase rather significantly in the near future. The primary source of energy is fossil fuel, however the finiteness of fossil fuel reserves and large scale environmental degradation caused by their widespread use, particularly global warming, urban and pollution and acid rain, strongly suggests that harnessing of non-conventional, renewable and environmental friendly energy resources is vital for steering the global energy supplies towards sustainable path. Energy is the primary and most universal measure of all kinds work by human beings and nature. Every thing what happens the world is the expression of flow of energy in one of its forms. Convention energy resources includes fossil fuel energy, hydraulic energy and nuclear energy, while non-conventional energy resources are being produced continuously in nature and are in exhaustible are called renewable sources of energy (or)non-conventional energy. Some of these sources are: wind energy, tidal energy, solar energy ctc.','','Conventional, Non-conventional energy, fossil fuel, application',' Anchla Gupta,  A. P. Singh',' 29-34','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2013-10-18 09:07:53','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1097,' Non-Conventional Energy Resources','Energy is the key input to drive and improve the life cycle. Primarily, it is the gift of the nature to the mankind in various forms. The consumption of the energy is directly proportional to the progress of the mankind. With ever growing population, improvement in the4 living standard of the humanity, in detribalization of the developing countries, the global demand for energy is expected to increase rather significantly in the near future. The primary source of energy is fossil fuel, however the finiteness of fossil fuel reserves and large scale environmental degradation caused by their widespread use, particularly global warming, urban air pollution and acid rain, strongly suggests that harnessing of non-conventional, renewable and environment friendly energy recourses is vital for steering the global energy supplies towards a sustainable path.','','Fossil fuel, Application',' Sapna Sharma,  A. P. Singh','35-38','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2013-10-18 09:08:25','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1098,' Dielectric Theory and Molecular Orientation in Liquid Crystal Mixtures','This paper reviews the present status and art of liquid crystals Liquid crystals, during the last three decades, have emerged as one of the most technologically important class of materials. We have observed liquid crystal materials are ordered fluids & soft materials. These materials have several common characteristics like molecular structure, rigidness of the long polarizable substituent. Weak external perturbations, such as electric or magnetic fields, thermal optical and acoustical energy change many of their physical properties like birefringence, optical activity, viscosity, thermal and electrical conductivity etc. the sharp change in colors of cholestric liquid crystals with small change in temperature have resulted in a number of temp. ','','technologically, characteristics, perturbations',' Vivek Chand Mishra  Jitendra Kumar Kushwaha',' 39-44','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2013-10-18 09:09:03','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1099,' Transforming Business: Integrating ERP with E-Business ','All businesses are focusing more on productivity, efficiency and cost saving nowadays and to materialize these factors they are emphasizing on technology, innovation, expansion of existing market and to generate new business areas. Organization today can communicate with customers, suppliers and sellers at e speed, hence it is must for an organization to reach outside the boundaries throughout the value chain system. Internal process can be integrated using ERP and it is expected that an ERP system can facilitate an E-business effort of an organization. By integrating ERP with E-business, a new extended ERP system emerges that create business which is more lively, more focused and highly competitive than traditionally structured business. Integration of ERP with E-business pushes activities within a business to the network edge and helps in expanding their market values, relationship with their customers and suppliers. As more and more companies realize that they need to open themselves to their customers and suppliers over the internet, integration with ERP system becomes a critical issue. This paper highlights the concepts of ERP and E-business and elaborates perspective of integrating ERP with E-business.','','ERP, E-Business',' Harsh Arora  ',' 45-51','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2013-11-15 10:07:23','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1100,' Use and Awareness of E-Resourses in Modern Academic Libraries  ','At present, the World Wide Web is the largest available repository of information with the largest number of users searching for information. Advances in computer applications during the past few decades have brought radical changes in the way information is gathered, stored, organized, accessed, retrieved and consumed. Todays users have their information needs met via a number of options. They need not come physically to the library to use print formats but can stay at home or the office and access online library resources and services via networks or authentication methods at anytime. E-resources can be used for efficient retrieval and meeting information needs. This is very important for academic libraries since most of them call for more and more research work. The goal of any academic libraries is to meet the teaching, research and other information needs of the user. The proliferation of the literature on all the subjects, price of journals hike in currency conversion rate and the budget crunch made the libraries depend upon each other. This leads to library co-operation, resource sharing and networks etc.  The advent of E-publishing has brought a revolution in journal publication, subscription and access delivery mechanism. This paper describes various facets in collection development an E- resource in the engineering college libraries. ','','E-resources, E-Publishing, Users, Modern libraries, Challenges ','  Ruchi Jain  ',' 53-59    ','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2013-11-15 10:08:00','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1101,'Issues and Challenges : Relation to Quality and Excellence ','In achieving the goals and objectives of the 12th  FYP (Five Year Plan) in higher education, there have been certain constraints and opportunities which need to be identified so that strategies could be evolved not only for addressing them but also to leverage the opportunities. Some of the constraints have a bearing on the expectations of the education sector from other Ministries and the States, including the private sector.','','Quality Of Education , Excellence, Curricular Reforms ','Subhash Singh	 ',' 61-66','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2013-11-15 10:08:57','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1102,' Role of Training & Library Marketing for User Education in Computing Environment  ','I believe that most librarians accept that they not only have a responsibility to provide quality information services but also to educate their library users with respect to the effective use of those library services and products. Training and teaching in libraries is carried out in the form of user training. I provide in my presentation arguments in support of the viewpoint that teaching and training in library context could be successfully used as a means or tool for Marketing.   ','','Introduction, Objectives of staff training & users training,Aspects library staff need  to be trained , Assistance & training for all library users,Conclusion,References   ','Satyaprakash Singh, Madhuri Gangal   ',' 67-74      ','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2014-01-03 04:48:10','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1103,' Price and Stock Dependent Inventory Model with Inflation and Time Value of Money','It is a common tendency of the demand that it is to decrease with the price but increase with displayed items. In the present study, an Economic Order Quantity inventory mathematical model is developed for deteriorating items having price and stock dependent demand. The deterioration rate is assumed to be weibull distribution and time value of money with inflation is also taken into consideration. Shortages are also allowed and partially backlogged. Finally, a numerical example is provided to illustrate the model. \r\n\r\n','','deterioration, partially backlogged shortage, price, and stock dependent demand.','Rekha Rani Chaudhary and Anuradha','323-332','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','34','51','2013-10-24 17:29:45','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1104,' An Inventory Model with Volume Flexible Process Under Inflation and Shortages','In the present paper, we assume a variable production rate of the manufacturing machine.  The demand rate in this model is assumed to be linearly time varying. The assumption is quite appropriate from a realistic point of view because the demand for some items such as electronic goods, fashionable clothes, luxury goods, etc. increases steadily after consumer acceptance, while the demand for the obsolete items decreases steadily. It is assumed that a constant fraction of the on-hand inventory deteriorates per unit time. The optimal number of cycles that minimizes the average system cost over a finite time horizon is determined. The results are illustrated with numerical examples.','','-',' Jitendra Kumar, S. R. Singh',' 333-340','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','34','51','2013-10-24 17:31:01','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1105,' An EOQ Model with Linear Demand Rate and Permissible Delay in Payment','In most of the EOQ models, demand is considered as constant, while in most of the practical situations demand changes with time. In the present study, an inventory model has been framed to study the items whose demand increases with respect to time and deterioration rate is assumed to be a constant. The effect of permissible delay permitted by the supplier is also incorporated in this study.  Mathematical models have been derived under two different situations, i.e. case I & case II. The main purpose of this paper is to investigate the optimal (minimum) total costs for both cases (i.e. case I and II). Finally, numerical examples, the graphical representation, and sensitivity analysis are provided to illustrate the model.','','Constant deterioration rate, delay in payment, inventory model and linear demand rate. ','Rekha Rani Chaudhary and Anuradha',' 485-494','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','23','35','2013-10-24 17:34:28','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1106,' Production Inventory Policy with Time and Stock Dependent Demand Rate','In practical circumstances, it is needless to say that a constant demand rate does not identify with any kind of inventory. A demand rate depending upon a single factor is, no doubt, more practical than the constant rate, but it has its own shortcomings. In this paper we have attempted to develop a deteriorating production inventory model with a very realistic and practical demand rate which depends upon both the stock level available and time. This whole setup is very close to the reality that is observed in the market.','','Time dependent demand; Stock dependent demand; Deterioration.',' Jitendra Kumar, S. R. Singh ',' 495-503','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','23','35','2013-10-24 17:35:35','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1107,' Empowering women through entrepreneurship','Entrepreneurship refers to the act of setting up a new business or reviving an existing business so as to take advantages from new opportunities. Women are one particularly understudied group of entrepreneurs. Women entrepreneurship is considered an important tool in enabling women empowerment. Women entrepreneurs not only create new jobs for themselves and others but also provide society with different solutions to management, organization and business problems as well as to the exploitation of entrepreneurial opportunities. The present study is designed to assess women entrepreneurs, focusing on empowering women entrepreneurship in the developing world.  The first part of the paper deals with the ideas why to boost the women entrepreneurship, scope for women entrepreneurship and the major factors affecting the performance of women entrepreneurs. The second part deals with challenges of women to connect enterprising women with the means to grow their businesses. It is hoped that women entrepreneurship has a bright future. Developing entrepreneurship among women will be the right approach for empowerment of women. ','','Entrepreneurship, Empower, Women',' Kamana Tripathi','777-782','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','30','37','2013-10-28 09:20:14','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1110,' Study of positive and negative emotions among adolescents','Emotion is perceived as one of the important aspect of well-being in everyone life. This study examined, the relationship between positive and negative emotion/affect among 240 male and female adolescents between the age group of 15 to 17 years residing in Gorakhpur city. These adolescents were subjected to measures of emotional intensity and affect. The result revealed that adolescents belonging to different categories differed significantly on dimensions of emotion (positive & negative) as well as affect (Positive & negative). The implications of the findings are discussed.','','Key words - emotion intensity, affect, adolescents',' Krishna Sharma, P.S.N. Tiwari','984-991','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','37','2013-10-30 06:09:42','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1111,' Ecological change and happiness among villagers of eastern Uttar Pradesh','The present research has examined ecological change and happiness among villagers in a sample of 240 subjects from a set of villages of eastern U.P. having different levels of ecological change (high & low). All the subjects were required to respond in their own way on two questions related to happy life. The responses were content analyzed. The results of content analysis of happy life projections revealed a quite similar pattern among villagers. Villagers were more concerned with personal and agriculture needs. Social, psychological and community needs were not frequently emphasized. The implication of the present findings has been discussed.','','happiness, needs, villagers, ecological change.','A.B. Singh, P.S.N. Tiwari',' 992-1000','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','37','2013-10-30 06:11:31','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1112,' test','-','','-','-',' 1001-1014','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','37','2013-10-30 06:12:05','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1113,' Production policy for inventory system with ramp type demand with shortages under inflation','In this paper, we bring in ramp type demand rate with its variable part being any positive function of time. We consider the concept of amelioration/deterioration items with shortages which are partially backlogged where backlogging rate is decreasing function of waiting time with the application of inflation and time value of money. ','','Ramp type demand, deterioration, time value of money',' Abhinav Goel, R. K. Pandey','1015-1031','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','25','37','2013-10-30 06:14:14','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1114,' A Stochastic Model to Determine the Expected Time to Seroconversion of HIV Infected Due to Antigenic Diversity or Virulence ','In HIV infection and its progression to AIDS, the expected time\r\nto seroconversion is an important aspect. This is a vital issue\r\nbecause antiretroviral therapy (ART) can be suitably introduced\r\nso that the time to seroconversion can be prolonged. The\r\nantigenic diversity threshold and the expected time to cross the\r\nsame due to the increase in antigenic diversity in successive\r\ncontacts has been discussed by using Stochastic models by\r\nseveral authors. In this paper the concept of virulence is also\r\ntaken into consideration. There is contribution to virulence also\r\ndue to successive contacts. The expected time to seroconversion\r\nby taking into consideration both antigenic diversity threshold\r\nand virulence threshold is discussed, and the expected time to\r\nconversation is obtained. Numerical illustration is also\r\nprovided. ','','Seroconversion, Antiretroviral Therapy, Antigenic\r\nDiversity Threshold, Virulence Threshold ','  U. Niyamathulla, R. Elangovan and R. Sathiyamoorthi ',' 311-320','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','32','48','2013-11-21 16:22:10','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1115,' Analysis of an Unsteady MHD Convective Heat and Mass Transfer Flow of a Micropolar Fluid Over a Semi Vertical Pereable Plate Embedded in a Porous Medium With Effect of Chemical Reaction and Suction','Analytical solutions for heat and mass transfer by laminar flow of a Micropolar fluid, electrically conducting and heat generation fluid on a continuously vertical permeable surface in the presence of a first-order homogeneous chemical reaction and the mass flux are reported. The plate is assumed to move with a constant velocity in the direction of fluid flow. A uniform magnetic field acts perpendicular to the porous surface, which absorbs the fluid with a suction velocity varying with time. The dimensionless governing equations for this investigation are solved analytically using two-term harmonic and non-harmonic func1tions. Graphical results for velocity, temperature and concentration profiles of both phases based on the analytical solutions are presented and discussed.','','Micropolar fluid, MHD convection, Porous medium.',' Rajiv Dwivedi and B.B. Singh','109-124','NO','','International Journal of Stability and Fluid Mechanics','36','55','2013-11-11 06:58:42','E',6,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1116,' Survey of Indian-English Novel','Development of Indian-English literature needs being discussed before the survey of Indian-English novel. Though English is not our mother tongue, yet our creative writers have got command over English writing and have secured a distinguished position among the renowned writers of English literature. Indian-English literature as critics say, began as an interesting by-product of an eventful encounter in the late eighteenth century between a vigorous and enterprising Britain and a stagnant as well as chaotic India.','','Indian-English, distinguished',' Neha Jain','459-462','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2013-11-15 10:03:41','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1117,' Growth and development of Feminism','As almost half of the population is comprised of woman who is no longer constrained within the four walls of her house. Education, new technologies, scientific innovations, industrialization, etc. are inviting woman to come forward, and in this attempt, feminism helped a lot to change the position of women in this male-dominated society.','','Education, feminism, society',' Neha Jain','75-78','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2013-11-15 10:11:17','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1118,' The Lasso Method for Variable Selection in the Cox Model Using Lung Cancer and Liver Data','Variable selection is an important topic in linear regression analysis especially in high-dimensional medical data sets, and has challenged many contemporary statistical problems from many frontiers of scientific disciplines. Over the past few years, many techniques have been proposed for variable selection in high-dimensional medical data sets. A field, in which such methods are applicable, is survival analysis. The Least Absolute Shrinkage and Selection Operator (LASSO) proposed by Tibshirani is a popular technique for model selection and estimation in linear regression model. Cox proportional hazard model is perhaps the most widely used statistical model in such a context. In this paper the LASSO method for Variable Selection in the Cox model using Lung Cancer and Liver data has been discussed. Finally an example of statistical analysis is included.','','-','R. Elangovan and A. Lokeshmaran','321-331','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','32','48','2013-11-21 16:24:01','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1119,' Determination of Expected Time to Recruitment in a Three Grade Organization .','In some organizations, the staff or personnel are in different divisions called grades. The transfer of personnel from one grade to other grade mutually is possible. It is likely that the wastage or depletion of  staff is possible from each of the grades. As and when the total or cumulative depletion on successive occasions crosses a level called the threshold level then recruitment becomes necessary.  Since, transfer is possible from one grade to the other; the depletion can be permitted up to the maximum of the individual thresholds. Using the Shock model and cumulative damage process, the expected time to recruitment in a three grade organization can be obtained. It provides the optimal solution because; it takes into consideration the cost of frequent recruitments, the cost of shortage of manpower. Any other policy adopted may not be cost effective.','','Depletion of Manpower, Optimal solution, Threshold level, Shock model approach, Wastages.','R. Arulpavai, R. Elangovan','333-354','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','32','48','2013-11-21 16:25:33','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1120,' Determination of Expected Time to Recruitment when the Reakdown Threshold has Five Components','In manpower planning there are different stages such as recruitment, training, promotion, demotion, resignations, death, etc., which in other words are called the attritions.  Frequent recruitment is not advisable due to the cost of the same.  Hence recruitment is postponed till a point called the breakdown point of total depletion beyond which the normal activities cannot be continued due to manpower attrition.  This level of allowable manpower depletion is called the threshold.  In this paper under the assumption that the threshold is the total of five individual components such as the natural level of attritions, attrition due to transfer of personal from other organizations, attrition due to extra time work of existing workers, frequent breaks of existing workers and level of attrition due to demotion, the expected time to breakdown in other words to time to recruitment and its variance is derived using the shock model approach.  Numerical illustration is also provided.','','Attrition, Breakdown Threshold, Manpower depletion, Recruitment, Shock Model Approach.',' R. Elangovan and T. Ramani ','31-46','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','39','61','2013-11-21 16:35:40','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1121,' A Stochastic Model in the Study of HIV/Aids Epidemic and its Progression','Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) infection, which can cause Acquired Immunodeficiency Syndrome (AIDS), has shown a high degree of prevalence in populations all over the world. Treatment of human immunodeficiency virus, HIV infection is an important challenge of todays research, since currently there is no definitive cure. In order to describe the dynamics of the disease, numerous mathematical models of varying details have been proposed in the open literature to capture different aspects of disease progression. The Stochastic nature of early HIV infection is described in a series of models, each of which captures aspects of the HIV during the early stages of infection. Stochastic models for the HIV epidemic to characterize the HIV infection and seroconversion has also been discussed in the recent literature. The antigenic diversity threshold is an important event in the sense that it gives the most likely time for the development of AIDS condition in an infected person. A Stochastic model is developed to know the HIV/AIDS epidemic and its progression using the concept of Antigenic Diversity Threshold (ADT) suggested by Nowak and May (1991) and Stilianakis (1994). The mean time to cross the ADT and its variance is derived in this paper. Numerical illustrations are also provided to validate the model.','','Acquired Immunodeficiency Syndrome, Antigenic Diversity Threshold, Human    Immunodeficiency Virus, Immune System, Seroconversion.','R. Elangovan and R. Ramajayam',' 415-422','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','62','2013-11-21 17:12:18','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1122,'Stochastic Model to Determine the Optimal Manpower Reserve at Fivenodes in Series','In any nation, the economic welfare of the citizens is as a result of proper perspective planning by the government. Needless say that the social prosperity and social life also depend upon the careful planning by the government in administration. Scientific methods of approach to economic problems and evolving suitable economic policies are important aspects of efficient administration. The economic welfare of a country depends to a large extent on the availability of natural resources, industrial production and proper exploitation of the available resources. It is in this context manpower is needed and quit often there may be an imbalance between the manpower requirements and the supply of the same. There are many industries and organizations where the skilled personnel are to be recruited and they must be given prior training before employment. In the area of Software and Information Technology the training and induction of the right type of personnel is a pressing problem. In this paper, we consider the optimal solution for the manpower to be kept as reserve inventory at five different nodes in series. This is based on the inventory model for finding the optimal size of reserve inventory at five successive stations in series. The model developed in this paper provides a tool for assessing the manpower profile and predicting future manpower development on industry wide basis.','','Inventory Model, Manpower planning, Optimal Solution. ','R. Elangovan and T. Ramani','63-82','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','63','2013-11-21 17:46:38','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1123,'Hematological Study of Fish Channa Punctatus Treated with Detergent','One such important class of pollutants which are part and parcel of such effluents as just mentioned, are the heavy metals. These have been placed at the top of priority list as they are persistent, water soluble, non-degradable vigorous oxidizing agents and strongly bind to many biochemical units. They produce cumulative toxicity in small doses over long periods of time and acute toxicity in higher doses. Living organisms are yet to develop mechanisms to get rid of non-essential metals having non biological role and hence tend to accumulate in the body and cause toxicity. This too depends upon a number of physio-chemical factors, biological half-life and also on the physiological state of the target organism.','','non-degradable, toxicity, organisms','Sonika Lalwani',' 79-84','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2013-12-26 10:46:42','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1124,' Jherh bafnjk xka/kh vkSj 1971 dk vke pquko','-','','-','f\'ko dkUr ;kno ] eukst dqekj ',' 85-88','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2013-12-26 10:48:27','H',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1125,'cjsyh tuin ds gkbZLdwy Lrj ds fo|kfFkZ;ksa dh vius fo|ky; ds fr vfHko`fRk dk v/;;u ','Hkkjr esa gh ugha oju lEiw.kZ fo\'o Hkj esa ek/;fed f\'k{kk ,d pkSjkgs ij [kM+h gSA loZtuh; igqap ds fy, izkFkfedrk;sa fu/kkZfjr djuk vkSj ek/;fed f\'k{kk dh izR;sd voLFkk esa lQyrk lqfuf\'pr djuk vc lHkh fodkl\'khy ns\'kksa ds ftuesa Hkkjr Hkh \'kkfey gSA uhfr fuekZrkvksa dk ,d izeq[k ljksdkj gS ek/;fed f\'k{kk dk lkoZtuhdj.k ,d egRoiw.kZ ljdkjh uhfr gS] ftldk ekxZn\'kZu ljdkj dh jktuSfrd dk;Zlwph ls gksrk gSA blfy, ek