s having linear time dependent demand under the effect of inflation. Deterioration rate is taken as Weibull distribution. Shortages are allowed and partially backlogged. Inflation is also considered.  The total cost per time unit is minimized. A numerical example is given to illustrate the model. Sensitivity analysis is carried out to study the changes in the decision variables and total cost of an inventory system.','','Deterioration, time dependent demand, inflation, partially backlogged ',' Vineet Kumar, S.R. Singh',' 445-456','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','69','2014-02-09 15:33:11','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1152,' Synthesis, Characterization and Application of Antimony(III) Iodosilicate a Cation Exchanger','The present work deals with the synthesis and ion exchange properties of antimony(III) iodosilicate. The material has been synthesized. The synthesized exchanger is  characterized on the basis of chemical stability, thermal stability, TGA, X-RD and FTIR studies. The mixtures analyzed are Pb++-cd++, Pb++-Mn++, Pb++-Ni++ and Pb++-Mg++. Their binary separations have been achieved on antimony(III) iodosilicate columns. Removal of toxic metal ions such as Pb++, Cd++ from an aqueous solution were determined by column method.','','Antimony(III) iodosilicate, Inorganicionexchanger, Ionexchangecapacity, Thermal stability, Chemical stability',' Subhash Chand,Seema, Rekha Rani,Vijayata, Brajsh Pal',' 457-466','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','69','2014-02-09 15:36:30','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1153,' Cadmium(II) Selective A New Inorganic Cation Exchanger Based on Antimony(III)','Ten different samples of a new cation exchanger antimony(III)  iodostannate were synthesized. One of the samples was selected on the basis of ion exchange capacity as determined by column method. The selected sample was synthesized again in bulk for detailed study. Ion exchange capacity of this synthesized material for Na+ was found to be 1.66 meq/g of the dry exchanger as obtained by column method. The characterization of the material was done by different studies. The studies include pH titration, chemical stability, thermal stability, IR, XRD and TGA. Distribution studies of the exchanger were also carried out for different metal ions which are Ca2+, Mg2+, Zn2+, Cu2+, Mn2+, Co2+, Ni2+, Pb2+, Bi3+ and Cd2+.','','Cation exchanger, Ion exchange capacity, pH titration, Thermal stability, Chemical stability, Distribution studies.','Subhash Chand, Teena, Manju',' 467-478','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','69','2014-02-09 15:51:57','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1154,' Eventually Stabilization of Impulsive Functional Differential Equations by Using Piecewisw Continuous Lyapunov Functions','In this paper, by using piecewise continuous functions, criteria of eventual stability for system of impulsive functional differential equations is investigated. The sufficient conditions that are obtained significantly depend on the moment of impulses. An example is provided to illustrate the effectiveness and the advantages of the results.','','Impulsive functional differential equations, Eventual stability, Lyapunov function',' Dilbaj Singh,Sanjay Kumar Srivastava',' 479-486','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','69','2014-02-09 15:56:40','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1155,' Chemistry, Safety Profile, Pharmacokinetics and Analysis of Haloperidol in Water and Wastewater Samples','Haloperidol is used very frequently for the treatment in various diseases in India. It is life saving catalyst but its unnecessary administration into human body is not desirable and lead to certain side effects and also alter the biological activities of the body. Some pharmaceutical industries and hospitals are releasing a variety of drugs including Haloperidol 