ubscription',NULL),(1158,' Empowering Women through Entrepreneurship','Entrepreneurship refers to the act of setting up a new business or reviving an existing business so as to take advantages from new opportunities. Women are one particularly understudied group of entrepreneurs. Women entrepreneurship is considered an important tool in enabling women empowerment. Women entrepreneurs not only create new jobs for themselves and others but also provide society with different solutions to management, organization and business problems as well as to the exploitation of entrepreneurial opportunities. The present study is designed to assess women entrepreneurs, focusing on empowering women entrepreneurship in the developing world.  The first part of the paper deals with the ideas why to boost the women entrepreneurship, scope for women entrepreneurship and the major factors affecting the performance of women entrepreneurs. The second part deals with challenges of women to connect enterprising women with the means to grow their businesses. It is hoped that women entrepreneurship has a bright future. Developing entrepreneurship among women will be the right approach for empowerment of women. ','','Entrepreneurship, Empower, Women','Kamana Tripathi',' 515-520','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','69','2014-02-09 16:18:14','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1159,' A Comparative Study of Systematic Risk (Inflation) of Selected Infrastructure Mutual Fund Schemes','The study of systematic risk which cannot be diversified has been important for investors, while taking an investment decisions. the present study  will give an analytical outlook to the retail investor as how to invest in market and would create an easy understanding to them which regard to market bulls and bears fluctuations and more importantly to understand The concepts and methods to calculate the beta coefficient, systematic risks efficiently before investing. Th