ied Sciences','35','69','2014-02-16 01:41:26','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1165,' The Combined Studies of Iron(III) and Manganese (II) Complexes of A Tridentate 1, 5-bis (4-Methyl, Benzimidazol-2-yl)-3-Thiapentane (BMBES) Ligand ','The mononuclear iron(III) & Manganese(II)  complexes with stoichiometry (Fe(BMBES)X3].nH2O & [Mn(BMBES)X2] have been synthesized and characterized utilizing a tridentate ligand. 1, 5-bis(4-methyl,benzimidazol-2-yl)-3-thiapentane (BMBES) with anionic ligand like Cl-, NO3-, H3O-. Mssbauer data for Fe(III) complexes indicate that the isomer shift values lie in the range typically observed for high spin Fe(III) complexes. While slightly large quadrapole splitting parameter indicate a rhombically distorted Fe(III) centre. Cyclic voltammetric  studies for Fe(III) complex indicate that binding  of HCOO- anion stabilize the Fe(III) centre whereas NO3- destabilized it. The EPR spectroscopy shows a strong single centered at   for Mn(II) complexes prove that non-cubic crystalline electric field are weak. Zero field splitting parameter   has also been calculated.','','Iron and Manganese','Meghraj Singh and Sharad Kumar',' 569-580','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','69','2014-02-16 01:44:20','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1166,' Mathematical Model with time dependent demand and shortages','A mathematical model for decaying items with time dependent demand has been developed. Shortages are permitted with partial backlogging. The backlogging rate is waiting time for the next replenishment. ','','time dependent demand, Shortages','Krishna Chandra, Minakshi ',' 587-594','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','69','2014-02-16 01:53:41','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1167,' Kinetic and Mechanistic Study of Oxidation of Primary Amines with Mn (III) in Acidic Medium','The results of the kinetics of oxidation of aliphatic amines (AA), such as methyl, ethyl, n propyl, iso propyl, n butyl, isobutyl, sec butyl, dimethyl and trimethyl amines by manganese (III) sulphate in aqueous sulphuric acid medium have been presented and discussed. The reaction shows first order dependence on [Mn (III)] and [AA]. Increase in [HSO4]_ and [H+] have little accelerating effect on the rate of oxidation. The inhibitory effect of [Mn(II)], on the reaction rate  has been found to be negligible. The Mn (III) amine redox reaction indicated that one mole of amine consumes two moles of Mn(III) sulphate for the first stage oxidation product. The oxidation reactions induced vinyl polymerization of acrylamide indicating the formation of free radical intermediates during the course of reaction. Main products of the oxidation reaction of primary amines were ammonia and corresponding aldehyde or ketone, which identified by their characteristic spot tests. Assuming Mn(HSO4)+2 ion as probable reactive species and most probable reaction mechanism, proposed for these oxidation reactions.','','n-Butyl amine, Isobutyl amine, Sec butyl amine, Dimethyl amine, Trimethyl amine','Munesh Kumar,Dinesh Chandra Agarwal,Deepali Rani',' 595-610','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','35','69','2014-02-16 02:10:59','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1168,' Growth and Characterization of ZnO based Nanowires','In this present work we explored the growth of ZnO nanowires with defined length and diameters, in a patterned arrangement, and at a defined position of the substrate by utilizing the bottom-up approach in order to understand their material properties. We have carried out electrodeposition of ZnO in to PCT membranes at two different concentrations. Structural characterization of the deposited ZnO, nanopillars, nanobrushes and nanoclusters was carried out using scanning electron microscopy (SEM) for different concentrations and different bath temperatures.','','ZnO, nanowires, electrodepositio