ity function.  Our  dissertation  proposal  explores  the   two  factor  authentication technique  and  implementation  issues  which  can  be  used  for  the   two  factor authentication technique. We implement Two-factor authentication method in two main phases. In the first  phase,   the  authenticator  gets  a  request  generated  by  the  application  to authenticate a specified user. When the request is received, it generates a one-time password and sends it through a SMS to a GSM cell phone registered for that specified user.','','Authentication, Password',' Inderpal Singh Oberoi','163-166','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','58','2014-02-22 09:58:20','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1181,' Role of Teacher Community in Developing Social Awareness towards Population Control and Its Relation with Oveal National Progress','Malthus, the famous economist, who in his `Theory of Population during the last century, explained that population was increasing in geometric progression whereas production increased in arithmatic progression He gave a signal warning that the rate of growth of population is high and with all our technical resources at our command, the agriculture and industrial production cannot keep pace with the population growth. His prophecy has come true. We find at present that production growth. The developing nations of the world are bent upon crubing the birth rate through national family planning programmes. The implementation of the small family norms in the minds of the people who have already some fixed traditional values is not an easy task.','','-','Sushil Kumar','209-213','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','59','2014-02-22 10:00:18','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1182,' MkW0 ,-ih-ts- vCnqy dyke ds f\'k{kk lEcU/kh fopkjksa dk v/;;u','-','','-','dqlqeyrk  fnyhi dqekj feJ ','215-220','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','37','59','2014-02-22 10:01:26','H',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1183,' A Pairing-Free Identity Based Authentication Protocol Using by ECC in Cloud Computing','In this paper, I present a pairing-free identity based authentication protocol using by ECC in cloud computing. In proposed protocol, user and server established a session key and can communicate securely over the public network. Detailed security analyses have been made to authenticate the competence of the protocol. Further, the protocol has the confrontation to probable attacks in cloud computing.','','Cloud Computing, Elliptic Curve Cryptography, Pairing-free Identity based Cryptosystem, Authentication and Security','Vinod Kumar',' 126-131','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','70','2014-02-23 05:13:23','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1184,' An Inventory Model under the effect of Learning and Inflation   ','In this paper we have developed an inventory model for deteriorating items with time dependent demand. Production rate is demand dependent. Effect of learning and efficiency of an organization both are correlated to each other. The objective is to find optimal values of production and minimizing the total relevant cost over the planning horizon. At the end of this paper a numerical illustration is given.  ','','EPQ, Learning, inflation, deterioration  ','  Sandeep Kumar and Sandeep Kumar Mittal  ',' 133-141    ','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','70','2014-02-23 14:11:07','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1185,' An Integrated Model for Stock Dependent Demand with Variable Holding Cost and Shortages','An inventory model for decaying items with time & stock dependent demand rate has been developed. The effect of inflation has been taken into account. In real life situation, the storage cost varies with time. Shortages are allowed in inventory with partial backlogging. Backlogging rate is waiting time for the next replenishment. We provided the solution procedure for finding the total cost. Further we used a numerical example to illustrate the model and sensitivity analysis. ','','Integrated Model,Stock Dependent Demand  ','  Ajeet Singh and Sandeep Kumar Mittal',' 143-152','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','70','2014-02-23 14:22:27','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1186,' An Order Model for Deteriorating Products with Time Dependent Demand  ','In this paper an inventory model with ramp type demand rate is developed. The deterioration of products is considered as a function of time. Shortages are partially backordered with a time varying backordering rate. The objective of this study is to minimize the total cost of the system. Finally, numerical example is provided to illustrate the theory of the proposed model and sensitivity analysis is also performed.   ','','Ramp type demand, Shortages  ',' Vineet Kumar, S.R. Singh  ','153-164    ','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','70','2014-05-16 17:13:38','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1188,'Modeling and Analysis of the Effects of Radial Variation of Viscosity with a Peripheral Layer on Resistance to Flow and Shear Stress in an Artery with Mild Stenosis      ','In this paper, a model to study the effects of peripheral layer viscosity of blood on the blood flow in an artery in the presence of stenosis in the lumen by considering the radial variation of viscosity in the core region, is proposed and analyzed. The analysis shows that the resistance to flow and wall shear decreases as the peripheral layer viscosity decreases for fixed values of stenosis height and thickness of core region. It is also seen that the peripheral resistance and wall shear increase as the size of stenosis increases for fixed value of peripheral layer viscosity.      ','','Radial variation, viscosity,stenosis      ','Lovely Jain and S.P. Singh      ','165-176           ','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','70','2014-05-16 17:14:30','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1189,' A Two-unit model with set-up time after preventive maintenance and repair ','This paper deals with the stochastic analysis of a two non- identical units. This paper discusses the concept of correlation between time to preventive maintenance time and repair time. On minor failure, preventive maintenance is applied on failed unit and also preventive maintenance is taken preferred over repair. In this paper, units after maintenance and repair requires to be set up before it work. A single repair facility appears in and disappears from the system randomly with constant rate. Here preventive maintenance time and repair time is taken as bivariate expontial. In this paper system is analyzed to determine various reliability measures by using mathematical tools MTSF/MTBF Markov chain, Markov Process, renewal process. It is assumed that a repaired unit is as good as new and switch over time is negligible.   ','','preventive maintenance, corrective maintenance, MTSF/MTBF, Markov chain, Markov process, renewal process etc. Regenerative Point, Availability, Busy Period. ','  Shruti Rani Raj Kumar and Ashutosh Sharma ','177-190  ','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','70','2014-05-16 17:15:26','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1190,' Exact Traveling Waves Solutions for GKdV, GIKdV and BBM Equations by Sine-Hyperbolic Function Method ','In this work, we established a traveling wave solution by using sine-hyperbolic algorithm for nonlinear partial differential equations. Sine-hyperbolic function method is used to obtain exact travelling wave solutions of nonlinear partial differential equations. The method is used to obtain the exact solutions for three different types of nonlinear partial differential equations such as, General Kortewegde Vries equation, General Improved Kortewegde Vries equation and BenjaminBonaMahony equation, which are the important soliton equations. The results reveal that the implemented technique is very effective and convenient for solving nonlinear partial differential equations arising in mathematical physics.\r\nKeywords: Sine-hyperbolic function Method, General Korteweg-De Vries (GKdV) equation, General Improved Korteweg-De Vries (GIKdV) equation, BenjaminBonaMahony equation (BBM) equation\r\n ','','hyperbolic function Method, General Korteweg-De Vries (GKdV) equation, General Improved Korteweg-De Vries (GIKdV) equation, BenjaminBonaMahony equation (BBM) equation ','Amit Tomar ','191-198  ','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','40','70','2014-05-16 17:16:31','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1191,' A mathematical Programming Approach for Sugarcane Cultivation in the state of North India','In Indian economy sugarcane has great contribution to GDP. A large population of India depends on the agriculture sector for livelihood. At, the same time, due to expanding population , diminishing arable land and rising service industry, there is need to increase the production by utilizing the available agriculture resources. This paper represents a linear goal programming model for sugarcane to help farmers to allocate different resources available for sugarcane production in optimum manner.','','Agriculture, arable, fertilizers, cash, sugarcane, goal.','Himanshu Pandey,Ashutosh Pandey',' 47-54','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','39','61','2014-02-27 11:32:20','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1192,' Optimal Diagnosis of AMI by Artificial Neural Network and Data Envelopment Analysis','Optimization of diagnostic efficiency by mathematic modeling rather than logic is getting momentum in the medical spectrum using computer data analysis. Effective evaluation of disease diagnosis is considered to be one of the research problems getting relief and reduction of cost. Thus the diagnosis of Acute Myocardial Infarction (AMI) by DEA-ANN method is a significant development received by Physician as well as R&D of Pharmaceuticals. This study proposes an optimization criterion of diagnosis by BCC method of Data Envelopment Analysis (DEA) and Artificial Neural Network. ANN is used as a logical tool to optimize the decision developed by DEA. Tables and graphs were provided for the optimization diagnosis of 100 patients and conclusions were made on the final diagnosis. ','','Diagnosis, Acute Myocardial Infarction (AMI), Data Envelopment ance, Optimization.','T.B. Ramkumar, Deepthi K.S',' 55-62','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','39','61','2014-02-27 11:34:23','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1193,' FDI in Indian Retail Market: The Proxy Way of Using Game Theory by Multinational Companies in India Market','From ancient time to present 21st century, India is always an attraction for other world countries for trade and business. These trades and business have made India many times rich and prosperous country in world. But in eighteen century a company came to India for trade but slowly takes full advantage of that time political condition and become the master of this nation. The declined of trade and the drainage of wealth to Europe made this prosperous country to stand in line of world poorer country in world. After independence the mixed economy of country and hard working Indian people along with industrialists again made India economy to stand in world trade.\r\nToday, India provides a large market for trade and business for the multinational companies (MNCs). Every country of world is egger to make the trade relation with India. The developed countries found a good market within India for their finished products and services. India had large resources for exploitation and purchasing power of India people made India in better position to compete the MNCs. In this paper, we study how these MNCs are using the game theory in strategy to capture the Indian market from Indian companies with analyzing its impact on India companies, market and business. The prime focus of this research paper on FDI for retail sector as one of strategy of game theory used by MNCs against in direct competition and making collaboration with Indian industries. And tried to find optional strategy should the Indian nation evolve to safe guard its companies and people healthy interest against those MNCs coming through FDI in Indian market.\r\n','','MNC, game theory, market, information','Himanshu Pandey,Upendra Nath Tripathi, Avinash Singh, Ashutosh Pandey',' 63-71','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','39','61','2014-02-27 11:37:09','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1194,'A Production Inventory Model for Deteriorating Items with Shortages and Time Dependent Exponentially Decreasing Demand','In this paper, a production-inventory model for deteriorating items is developed over a finite planning horizon where the demand decreasing exponentially with time. The production rate is assumed to be finite and constant. Shortages in inventory are allowed and are completely backlogged. Deterioration rate is constant. As a result, we establish a model to find the optimum values of time and inventory level by minimizing the average cost.','','Production inventory, time-dependent demand, deteriorating item, shortages.',' Balvinder Singh Sandhu, Arun Kumar Tomer','73-82 ','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','39','61','2014-02-27 11:38:56','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1195,' Optimized Layout for Machines by Applying Genetic Algorithm','Developing a machine layout is an important step in designing manufacturing facilities due to the impact of the layout to material handling cost and time, and consequently, affects the overall productivity of the shop floor. Poor layout would result in having more parts spending longer time moving from one machine to another, and thus results in increasing material handling costs.  In contrast to the block layout, the objective of the machine layout problem is to find the appropriate placement of machines in a cell. This paper provides descriptions to solve the layout problem and describes a novel method based on genetic algorithms (GA) to solve the machine layout problem. The GA-based method developed to solve this uses the objective of minimizing the movements of parts being processed in the cell. ','','machine layout, genetic algorithms, cellular manufacturing.',' Anuj Kumar Jhankal, Vikas Sangwan and Subhash Chand Gupta','83-87','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','39','61','2014-02-27 11:40:50','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1196,'A Two-unit model with three types of maintenance and repair','This paper investigates a mathematical model based on reliability theory of a system composed of two units - one is operative and other is cold standby having only one repairman. In this paper, we considered different types of maintenance and repair. Mainly three types of maintenance viz. Preventive, Corrective and emergency maintenances are considered along with the repair facilities. In this paper system will be analyzed to determine various reliability measures by using mathematical tools MTSF/MTBF, Markov chain, Markov process, renewal process etc.','','preventive maintenance, corrective maintenance, MTSF/MTBF, Markov chain, Markov process, renewal process etc. Regenerative Point, Availability, Busy Period.',' Shruti Rani, Raj Kumar and Ashutosh Sharma',' 89-102','N