orical background of Japanese encephalitis, scenario of Japanese encephalitis in India, its transmission, clinical features, prevention & treatment. And the second part deals with the psycho- social problems associated with the encephalitis. In a nut shell present article gives an overview of the disease encephalitis with special reference to Japanese encephalitis and all the related psycho-social problems.','','Encephalitis, Japanese Encephalitis, Psychological problems, India',' Krishna Sharma & P.S.N. Tiwari',' 19-31','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','42','71','2014-08-23 06:44:13','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1256,' A Comparative Study of Personality Factors of Pupil Teachers Studying in Self-Financed and Aided Institutions','Until 1999 there was no self-.financed teacher training college is U.P. In the year 2000 C.C.S. University Meerut has nine affiliated degree college imparting teacher education. In the year 2001 first self finance college of education come in to existace under C.C.S. University Meerut. Thus year by year number of self-financed teacher education institutions increased and this number reached 270 during academic session on 2010-2011 B.Ed. program runs in education department govt. Aided institutions is praised by the teacher and educationists how for there education department of aided college satisfy pupil teachers academically. Do they provide quality education to pupil teacher or not? To what extent quality of B.Ed. program run in teacher education department of aided college is superior to quality of teacher education of self financed teacher education institutions. Do they have batter teachers and superior staff-than self-financed institutions? Thus the study impartially and scientifically compared quality of teacher education programme organized by self-financial and aided institutions. On they basis of result discussed above it can safely be concluded that aided institutions are more effective than self - financed institutions in satisfying their pupil teachers on personality factors where as Govt. aided institutions are found more effective than self financed institute in I, L, M, O & Q4 in terms of personality factors, self-financed institutions are more effective than government aided institutions in satisfying their pupil teachers on personality factor G, H, N, & Q2 whereas self-financed institutions are found more effective than government aided institutions in G, H, N, & Q2 in terms of personality factors and the remaining personality factors (A, B, C, E, F, Q1 & Q4) have similar degree.','','Personality Factors, self-financed institutions','Jeetendra Singh & Rachit Kumar',' 33-38','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','42','71','2014-08-23 06:46:43','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1257,' Investigation of Optical Categorization of Zinc Oxide Sintered Films','Zinc Oxide is multifunctional material which has received great attention during the last few years due to their unique applications in microelectronic and optoelectronic devices, and for self-assembled growth of three-dimensional nanoscale systems. Zinc oxide films have been prepared on to highly cleaned glass substrates in open air atmosphere by screen printing technique followed by sintering process. The ZnO sintered films are characterized by optical spectroscopic measurements, X-ray diffraction pattern and scanning electron microscopy.','','Sintered; Reflection Spectra','Suba Sharma',' 39-42','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','42','71','2014-08-23 06:47:39','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1258,' Inculcating Values Through Constructivism','Value development being a process of maturation, internalization and cognitive restructuring through reasoning, judgment and decision making rather than being imposed what to think and how to behave, corresponds with the principles of constructivism  a cognitive approach of meaningful learning which holds that knowledge is constructed by learners on their own by actively participating in meaningful and collaborative learning tasks. The author suggests constructivist strategy to be effective for value development among students.','','Value Education, Constructivist Strategy','Seema Agrawal','43-47','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','42','71','2014-08-23 06:48:51','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1259,' Need and Scope Of Biostatistics In Epidemology','Epidemiology is the study of the patterns, causes, and effects of health and disease conditions in defined populations. It is the cornerstone of public health, and informs policy decisions and evidence-based medicine by identifying risk factors for disease and targets for preventive medicine. For many professionals, physicians, Instructors and nurses, there is a fright of statistics. Sometimes, because of lack of training and knowledge professional not able to understand applications. In the present paper describe how biostatistics helped to develop methodology used in clinical research, public health studies and, to a lesser extent, basic research in the biological sciences. The present paper also deals with the scope and application of biostatistics in epidemiology.','','-','Sonia Sharma, Rachit Kumar, Hemlatha Vasishtha & Deepankar Sharma','49-54','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','42','71','2014-08-23 06:50:11','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1260,' A Common Core Challenge : Stress Free Learning ','As the summer winds down thought of books and classes form in our minds. Students of all ages must now focus on the necessary tools required to help them to become successful people in the class room . ','','- ',' Sundari Bala Sharma, Arti Sharma ',' 55-60','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','42','71','2014-08-23 07:13:46','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1261,' Designing of High Gain Wang Shaped Microstrip Antenna','In this paper, a novel design technique for enhancing gain that improves the performance of a conventional microstrip patch antenna is proposed. A novel multi slotted High Gain Wang shaped Rectangular Microstrip Patch Antenna is designed using IE3D. The aim of the thesis is to Design and fabricate a High Gain Coaxial fed Rectangular Microstrip Antenna and study the effect of antenna dimensions Length (L), Width (W) and substrate parameters, relative Dielectric constant (r), substrate thickness, Radiation parameter. Low dielectric constant substrates are generally preferred for maximum radiation. The conducting patch can take any shape but rectangular and circular configurations are the most commonly used configuration. Other configurations are complex to analyze and require heavy numerical computations. The proposed design offers low profile, very high gain and compact element. The maximum gain is 12 dBi to 12.55 dBi from 1.82GHz to 1.99GHz. Antenna efficiency and Radiation efficiency are more than 90% and bandwidth is 9% from 1.82 GHz to 1.99GHz. The proposed design is suitable particular for wireless communication application such as Wi-Fi and WLAN. Desired Patch Antenna Design is initially simulated by using IE3D simulator. This Patch antenna is realized as per design requirements.','','microstrip, radiation, communication','Bhuma Naresh','503-508','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2014-08-23 10:06:49','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1262,' Effect Of Water Stress On Yield And Quality Of Potato Tubers','By the late 18th and early 19th century, potatoes were sufficiently established in the hills and plains of India. The initial varieties had acquired local names, such as Phulwa (flowering in the plains), Gola (round potatoes) and Satha (maturing in sixty days) etc. The early potato varieties in India were introduced via Europe, most of which proved unsuitable to Indian conditions on the hotter plains, since they were adapted to cultivation during the long winter days of Europe.','','-','Devendra Kumar Mishra','509-513','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2014-08-23 10:07:35','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1263,' Role and Management of Trade Unions in India','Thus, managing trade unions is a challenging task. Unlike the business organisations, trade unions as organisations, cannot purchase the compliance of the members through monetary rewards alone. They have to ensure that both the economic and noneconomic interests of the members are satisfied on a continuous basis. Keeping all this in view, in this unit we shall try to understand unions as organisations, the internal affairs of the unions, leadership aspect of unions, and union activities.','','Monetary, Economic, Leadership','Gyan Prakash','515-519','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2014-08-23 10:08:30','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1264,' Inter Relationship between Micro Finance and Ngos Programmes','The origin of Micro finance or micro credit can be traced to the 1976 when Mohammed Yunus set up the Grameen Bank experiment on the outskirts of Chittagong University Campus as an experiment. Grameen we mean rural or village in Bangladesh language. These Grameen banks provide loans to the poor who do not have anything to put up for collateral. Grameen banks are the largest rural financial institution in Bangladesh. Their lending guidelines and procedures are mainly for women, 97% are women. In terms of clients, Grameen Bank is doing very well. To most, Microfinance means providing very poor families with very small loans to help them engage in productive activities or grow their very small businesses.','','Language, Guidelines, Financial','Kadrekar Prakash Gangadhar Rao','521-525','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2014-08-23 10:09:28','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1265,' Need and Achievement of Adolescents and Their Relationship with Parents','The entire treasure of Vedic literature contains religious philosophies, ideas and moral principles. The basic aim of education was the propagation of those ideas, the ultimate aim however being the realization of the True knowledge and the Absolute. A study of the ancient scriptures of the Vedic, post.-Vedic and the Buddhist periods reveals that the development of character and personality of the learners was an essential object of education in ancient India. The preachers of the time paid adequate attention to inculcate values along with the mental uprightness. During Buddhist period also, education was value-oriented; the pupils were required development and observance of strict code of moral conduct and discipline. It is relevant to mention that the education system in the Buddhist period in India was liberal, democratic and free from communal narrowness unlike Hindu system of education.','','Buddhist, Propagation, Relevant','Manjulika Tyagi','527-530','NO','','International Journal of Education and Information Sciences','31','57','2014-08-23 10:10:25','E',11,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1266,' Study of Multilayer CdS Thin Film','Polymers are generally known for their insulating property because of covalent bond present in saturated carbon compounds. Since desirable properties can be conveniently attained by tailoring the polymer structure and also by incorporating additives, scientists have been enthusiastic to explore the possibility of transforming insulating polymers into conducting or semiconducting materials envisaging such special characteristics like low density, ease of fabrication, fle