ed . First derived the dynamical equation of the two link robot manipulator using Euler- Lagrange Method and then a simple and efficient control scheme developed. The efficiency of the PID control law is tested by the simulation results.','','Control Design and Simulation',' Rahul Kumar, Rajendra Kumar and Sandeep Kumar','101-112','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','49','84','2015-09-21 16:31:10','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1313,' Exact Degree of Approximation of Periodic Functions by Hausdorff Means of Fourier Series ','In this work, Many investigators have proved that   where   and   are the Hausdorff means of the Fourier series of f.  We observe that the degree of approximation depends on p and proof of the results given by the authors are not valid for p = 1. In this paper, we obtain the degree of approximation free from p with a separate proof for p = 1. Some corollaries are also derived. ','','Degree of Approximation, W - class, Fourier Series, ',' Lalit Kumar Som,Deepika Agrawal, Deepak Bhati',' 113-120','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','49','84','2015-09-21 16:35:51','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1314,' Conceptualizing Belongingness and its behavioral consequences  ','The fundamental, core and intrinsic motive to belong has a number of meaning for individuals and every meaning possesses the same sense of importance. This paper aims to point out the important role of motive to belong, clearing the meaning and concept of belongingness. The article further talks about how a sense of Belongingness works as a facilitator in enhancing many other important variables. In this post, I\'ve described a few of the many benefits that come from greater belongingness. On the other hand, the article reviews about the negative outcomes of deprivation. When this need is not come to meet; it produces the great harm for the well-being of 