e which is linearly time dependent and the production rate depends on the demand. Here, deterioration rate is considered as a constant and shortages are fully backlogged. The mathematical model is derived to investigate the total cost which need to be minimized. Finally, a numerical example is given to illustrate the model and sensitivity is also included.','','Deterioration, time dependent demand, production, shortages.','Anuradha and Jitendra Kumar','381-390','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','44','85','2015-10-13 16:18:41','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1320,' An economic order quantity model with stock dependent demand with trade credit period and inflation ','This paper deals an economic order quantity model having stock dependent demand with trade credit period and inflation for decaying items. Cost minimization technique has been taken in this study. In this study the supplier allows a permissible delay period to the retailer to pay all the dues account. Considering the real life situations ordering cost is also taken as time dependent.  Here the retailer invests on preservation expenses, to reduce the rate of deterioration. However, there is a constraint up to which deterioration rate can be reduced; hence a upper bound is also involved.  Numerical illustration is given to show the convexity of the model and sensitivity analysis is also given ','','stock dependent demand, trade credit period,  inflation  ','  Nirdosh Kumar Shishodia, Shiv Raj Singh ',' 391-402  ','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','44','85','2017-05-18 04:12:16','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1321,' An order model with exponential demand under shortages and inflation','This paper deals an economic order quantity model having time dependent demand with inflation for decaying items. Cost minimization technique has been taken in this study.  An ordered quantity inventory system for decaying items with exponential demand has been discussed. Items deteriorate at a two parameter Weibull distribution function. Numerical illustration is given to show the convexity of the model and sensitivity analysis is also given.','','time dependent demand, inflation',' Madan Pal',' 403-412','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','44','85','2015-10-13 16:26:19','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1322,' TWO STORAGE INVENTORY MODEL FOR DETERIORATING ITEMS WITH VARIABLE DEMAND UNDER INFLATION',' In this paper, we proposed a production model for deteriorating items with shortage and inflation. We considered a demand rate which is price and time dependent at the same time production is also depends on demand. As we know that sometimes manufacture produced more quantity of goods which is not easily stored in single ware house so that RW is used for the storage. As a realistic assumption, we assume that the deterioration of RW is different from the OW. To show the utility of the model, we solve a numerical example, convexity and sensitivity analysis.   ','','production model, deteriorating items, shortage and inflation','Jayshree','413-424','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','44','85','2015-10-13 16:28:49','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1323,'  Opticalproperties of GaAs/Gebasedone-dimensional non-linear photonic crystal','Non-linear property of materials of the constituent layersof one-dimensional binary photonic crystalstructures consisting of alternate layers of nonlinear material such as, Gallium arsenide (GaAs) andGermanium (Ge).Reflectance, dispersion, normalized group velocity and effective group index of refraction of these multilayered structures, have been studied for different intensities of controlling wave by solving Maxwells electromagnetic equations. The propagation of an electromagnetic signal wave is possible at high intensity of the controlling wave, which is prohibited in absence of the controlling wave. Hence, a signal wave inside the structure may be, possibly, trapped inside the structure by changing the intensity of the controlling wave. Also, the most interesting feature of the structure considered in this paper, is the dependence of the group velocity of the signal on the intensity of the controlling wave. By increasing the intensity of the controlling wave, the negative effective group index can be shifted towards the longer wavelength side. The structure may behave like a good reflector or a transparent material by choosing appropriate intensity of the controlling wave, and hence can be used as optical switch.','','Nonlinear Photonic crystal, TMM method, Kerr coefficient.',' Vinay Kumar',' 425-435','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','44','85','2015-10-13 16:32:44','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1324,' Tunable optical filter based on multilayer photonic structure','A novel method to design the tunable optical band pass filter using multilayer photonic structure has been proposed. The multilayer structure has been suggested choosing Ge as high refractive index material and ZnS as low refractive index material. The refractive index of both the materials has been taken as wavelength and temperature dependent. So the allowed bands can be tuned by varying the temperature without changing geometry and angle of incidence.','','Photonic crystals, Multilayer structure, Optical filter ',' Vinay Kumar',' 451-460','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','44','86','2015-10-13 16:38:55','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1325,' Effect of permissible delay in payments and inflation on Two warehouse inventory model  ','In the present study we developed the two warehouse inventory model for decaying items with exponential demand. Shortages are allowed with partial backlogging. The effect of trade credits in an inflationary environment has been considered.