 AND ALMOST SEMICONNECTED MAPPINGS','Continuous mappings are special cases of connected mappings, therefore it is of great interest to know what conditions must be imposed upon a given mapping or upon the topological spaces in order to conclude that a given mapping is continuous or homeomorphism. Professor John Jones Jr. [1] introduced semiconnected mappings. Semilocally connected spaces were introduced by G.T. whyburn [10]. Using this we study here almost S-continuous mappings, almost semiconnected mappings and weakly almost semiconnected mappings. The S-continuous mappings [3] are stronger forms of almost S-continuous mappings. Various properties of above mentioned mappings, have been investigated and studied. In the last monotone extensions are also found useful in the study of these mappings.','','continuous mappings, almost semi connected mappings',' Kapil Kumar Sharma, B.S. Sharma',' 135-143','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','49','84','2016-01-17 14:36:23','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1340,' An Inventory Model with variable holding cost and inflation under limited storage capacity','In the present study, we developed a two warehouse model with imperfect quality items with variable holding cost which is more realistic. We assume that demand is time- dependent and deterioration is taken as Weibull for both OW and RW. Shortages are also allowed in this model. The aim of this study is to minimize the total cost per unit time. Numerical examples, convexity, and sensitivity are provided to illustrate the real problem.','','Variable Holding Cost, Inflation',' S K Shon, Vinesh Kumar',' 145-158','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','49','84','2016-01-17 14:39:13','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1341,' An Integrated Inventory Model for Items under inflationary conditions','In the present study a supply chain inventory model for repairable items has been developed.  In this paper the used products are collected from the market and a certain ratio of these products is repaired and remanufactured. These products are delivered to the retailer, for which a lead time is also considered. The total average cost for the integrated system has been calculated. The theoretical results are illustrated with the help of a numerical example.','','Inventory, supply chain ',' Pravesh Kumar Sharma',' 159-172','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','49','84','2016-01-17 14:42:03','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1342,' A HYPERSPACE AND ITS SEPARATION AXIOMS ','In this paper, we have considered a topological space ( ,I)with its bi-topological space( , I1, I2). We have studied various Separation axioms in a particular hyperspace 2I1, 2I2) of a bi-topological space. As a part of this, properties of separation axioms such as pair-wise Hausdorff, pair-wise Urysohn, pair-wise Stone space and others have been discussed. In this contribution, we consider the separation axioms T2 and T3 and the associated concepts of stone space, Urysohn functions and regularity. Our main conclusion is that the hierarchy of separation axioms that is familiar from topological spaces generalizes to hyperspace  .','','Bi-topological space, Hausdorff space, Urysohnspace, Stone space, Bi-compactness, Separation axioms',' Yogesh Sharma, Parul Tiwari',' 71-76','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','49','78','2016-01-17 15:29:06','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1343,' Optimal policy for time dependent decaying items with ramp-type demand and Variable holding cost ','In this paper a deterministic inventory model has been developed for decaying item having a ramp type demand. The deterioration rate follows Weibull distribution function. Shortages in inventory are allowed. Holding cost is taken as  function of time. Numerical example is also used to study the behavior of the model. Cost minimization technique is used to get the expressions for total cost and other parameters ','','deterministic inventory model,Shortages  ','  Nirdosh Shishodia, Shiv Raj Singh ','77-86  ','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','49','78','2017-05-18 04:10:48','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1344,' L (- OPEN, SEMI OPEN) MAPPINGS','In this paper we study a new class of mappings namely L(*-open, semi open) mappings which contains the class of strongly continuous mappings of Levine [3] and is contained in the class of L(*-open, open) mappings [2]. Besides various properties, the restrictions, compositions in reference of new mappings are established. Nets and filters are used to characterize the mappings. Some seperation and covering axioms are studied concerning the mappings. In the last the graph map and preservation results are also studied in the connection to the new class of mappings.','','strongly continuous mappings',' Kapil Kumar Sharma, B.S. Sharma',' 87-96','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','49','78','2016-01-17 15:34:06','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1345,' Optimal ordering quantity of the inventory system with ramp type demand with random rate of deterioration and variable holding cost','This model is based on time dependent ramp-type demand rate. If demand pattern of seasonal products within the season I considered then it increases initially with respect to time, in the mid of the season it is static and towards the end of the season it decreases and becomes asymptotic. This phenomenon of demand for perishable seasonal products for a season is discussed by considering six possible Cases related to the demand transfer points and cycle times. All the cost functions are derived and their convexity is established. An easy-to-use algorithm is provided to determine the optimal system running cost and ordering quantity for the entire season. The demand pattern assumed here is found to occur not only for all types of seasonal products but also for fashionable goods, computer chips of advanced computers, spare parts etc  and  Linear increasing holding cost is also assumed. The running cost of the system for the entire season is derived and minimized by determining the optimal ordering quantity of the system','','Variable Holding cost, ramp type demand, deterioration',' Vikramjeet Singh',' 0 1-18','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','51','91','2016-01-17 16:09:55','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1346,' An integrated model with ramp type demand under inflationary environment','This model is an integrated inventory model with two parameter Weibull deterioration and variable holding cost under inflation. The objective of this model is to determine the optimal value of length of the production time and production that minimizes the total cost of the inventory system. If we take the example of food items, which deteriorate with the weather condition and their holding cost is not constant then this model is more applicable. Thus this chapter gives a unique theory on supply chain management. ','','integrated inventory model, Weibull deterioration, variable holding cost',' Jayshree',' 19-32','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','51','91','2016-01-17 16:12:23','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1347,' Effect of Progressive Payment Scheme on an Optimal Ordering Policy with Stock Dependent Demand','This model is an EOQ model for deteriorating items with stock- dependent demand when the supplier offers two progressive credit periods to the retailer to settle his account. In progressive payment scheme, a supplier suggests two different offers to increase the amount of purchasing. Firstly, if the order quantity is greater than or e