er inflationary environment','In this study we developed an inventory model with stock dependent demand and non-instantaneous deterioration. Shortages are allowed and partially backordered with a variable backlogging rate. Numerical examples, convexity, and sensitivity are provided to illustrate the real problem.','','stock dependent demand, partial backlogging, inflationary environment','S K Shon, Vinesh Kumar',' 13-24','NO','','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','52','87','2016-06-23 15:30:17','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1351,' Six Sigma:  A new management Mantra','In the changed global scenario, almost all organizations are striving hard to upgrade its system to cope up with the man management as well as improvement in overall qualities of the organization including process and procedure. Quality is directly related to customers satisfaction. This finally culminates in brand building. In modern day management  six sigma  approach has been accepted as most emerging  management philosophy and technology which helps in minimizing errors or defects up to 3-4 % in parts per million (ppm). This paper is to provide general idea about six sigma concepts, implementation and how it helps optimize performance in various fields','','Six-Sigma  ',' Bikas Prasad',' 01-08','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','53','94','2016-06-23 16:21:56','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1352,'  Inventory Model for non-instantaneous decaying items with partial backlogging under inflationary environment  ','In this paper we developed an inventory model with stock dependent demand and non-instantaneous deterioration. Shortages are allowed and partially backordered with a variable backlogging rate. To illustrate the results and its significant features, a numerical example is given.  ','','inflation and deterioration  ','   Sanjay Kumar Sharma, Shiv Raj Singh  ',' 09-18    ','NO','','Inter