ors, one is time, and other is the stock level. The stock level in itself obviously gets depleted due to the customers demand. This assumption takes the customers interests as well as the market forces into account. The demand rate is such that as the inventory level increases, it helps to increase the demand for the inventory under consideration.  ','','time dependent demand, shortages',' Pravesh Sharma',' 57-71','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','51','91','2016-06-23 16:45:19','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1356,' An EOQ model with price dependent demand and shortages under inflation and delay in payments','In this paper we developed an Inventory model for deteriorating products having selling price dependent demand rate. The model is developed with two level of two credit financing and partial backlogging. A numerical example and sensitivity analysis is also given to illustrate the model.','','EOQ model,  price dependent demand, shortages, inflation  ',' S K Shon, Vinesh Kumar',' 101-108','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','51','92','2016-06-23 16:48:00','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1357,' A two-warehouse supply chain multi-items inventory model for decaying items with inflation induced demand',' In this paper, we proposed a two-warehouse supply chain multi-items inventory model for decaying items with inflation induced demand. We assume that the inventory costs (including holding cost and deterioration cost in RW are higher than those in OW). The effect of permissible delay in payments has been taken in this study. Shortages are allowed with complete backlogging. Production rate is considered as demand dependent in vendor model. The model has also been exemplified with numerical examples. The results have also been interpreted graphically.','','two-warehouse, supply chain, multi-items, inflation induced demand',' Mahender Kumar',' 109-122','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','51','92','2016-06-23 16:49:59','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1358,' An inventory model with selling price dependent demand, shortages under inflation and delay in payments ','In this paper we developed an Inventory model for deteriorating products having selling price dependent demand rate. The model is developed with two level of two credit financing and partial backlogging. A numerical example and sensitivity analysis is also given to illustrate the model ','','deteriorating products, selling price dependent demand  and partial backlogging ','  Sanjay Kumar Sharma, Shiv Raj Singh ',' 01-10  ','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','55','96','2017-05-18 04:07:44','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1359,' Least Absolute Deviation Estimation versus Nonlinear   Regression Model With Hetroscedacity Errors','Least absolute deviation (LAD), also known as least absolute errors (LAE), Least absolute value (LAV) Least absolute residual (LAR) Sum of absolute deviation, or the L1 norm condition is a statistical optimality criterion and the statistical optimization technique that relies on it. The least absolute Deviation (LAD) estimation in a  field of great interest in regression analysis .The application of this method are available in the recent literature covering various aspects of modeling ,computational efficiency, error analysis ,gross error identification etc. Nonlinear regression is characterized by the fact that the prediction equation depends nonlinearly on one or more unknown parameters. The inferential aspect of unknown regression models and the error assumptions are usually analogous to those made for linear regression models. The various inferential problems on nonlinear regression models, involving hetroscedastic errors have been studied by several author cited in the recent  literature. In this paper its proposed to discuss LAD estimations versus nonlinear regression model with hetroscedastic errors. The problem of heteroscedasticity can also be studied with reference to nonlinear regression models with suitable illustration.','','hetroscedastic errors, nonlinear  regression models.',' S.Eakambaram, M. Salomi, and R. Elangovan',' 1-20','YES','01 IJORO V 7-1-2016-1-20.pdf','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','56','97','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1360,' Determination of Optimal Reserve Inventory between one Machine in First Stage and Two at Second Stage','Inventory control is a branch of Operation Research. Deterministic and stochastic models are derived to obtain the optimal inventory size taking into consideration the demand for any product, the cost of inventory holding and shortage. An interesting model is to derive the optimal reserve or stock of the semi-finished product between two machines in series. The output of machine M1 is the input of machine M2. The breakdown of M1 will force M2 to go to down stage. Determination of optimal reserve has been attempted by several authors. In this paper, it is assumed that the output of M1 happens to be the input for two machines which are in parallel system, in the second stage. The optimal size of reserve inventory is the obtained under the assumption that the inter arrival times between successive breakdowns of M1 is a random variable which undergoes a change of distribution. Numerical illustration also provided Numerical examples are also provided.','','Reserve inventory, first stage and second stage, repair time, change of distribution',' M. Govindhan, R. Elangovan and R. Sathyamoorthi',' 21-34','YES','02 IJORO V 7-1-2016-21-34.pdf','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','56','97','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1361,' Handling of Missing and Anomalous Data through Inference in Data Mining','Research about data for data mining / big data /database is an essential stage of data analysis. During data research the main complications crop up because of missing data, outliers and contaminated data. Missing data are defined as some of the values in the data set which are either lost, not observed, not available due to natural or non natural reasons. Whereas outlier is defined as data point this is very different from the rest of the data based on some measure because outliers can skew statistical results.  Data with outlier / missing values confuses both the data analysis and the submission of a solution to fresh data.  This situation is widely recognized problem affecting large database in data mining. Major problems that may arise when dealing with incomplete data are loss of information and, as a consequence, a loss of efficiency and bias results. To overcome this condition, some of the mechanisms are used like ignore the tuple, fill in the missing value manually, use a global constant to fill in the missing value, use the attribute mean to fill in the missing value and use the most probable value to fill in the missing value. Therefore, the need to find the best way in estimating missing values is very important so that the data analyzed is ensured of high quality. The objective of present study is proper handling of missing data values and their analysis with removal of the anomalous/outlier data. Therefore, the key premise of this projected work is to analyze the role of inference in data preparation for data mining in context of missing and anomalous data in the database.','','Missing Values, Outlier, Attribute, Data Mining, Inference','Sanjay Gaur ',' 1-7','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:10:56','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1362,' Optimization of Reaction Parameters by Taguchi Method:  Emulsion Polymerization of Acrylic Monomers','In this article, Taguchi method is used to theoretically optimize the various reaction parameters and their interactions that may affect the end properties of synthetic acrylic latex using emulsion polymerization made in a laboratory batch reactor. An attempt has been made to assess and predict the effect of temperature, reaction cycle time and concentration of initiator on one of the properties of finished latex i.e. Particle size. In the present studies effect of three process parameters on the particle size of the finished latex has been studied. By using Taguchi method, orthogonal experimental design and analysis technique; the performance of this process is analyzed with more objective conclusion and by conducting only a small number of simulation experiments. Analysis of variance (ANOVA) was performed to identify the significant factors affecting the response and the best possible factor level combination was determined through.','','Taguchi method, ANOVA, Acrylic Latex, Emulsion Polymerization, laboratory batch reactor, Minitab 14','Purvi J Naik and Sandeep Rai',' 8-20','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:13:12','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1363,' Regression Analysis of Crime at Hyderabad in last five Years','Over the past five years, crime has been increasingly making its way into the world of information. The government has been looking into ways of curbing all these types of crimes. Crime is evolving; since the days when goods were transported by robbery murder etc. The government has been looking into ways of curbing all these types of crimes; there are some laws on the books and more being considered. In this project, we examine the types of crime  that have been committed in the past five years .Regression analysis is a Statistical technique for estimating the relationship among variables which have reason and result relation. Regression analysis provides information on relationship between a response variable and one or more predictor variables but only to the degree that such information is contained in the data base. Whether the data are compiled from a complete enumeration of a population an appropriate sample survey, regression coefficient can be estimated and conclusions can be drawn from the fitted model. ','','Crime Statistics, Criminals, Crimes, Convictions, Demographic Characteristics, Criminal Rates, Crime Rates, Spatial analysis. ',' P. Laxmi  Prasanna  ',' 21-27','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:15:17','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1364,' B Spline Collocation approach for the Solution of Boundary Layer Convective Heat Transfer Flow over a Flat Plate','In this paper we examine the boundary layer convective heat transfer flow over a flat plate. The nonlinear equations of momentum and energy are transformed from partial differential equations into ordinary differential equations by using similarity transformation; the results are compared with Numerical method and Homotopy Perturbation Method. Conclusion can be drawn that B Spline Collocation method provides highly precise numerical solution for nonlinear differential equations. The results were accurate especially for 4, a general equating terms of Eckert number is derived which can be used to investigate velocity and temperature profiles in boundary layer. The effect of various flow parameters are presented and discussed as they affect the flow.','','B Spline Collocation method, Convection heat transfer, Boundary layer.',' Pragna Mistry, D.C. Joshi',' 28-39','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:17:17','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1365,' Star Topology Network with Fast Switching Capabilities','We analyze a star network with fast switching capabilities in the central hub using discrete queueing theory. We describe the characteristics of fast switching (FS) capabilities system. We present the performance analysis of a finite capacity star network with FS capabilities by using FIFO selection policy. We provide mean normalized total delay of star network with infinite capacity. We also present performance analysis of a star network with FS capabilities by implementing RND selection policy.','','Star topology, Fast switching capabilities, FIFO policy, RND selection policy ',' Poonam Singh',' 40-52','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:18:55','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1366,' Numerical Solution of G/M/1 Queueing Model with Removable Server','In this investigation, we deal with the single removable server in a  queueing system with finite capacity under the -policy. The present model has wide applications in telecommunication, computers and several other fields. A Computational technique is used to study the optimal control of a removable server in a  queueing system with finite capacity , where is the maximum capacity of the system. The term removable server is just a term for the system of turning on and turning off the server, depending on the number of customers in the system. First, the steady-state equations for the model are given. A computational method for the solution of these equations is described and an algorithm is developed for the same.  The method is tested on two examples taking inter-arrival distribution as exponential and Erlangs. The present method is powerful and is easy to implement. Numerical results for system performance measures such as expected number of customers in the system and expected waiting time in the queue are calculated. It is observed that as offered load increases for the fixed value of , average number of customers in the system also increases.','','G/M/1 queueing model; Removable server; N-policy; Customers; System capacity.',' Mohit, Summiya Parveen, Ather Aziz Raina',' 51-66','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:20:51','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1367,' Numerical Solution of Transient Multi-server Queueing Model','Multi-server queueing systems with Poisson arrivals and Erlangian service times are among the most applicable in queueing theory. A transient solution of the governing equations is a complicated task. Using a standard numerical procedure, probabilities of a number of customers in the system, expected the length of the queue and expected to wait time in the system are computed. ','','Transient; Multi-server; Numerical solution; Queueing model.',' Vikram Rawat, Mohit, Ather Aziz Raina',' 61-75','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:25:43','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1368,' Modified Algebraic Reconstruction Techniques in Computer Tomography','The Finite Series Expansion approach to image reconstruction from projection differs fundamentally from the approach generally termed transform methods because the problems is discretized at the very beginning whereas with transform method the continuous problems is handled until the very end when the final formulas are discretized for computational implementation. \r\nIn this paper we discussed finite series-expansion approach. It describes the methodology of the approach and takes the reader on a short tour of some reconstruction algorithms. We intentionally refrain from mathematical analysis and stay on a descriptive level trusting that readers with further interest will fill in by following the literature. Such reading could start with Hermans book [33, Chp. 6, 11-14] or with the survey [36]. Yet another suggestion would be to read our recent review [11] in conjunction with the presents paper, The emphasis in [11] is on the mathematics of the so- called row- action methods which include many of the series- expansion reconstruction methods, whereas here the reconstruction problem itself is the central theme and the problem is formulated in digitized model and algebraic approach .An algorithm Modified Simultaneous Algebraic Reconstruction Technique (MSART) is proposed for algebraic reconstruction method. And the convergence of this algorithm is also discussed and test for some images.\r\n','','Reconstruction techniques, Algebraic Reconstruction Method, Finite series expansion Method, Projection Methods. Tomography, Image processing',' Summiya Parveen, Mohit Gupta and Ajay Tomar ',' 76-91','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:27:41','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1369,' The role of Mathematics in Entrepreneurship','Mathematics is assuming greater and greater importance with every passing day. In the fast developing world of science and technology competence in mathematical applications has become essential for an entrepreneur. An entrepreneur is concerned with the setting up of a new enterprise. Cost calculation is the most important aspect where he needs Mathematics, especially operational research. He is also concerned with the purchase of construction material, raw material for the manufacture of his products. He needs mathematical calculation which can be of immense value in ensuring cost effective establishment and cost effective manufacture of various items of production.','','Entrepreneurs, Operational Research, Innovate, Motivation, Quality control, Risks, Management and Manufacture',' Amarjeet Malik, A.K. Malik',' 92-96','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:29:43','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1370,' Mathematical modelling of an Inventory Model with linear decreasing holding cost and Stock-Dependent Demand rate','Todays in fashionable trade, to impress the consumers\' interest through displaying the inventory items at the shopping centre, stores etc., is an important issue for every business organizations. The present paper deals with the analysis and mathematical modelling of an inventory model with non-instantaneous deteriorating items have been discussed. The holding cost is taken as in linear decreasing function of time. Here demand rate is taken as stock dependent. We determine in this paper the optimal profit and optimal order quantity for the developed model. A numerical example is discussed for the check of optimality of the optimal profit function with its important parameters of the developed mathematical model.','','Inventory Model, Linearly decreasing holding cost, Ordering Cost, Non-instantaneous deterioration, Purchasing cost, Sales revenue cost.',' A. K. Malik, Ajay Tomar,  Dipak Chakraborty',' 97-104','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','98','2017-02-24 08:31:56','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1371,'Sudoku Solutions: New and Advanced Intuitive Heuristics','Sudoku, a logic-based popular number game has been of interest to programmers and a number of computer solvers are available. In this paper we introduce some advanced heuristic moves based on constraints of Sudoku. Later we explore the order in which these heuristic moves are to be applied i.e. the order or permutation which requires less computation. Finally, the validity of the move selection order is verified by simultaneously calculating probabilities for correct filling.   ','','Sudoku, heuristic moves ',' S  Durga',' 105-117','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','99','2017-02-24 08:38:30','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1372,' Implementation of An Automated Attendance Monitoring Application Using Eigen Faces Recognition Algorithm in MATLAB','Attendance monitoring is a very tedious task due to traditional approach of marking the attendance. These include calling the name and marking in the attendance registers. This paper is based on the development of such an application to mark the attendance by using image processing technique of face detection and recognition. Image processing is an emerging field and is the future. It enables us to do the task of digital representation of images as well as very complex task of feature detection and recognition can be done very easily. Face detection and recognition are the key concept used for this task of monitoring.  ','','Image processing, face detection, face recognition and Eigen face',' Ramakant Soni and L. Solanki',' 118-129','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','99','2017-02-24 08:40:30','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1373,' Test case prioritization for reduced test suit on the basis of Requirements, code coverage, and cost','Software testing is the process of executing software using test data, with a view to identify errors. Testing involves generation of test data on the basis of test cases that are most likely to reveal errors. Software cant be tested for every possible input data i.e. exhaustive testing is never possible. This requires generation of only those test cases that are most likely to reveal errors. Due to time and cost constraints associated with software testing we need to prioritize the test cases. Test case prioritization is the process of arranging the test cases in descending order of priority. The priority of a test case may be decided on the basis of cost, time, requirements, and code coverage. Increase in number of test cases and resource constraints leads to the necessity of test case prioritization. In this paper we have tried to capture already proposed techniques in a single platform. This paper proposes techniques to reduce as well as prioritize a given set of test cases. The reduction is on the basis of code coverage and requirements. Prioritization is done on the basis of requirements.','','Test case Prioritization, Regression testing, Requirements, Test case, code coverage, test case weights, requirement weight, test case cost. ',' Vipin Kumar Saraogi',' 130-141','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','99','2017-02-24 08:42:04','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1374,' Relevance of UML 2.0 in Defining IT Architectures and its Support for Systems Engineering','System Modelling and concept of Object Orientation can be leverage to model the systems in the desired way. Specifying system requirements which are clear-cut, complete, unambiguous and comprehensive is next to impossible using any natural language. On the other hand, expressing system requirements in terms of modelling elements like diagrammatic symbols, notations, signs, lines, etc. should make it better understandable, consistent and less ambiguous. This is where exactly UML comes from, a graphical language to visualize, specify, verify and document a system and its components in a very effective way. System requirements expressed in UML terms are easy to understand, comprehensive, quite unambiguous and consistent. An important point to note here is that while modelling software is useful, it will not solve all design issues. But if used correctly, UML and the modelling process can help improve quality, completeness, and scalability and reduce production time in many software projects. OOAD is the methodology, Language used to model is UML and rational unified Process will provide the framework to deploy the model created.\r\nIn this paper, we will see how to use UML 2.0 to model the system which can help to improve quality, completeness and scalability and reduce production time in many software projects. \r\n','','Object Oriented Concepts, UML 2.0 Standard Diagrams, Timing Diagram, Communication, Interaction Overview, Package, Composite Structure Diagram.',' Abhishek Khandelwal & Sanjeev Sultania',' 142-160','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','99','2017-02-24 08:44:15','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1375,' Data Visualization through Variant Choropleth Map','In present days, vast amount of data is available at our disposal by the introduction of various information processing devices and systems. We can use this data wisely to produce some additional meanings. A try is made here through our developed system to make the best use of the available data. The data is presented to the end users in augmented and guided visualization to improve cognitive abilities. This enhancement certainly assists the end users to make certain analysis improvising the decision making abilities. Choropleth map is popular for its usual capabilities of cartographic presentation. Here we are just varying its capabilities to use it as a tool for data visualization making use of PHP','','Data Visualization ',' Shridhar B. Dandin, Ivan FroutGuen',' 160-174','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','99','2017-02-24 08:45:50','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1376,'  Multiple Regression Analysis of Measuring Factors Effecting PG Students of Academic performance','The introduction of continuous assessment evaluation in educational institutions becomes as a component of student\'s final assessment. Educational institutions are always given a great emphasis on the factors governing the student\'s performance. Success and retention have been predicted by using demographic and social factors are assumed to have effect on Post Graduate students. The aim of this study is to determine some factors effecting Post Graduate students performance at private educational institutes in Hyderabad city. A survey is conducted through structured questionnaire consists of 19 questions includes demographic and social factors. Categorical Multiple Regression Analysis is applied to the questionnaires as statistical method by using Minitab software. Categorical Multiple Regression Analysis (CMRA) is an optimal scaling method and can be used when the data is in numeric, nominal and ordinal.','','continuous assessment, demographic, social factors, categorical multiple regression analysis, academic performance.',' T. Vani  Madhavi',' 175-184','NO','','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','57','99','2017-02-24 08:47:28','E',1,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1377,' Importance of Operations Research in Higher Education','India is moving fast towards its economic development. Economic development is integrally related to HE. Without impetus provided by HE economic development cannot be thought of. Happily economic growth is getting impetus from the policies of Indian Government. In this regard the Government\'s main focus is towards increasing the number of employees having higher-level skills, through co-operation between employers and academics and thereby to develop appropriate programmes of study. In this study we purpose to present a selective review of the application of OR in HE to identify some important types of OM problems in HE and discuss the use of OR methods to deal with these problems. It seeks to make administrators in HE aware of the great potential of application of OR to assist them in making decisions, and to show to the OR community that HE is an area where plentiful opportunities exist for OR applications','','Decision Making, Education',' Ajit Malik, Vinod Kumar and A.K. Malik',' 35-40','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','56','97','2017-02-24 08:57:02','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1378,' An inventory model for deteriorating items with ramp type demand and backlogging','An inventory model with ramp type demand with three wei-bull distribution with the concept of life time of an item has been developed. Shortages are allowed and unsatisfied demand is partially backlogged. It is comparatively general in practice, as the demand of some items such as fashionable items increases up to the time of its stabilization. The backlogging rate is the non- increasing function of the waiting time till the next replenishment.','','deteriorating items, ramp type demand, shortages.',' Pushpendra kumar, Rekha Choudhary',' 41-62','NO','','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','56','97','2017-02-24 09:00:32','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1379,' EOQ Model with Trade-credit Financing and Impulsive Holding Cost under Inflation','In this paper, we developed under the situation in which toy supplier provides a delay period to the retailer. There arise two situations of dealings: Case (1): Trade credit period is equal or less than the duration for the settlement of account. Case (2): Trade credit period is equal or greater than the duration for the settlement of account. So model suggests if toy retailer pay timely to the supplier, will get optimal profit','','Trade-credit,Impulsive Holding Cost,EOQ Model,Inflation',' Vikas Sharma and Anubhav Pratap Singh',' 72-100','YES','06.pdf','International Journal of Operations Research and Optimization','51','91','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',4,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1380,' Job Stress among the Teachers of Dehradun ','Teachers are the most critical agents of change, responsible for growth, development and progress of societies and communities. They prepare the next generations, who are expected to take the nation to greater heights. Hence, expectations of society and nation from the teachers are very high. To meet the high expectations, the teacher has to be effective to bring about desirable changes in the behaviour of their students. With globalization, liberalization and vast expansion of new information and communication technologies, the roles of teachers are rapidly changing in current times. The teacher has to remain updated and accordingly convey the same to the pupils in an efficient manner. Achieving the various objectives of teaching and taking care of the behavioural needs of students, often make teaching a stressful job. Stress in job indicates to any characteristics in the job environment, which pose threat to the individual and affect his performance. In other words, stress is a natural biological response, it brings down efficiency of an individual and in long term has an adverse effect on the individuals health. The society cannot afford to lose effective and efficient teachers to stress. The loss will be too high and irreversible. Hence, it is important to identify the factors that cause stress among teachers so that corrective steps can be taken up immediately. The paper deals with the level of stress among the teachers of Dehradun ','',' ',' Shruti Sharma and  Seema Dhawan ',' 1-6  ','NO','','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','60','101','2017-03-07 07:18:14','E',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1381,' Pollen Morphology of Some Angiospermic (Dicotyledonous) Plants of Dehradun 	','Palynology is the study of pollen grains and spores. The morphological characterstics viz., exine ornamentation, aperture of pollen grains and spores are representatives of the various taxa and consequently are of diagnostic valve. The present paper deals with morphology of angiospermic pollen grains. Over all four morphotypes based on the number and position of aperture are recorded. The morphological analysis indicates the dominance of reticulate ornamentation.','','Palynology, Ornamentation, Exine.   ',' Poonam Sharma',' 101-108','YES','ITAS V8 2 101-108.pdf','International Transactions in Applied Sciences','59','102','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',2,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1382,' IMPORTANCE OF BANCASSURANCE IN INDIA ','Bancassurance term first appeared in France in 1980, to define the sale of insurance products through banks distribution channels. This term is extremely popular among the European countries as banks selling insurance products in most of these countries are a common feature.The scope for bancassurance models as feasible source of sustainable income to banking sector is explored by exploiting the synergy in the context of India having the largest banking network on the one hand and lower insurance penetration and insurance density on the other hand. While analyzing the present trend of banks handling insurance products, it also highlights some of the likely issues in general as well as specific from the point of regulator and supervisor. It concludes that going by the present pace, bancassurance would turn out to be a norm rather than an exception in future in India and it would be a win-win situation for all the parties involved - the buyers, the insurance companies and the banks ','',' ',' PARMIL KUMAR ANURAG ',' 7-9  ','NO','','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','60','101','2017-03-07 07:18:02','E',3,'','',NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1383,' Conflict of Values and Belongingness in the Novels of Aravind Adiga','The Indian authors writing in English are endowed with a creative intelligence and a sense of distinctive Indian voices to depict the various real aspects of everyday life. In past decades, the writers like Mulk Raj Anand and R.K. Narayan always offered rich diversity of themes from day to day Indian life and society to present the real portrait of contemporary India. Their works established the whole spectrum of features which constitute the Indianness and can be viewed as metonymic of Indias passage through the age of modernity with sharp contrast to the values and tradition.','','',' Parul Agarwal',' 10-13','NO','','International Transactions in Humanities and Social Sciences','60','101','201