\n',' , ,     ','   ','63-70            ','YES','10.   -n (1).pdf','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','82','130','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',1,'akt1974.at@gmail.com','   - ,\r\n     ,  ,  ','','pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1460,' Desktop Application Based Implementation of Ancient Indian  Mathematical Formulae in Different Radix System ','<p>\r\n	Vedic sutras (formulae) are mostly formulated for decimal radix system. In this paper, it has been shown that those formulae or methods are applicable in any radix system. In this paper, we focus on the subtraction, multiplication and squaring techniques discussed in ancient Indian mathematics. An application has also been developed to compute the subtraction, multiplication and squaring of operands using ancient Indian Mathematics because these arithmetic operations are widely used in our daily life. Our main focus is to show the application using the Vedic mathematics. Since the application development is new to the best of the knowledge of the authors so no comparison has been made in this regard.</p>\r\n','<div>\r\n	[1]. Diganta Sengupta, Mahamuda Sultana and Atal Chaudhuri, &ldquo;VEDIVISION &ndash; A Fast BCD DivisionAlgorithm Facilitated by VEDIC MATHEMATICS&rdquo;, International Journal of Computer Science &amp; Information Technology (IJCSIT), Vol. 5, No 4, August, 2013.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[2]. Krishna Prasad Karani, &ldquo;An Empirical Study on Role of Vedic Mathematics in Improving the Speed of Basic Mathematical Operations&rdquo;, International Journal of Management, IT and Engineering, Vol. 6, No. 1, January, 2016.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[3]. Milo d Iv nkovi, &ldquo;The Ultimate in Vedic Code-breaking: Varuna-deva and Dragon&rsquo;s Eye&rdquo;, AUM Veda, March, 2021.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[4]. Python Code for User Interface, Arindam Banerjee, JISCE, link: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1r9tpQkRGnjyiW77RrfDrxBQ3SzsIVgdq/view?usp=sharing</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[5]. Python user interface cr