 Roorkee College of Engineering, Roorkee, Uttarakhand ','','pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1462,' History of Binomial and Multinomial Expansions      ','<p>\r\n	In applied mathematics Binomial Expansion and Multinomial expansion are of great importance. In around 300 BCE Indian mathematician Pingala had derived the method of obtainng a triangular arrangement known as &ldquo;Meru-Prastar&rdquo; for attainment of coefficients of binomial expansion. In sixteenth century, CE it was rediscovered by French mathematician Blas&eacute; Pascal (1588-1688CE) and termed as Pascal&rsquo;s triangle. This paper discusses the development of binomial expansion, multinomial expansion with its applications. The paper also emphasizes the fact that the historical roots of binomial expansion are embedded in Pingalacharya&rsquo;s Meru-Prastar.</p>\r\n','<div>\r\n	[1]. B Datta, A N Singh, Use of permutations and Combinations in India, revised by K</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	SShukla,IJHS, INSA, Vol 27, No 3 (1992), pp [231-249].</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[2]. C.B.Boyer, A History of Mathematics (revised by Uta C. Mertzbach),John Wiley and Sons,</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	New York, 1991.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[3]. The Gaitakaumud&icirc;(1356 AD) of NryaaPadita,translated by Parmanand</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Singh,GanitaBharati, Vol. (23),No. 1-4, (2001), pp 18-82].</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[4]. Ramesh Chand, A Study of Siddhant Siromani, Ph.D Thesis, GurukulKangri</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Vishwavidyalaya, Haridwar, India, 1991.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[5]. J.L. Collidge, The Story of Binomial Theorem, The AmericanMathematical Monthly 56:3(1949),</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	pp 147-157.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[6]. Kapil Dev Dwivedi and S.L.Singh, The Prosody of Pingala, Vishwavidyalaya Prakashan,</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Varanasi, 2008, pp 262-264.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[7]. R.C. Gupta, Varahmihira&rsquo;s Calculation of nCr and Pascal&rsquo;s Triangle,Ganita Bharati, Vol 14, No. 1-</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	4 (1992) pp.45-49.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	[8]. R.C. Gupta, Comb