iminished. Additional, compulsory and satisfactory circumstances are afforded to&nbsp;illustrate the survival and exclusivity of the best solution. Here we have solved this problem by using Wolfram Mathematica 12.0 software. Lastly, numerical exemplifications, perceptivity study all along graphical demonstrations are revealed to exemplify the realistic purpose of the projected model.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	Abad, P.L., 1996. Optimal pricing and lot sizing under conditions of permissibility and partial backordering. Management Science 42, 1093&ndash;1104.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Baker, R.C., Urban, T.L., 1988. A deterministic inventory system with an inventory level dependent demand rate. Journal of the Operational Research Society 39, 823&ndash;831.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Barman, H., Pervin, M., Roy, S.K. and Weber, G.W.: Back-ordered inventory model with inflation in a cloudy-fuzzy environment, Journal of Industrial and Management Optimization 17(4) (2021) 1913&ndash;1941.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Bierman, H. and Thomas, J. (1977) &lsquo;Inventory decisions under inflationary condition&rsquo;, Decision Sciences, Vol. 8, No. 1, pp.151&ndash;155. Buzacott, J.A., &ldquo;Economic order quantity with inflation&rdquo;, Operational Research Quarterly, 26 (3) ( 1975) 553&ndash;558.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chang, H.J., and Dye, C.Y., &ldquo;An EOQ model for deteriorating items with time varying demand and partial backlogging&rdquo;, Journal of the Operational Research Society, 50 (11) (1999) 1176-182.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Covert, R.P., Philip, G.C., 1973. An EOQ model for items with Weibull distribution deterioration. AIIE Transaction 5, 323&ndash;326. Dye, C.Y., 2007. Joint pricing and ordering policy for a deteriorating inventory with partial backlogging. Omega 35, 184&ndash;189&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Geetha, K.V., Uthayakumar, R., 2010. Economic design of an inventory policy for non-instantaneous deteriorating items under permissible delay in payments. Journal of Computational and Applied Mathematics 223, 2492&ndash;250