imal replenishment policy for noninstantaneous deteriorating items with stock dependent demand and partial backlogging. International Journal of Production Economics 101, 369&ndash;384.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yang, C.Te, Quyang, L.Y., WU, H.H., 2009. Retailers optimal pricing and ordering policies for non-instantaneous deteriorating items with price-dependent demand and partial backlogging. Mathematical Problems in Engineering.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n','partially backlogged shortages, inventory, inflation, noninstantaneous deterioration, stock and price dependent demand. ','  Alka Chaudhary, S. R. Singh, Divya Bharti, and Surbhi Singhal ','35-57   ','YES','paper 3 (2022) issue 1.pdf','International Journal of Inventory Control and Management','84','133','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',5,'divya.statistics14@gmail.com',' Department of Statistics, Meerut College,  Meerut, 250001, India,  ',' http://dx.doi.org/10.58517/IJICM.2022.11103','pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1477,'<p>\r\n	Effect of Inflation and Time Varying Holding Cost on an Inventory Model with Permissible Delay in Payment under Ramp Type Demand</p>\r\n','<p style=\"margin-left:.5in;\">\r\n	In the present market scenario, inflation has become a permanent feature of economy throughout the world. In this paper we have proposed an inventory system of deteriorating items with time varying holding cost under inflationary environment. Most of the inventory faces the problem of deterioration which decreases the total profit. To control the rate of deterioration preservation technology techniques is used. In the proposed inventory model demand is ramp type and shortages are allowed and partially backlogged with constant backlogging rate. Due to ramp type demand, this inventory system is divided into two inventory models. Both inventory models have been solved by using distinct numerical examples. Also the concavity of the objective function for each model has been shown. Finally, the sensitiv