quo;</strong>Lot-sizing for inventory systems with product recovery&rdquo;, <em>Computers &amp; Industrial Engineering</em>, 46(3), 431&ndash;441.</p>\r\n',' Inventory, Green Supply Chain, Short Life cycle products.\r\n ','  Jaivindra Tomar ',' 1-15  ','YES','Vol 13 issue 1 ITMSC 2020.pdf','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','70','115','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',1,'arvindtomermaths@gmail.com',' Department of Mathematics, V.V.(P.G.) College, Shamli ','','pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1490,'<p>\r\n	EFFECT OF RAMP TYPE DEMAND ON PRODUCTION INVENTORY MODEL</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	In the classical inventory models, the demand rate is regularly assumed to be either constant or time-dependent but ramp type demand is very realistic demand pattern which follows behavior of all business situation. In this paper, we developed a production inventory model with ramp type demand. To validate this model numerically we used Mathematica software 12.0. Sensitivity analysis is carried out to see the behavior of different parameter on optimal solution</p>\r\n','<p style=\"margin-left:.5in;\">\r\n	1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deng, P.S., Lin, R.H.J. and Chu, P. (2007), &ldquo;A note on the inventory models for deteriorating items with ramp type demand&rdquo;,E.J.O.R., 178, 112-120.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:.5in;\">\r\n	2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Giri, B.C., Jalan, A.K. and Chaudhuri, K.S. (2003), &ldquo;Economic order quantity model with Weibull distribution deterioration, shortage and ramp-type demand&rdquo;, I.J.S.S., 34(4), 237-243.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:.5in;\">\r\n	3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Goswami, A. and Chaudhuri, K.S. (1991), &ldquo;An EOQ model for deteriorating items with a linear trend in demand&rdquo;, J.O.R.S., 42(12), 1105-1110.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:.5in;\">\r\n	4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Goyal, S.K. (1986), &ldquo;On improving replenishment policies for linear trend in demand&rdquo;, Engineering cost