003), &lsquo;An EOQ Model for Deteriorating Items Under Supplier Credits Linked to Ordering Quantity&rsquo;, Applied Mathematical Modeling,27, 983-996</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Chang, C.T. , and Wu, S.J. (2003), &lsquo;A Note on &ldquo;Optimal Payment Time Under Permissible Delay in Payment forProducts with Deterioration&rdquo;, Production Planning &amp; Control, 14,478-482.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		De, S.K., and Goswami, A. (2006), &lsquo;An EOQ Model with Fuzzy Inflation Rate and Fuzzy Deterioration Rate when a Delay in Payment is Permissible&rsquo;, International Journal of Systems Science,37, 323-335.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Goyal, S.K., and Giri, B.C. (2001), &lsquo;Recent Trends in Modeling of Deteriorating Inventory&rsquo;, European Journal of Operational Research,134, 335-338.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Hou, K.L., and Lin, L.C. (2006), &lsquo;An EOQ Model for Deteriorating Items with Price and Stock-dependent Selling Rates Under Inflation and Time Value of Money&rsquo;. International Journal of Systems Science, 37, 1131-1139.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Huang, Y-F. (2005), &lsquo;Buyer&rsquo;s Optimal Ordering Policy and Payment Policy Under Supplier Credit&rsquo;, International Journal of Systems Science, 36, 801-807.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Huang, Y-F., and Huang, H.F. (2008), &lsquo;Optimal Inventory Replenishment Policy for the EPQ Model Under Trade Credit Derived Without Derivatives&rsquo;, International Journal of Systems Science, 39, 539-546.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Liao, H.C., Tsai, C.H., and Su, C.T, (2000), &lsquo;An Inventory Model with Deteriorating Items Under Inflation when a Delay in Payment is Permissible&rsquo;, International Journal of Production Economics, 63,207-214.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ouyang, L.Y., Chang, C.T., and Teng, J.T., (2005), &lsquo;An EOQ Model for Deteriorating Items Under Trade Credits&rsquo;, Journal of the Operational Research Society, 56,719-726.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ouyang, L.Y., Teng, J.T., and Chen, L.H. (2006), &lsquo;Optimal Ordering Policy for Deteriorating Items