NULL),(1498,'<p>\r\n	A Review of Two Warehouse Model with Volume Elasticity and Reliability Consideration</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	Inventory management of produced, remanufactured/ repaired items has been in receipt of emergent attention in recent years. Demand uncertainty is another challenging but most important issue in inventory management. So, we consider a model with volume elasticity and reliability of the production process. All items are subjected to inspection and defective items are going in remanufacturing. The unit cost of production is inversely related to both process reliability and demand rate. Capacity of own ware house is limited. Production and demand are taken to be fuzzy in nature. Numerical illustration is given for the optimality of the cost functions</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	Chang, H.C., Yao, J.S., Ouyang, L.Y., (2004), &ldquo;Fuzzy mixture inventory model with variable lead-time based on probabilistic fuzzy set and triangular fuzzy number&rdquo;, Mathematical and Computer Modelling, 39, 2-3, 287-304.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chang, H.C., Yao, J.S., Ouyang, L.Y., (2006), &ldquo;Fuzzy mixture inventory model involving fuzzy random variable lead time demand and fuzzy total demand&rdquo;, European Journal of Operational Research, 169, 1, 65-80.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;Dey, J.K., Kar, S., Maiti, M., (2005), &ldquo;An interactive method for inventory control with fuzzy lead-time and dynamic demand&rdquo;, European Journal of Operational Research, 167, 2,381- 397.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;Hartely, R.V. (1976), &ldquo;Operations Research-A managerial emphasis&rdquo;, Good year publishing company, California, 315-317.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;Rosenblatt, M.J., Lee, H.L., (1986), &ldquo;Economic production cycles with imperfect production processes&rdquo;, International Industrial Engineers Transactions, 14, 48-55.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;Porteus, E.L., (1986), &ldquo;Optimal lot sizing, process quality improvement and setup cost reduction&rdquo;, Operations Research, 34,137-144.</p>\r\n