ICM.2018.7101 ','pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1502,' An economic production lot-sizing model for deteriorating items with partial backlogging under the effect of learning','<div>\r\n	In this article we have developed an economic production lot-sizing model in infinite horizon. Deterioration is taken into consideration. Shortages is allowed and partially backlogged and the backlogging rate is taken to be waiting time dependent. To make the system more realistic, the effect of</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	learning is also considered. A mathematical formulation has been done. Theoretical results are illustrated with a numerical example. Sensitivity analysis is also given.</div>\r\n','<div>\r\n	1. Abad, P.L., (1996) &ldquo;Optimal pricing and lot-sizing under conditions of perishability and partial backlogging&rdquo;, Management Science; 42(8), 1093-1104.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	2. Abad, P.L., (2001). &ldquo;Optimal price and order size for a reseller under partial backordering&rdquo;, Computers &amp; Operations Research; 28, 53-65.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	3. Chang, C.T., Goyal, S. K. and Teng, J.T. (2006-a), &ldquo;On an EOQ model for perishable items under stock-dependent selling rate and time-dependent partial backlogging&rdquo;, European Journal of Operational Research; 174(2), 923-929.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	4. Chang, H.J., Teng, J.T., Ouyang, L.Y. and Dye, C.Y. (2006-b). &ldquo;Retailer&rsquo;s optimal pricing and lot-sizing policies for deteriorating items with partial backlogging&rdquo;, European Journal of Operational Research; 168(1), 51-64.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	5. Chu, P. and Chung, K.J. (2004). &ldquo;The sensitivity of the inventory model with partial backorders&rdquo;, European Journal of Operational Research; 152, 289-295.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	6. Dye, C.Y., Hsieh, T.P., Ouyang, L.Y. (2007). &ldquo;Determining optimal selling price and lot size with a varying rate of deterioration and exponential partial backlogging&rdquo;, European Journal of Operational Research; 181(2), 668-67