ance systems employ this technology extensively. Object detection is the first step in the process, wherein computer vision algorithms locate and identify things within individual video frames. This may entail methods like region-based Convolutional Neural Network (Faster R-CNN) or YOLO (You Only Look Once), which are object detection models based on deep learning. Based on the object&#39;s past trajectory, the tracking algorithm assists in predicting the object&#39;s position in the frame.</p>\r\n','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		E. Hjelm&aring;s and B. K. Low, &ldquo;Face detection: A survey,&rdquo; Comput. Vis. Image Underst., vol. 83, no. 3, pp. 236&ndash;274, 2001, doi: 10.1006/cviu.2001.0921.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A. Zimman, J. A. Berliner, and T. G. Graeber, &ldquo;Phosphoproteomic analysis of aortic endothelial cells activated by oxidized phospholipids,&rdquo; Methods Mol. Biol., vol. 1000, no. June, pp. 53&ndash;69, 2013, doi: 10.1007/978-1-62703-405-0_5.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		H. Jiang and E. Learned-Miller, &ldquo;Face Detection with the Faster R-CNN,&rdquo; Proc. - 12th IEEE Int. Conf. Autom. Face Gesture Recognition, FG 2017 - 1st Int. Work. Adapt. Shot Learn. Gesture Underst. Prod. ASL4GUP 2017, Biometrics Wild, Bwild 2017, Heterog. Face Recognition, HFR 2017, Jt. Chall. Domin. Complement. Emot. Recognit. Using Micro Emot. Featur. Head-Pose Estim. DCER HPE 2017 3rd Facial Expr. Recognit. Anal. Challenge, FERA 2017, pp. 650&ndash;657, 2017, doi: 10.1109/FG.2017.82.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		L. Garrido, B. Duchaine, and K. Nakayama, &ldquo;Face detection in normal and prosopagnosic individuals.,&rdquo; J. Neuropsychol., vol. 2, no. Pt 1, pp. 119&ndash;140, 2008, doi: 10.1348/174866407X246843.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		D. Geman, &ldquo;Coarse-to-Fine Face Detection,&rdquo; vol. 41, pp. 85&ndash;107, 2001.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		P. Gebert, A. Roitberg, M. Haurilet, and R. Stiefelhagen, &ldquo;End-to-end prediction of driver intention using 3D convolutional neural networks,&rdquo; IEEE Intell.