p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:25.1pt;\">\r\n	9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Singh, S. R., &amp; Rana, K. (2023). A sustainable production inventory model for growing items with trade credit policy under partial backlogging.&nbsp;<em>International Journal of Advanced Operations Management</em>,&nbsp;<em>15</em>(1), 64-81.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:25.1pt;\">\r\n	10.&nbsp; Tayal, S., Singh, S. R., &amp; Sharma, R. (2014). A multi item inventory model for deteriorating items with expiration date and allowable shortages. <em>Indian Journal of Science and Technology</em>, <em>7</em>(4), 463&ndash;471. https://doi.org/10.17485/ijst/2014/v7i4.17</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:25.1pt;\">\r\n	11.&nbsp; Tayal, S., Singh, S. R., Sharma, R., &amp; Chauhan, A. (2014). Two echelon supply chain model for deteriorating items with effective investment in preservation technology. <em>International Journal of Mathematics in Operational Research</em>, <em>6</em>(1), 84. https://doi.org/10.1504/ijmor.2014.057854</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:25.1pt;\">\r\n	12.&nbsp; Tiwari, S., C&aacute;rdenas-Barr&oacute;n, L. E., Iqbal Malik, A., &amp; Jaggi, C. K. (2022). Retailer&rsquo;s credit and inventory decisions for imperfect quality and deteriorating items under two-level trade credit. <em>Computers &amp;amp; Operations Research</em>, <em>138</em>, 105617. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cor.2021.105617</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:25.1pt;\">\r\n	13.&nbsp; Vandana, Singh, S. R., Yadav, D., Sarkar, B., &amp; Sarkar, M. (2021). Impact of energy and carbon emission of a supply chain management with two-level trade-credit policy. <em>Energies</em>, <em>14</em>(6), 1569.<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.3390/en14061569\">https://doi.org/10.3390/en14061569</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:25.1pt;\">\r\n	14.&nbsp; Wee, H. M., &amp; Law, S. T. (2001). Replenishment and pricing policy for deteriorating items taking into account the time-value of money.&nbsp;<em>International Journal of Production Economics</em>,&nbsp;<em>71</em>(1-3), 213-220.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:25.1pt;\">\r\n	15.&nbsp; Yang, C. T., Dye, C. Y., &amp; Ding, J. F. (2015). Optimal dynamic trade credit and preservation technology allocation for a deteriorating inventory model.&nbsp;<em>Computers &amp; Industrial Engineering</em>,&nbsp;<em>87</em>, 356-369.</p>\r\n','Trade Credit; Multivariate demand; Shortage',' Sanjeev Kumar, Jaivindra Tomar',' 65-84','NO','No file','International Journal of Science and Engineering','92','145','2024-01-29 10:20:41','E',10,'sanjeevkumarbsr56@gmail.com','Department of Mathematics, DAV College, Bulandshahr, Uttar Pradesh, India','https://doi.org/10.58517/IJSE.2023.2202','pending',NULL,NULL,'subscription',NULL),(1512,' An Analytical Study of the Eight Mathematical Operations in Ganit Yukti Bhasa','<p>\r\n	Written by the Indian astronomer Jyesthadeva in 1530, Ganit Yukti Bhasa (Rationales in Mathematical Astronomy) is a seminal treatise that combines the profound knowledge of mathematics and astronomy. This work represents a comprehensive consolidation of the discoveries made by the astronomers and mathematicians of the Kerala School, originally composed in Malayalam and later translated by C.M. Whish. This essay provides a review of the eight mathematical operations detailed in Ganit Yukti Bhasa. The work was further expanded with explanatory notes by K. Ramasubramanian, M. D. Srinivas, and M. S. Sriram, and was critically edited, with an English translation, by K.V. Sarma.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	1. A History of the Kerala School of Hindu Astronomy and the Bibliography of Kerala and Keralabased Astronomy and Astrology. Both by K. V. Sarma, Vishveshvaranand Institute, Sadhu Ashram, Hoshiarpur, (Punjab), 1972.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2. Science Texts in Sanskrit in the Manuscripts Repositories of Kerala and Tamilnadu (K. V. Sarma, Rashtriya Sanskrit Sansthan, New Delhi, 2002).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3. The Methodology of Indian Mathematicians and its Contemporary Relevance, PPST Bulletin, Madras, No.12, Sept. 1987, 1-35.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	4. S.R. Singh, Rashmi Yadav at al., A Review of Brahmagupta&#39;s Contributions, International Journal for Multidisciplinary Research (IJFMR), Volume 6, Issue 3, May-June 2024.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	5. Aryabhatyabhas.a by Nlakantha Somayaj (1443-1560).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	6. Rashmi Yadav (2021) at al., Some Important Comparison by Vedic and Modern Method, Conference Proceedings RDMOCS.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	7. Ganitayuktayah. (27 rationalistic tracts culled from Mss. and edited under the above common title, by K. V. Sarma, Hoshiarpur, 1979).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	8. Siddhanta Darpana vyakhya by Nilakantha Somayaj (1443-1560) Ed. K. V. Sarma.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	9. Rashmi Yadav (2021) at al., Comparison of Vedic and Modern Maths in Forward Difference by Meru-Prastar, Volume 7, Issue 5, IJARIIT.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	10. Grahamadhyamayuktayah, Sahasradinanam, in 8 verses, by Puradahanapuradvija Parame&acute;svara.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	11. Tantrasangraha of Nlakantha Somayaj, Ed. with two commentaries, Yuktidpika and Laghuvivrti, both by Sankara, by K. V. Sarma, Vishveshvaranand Institute, Hoshiarpur, 1977.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	12. Sarma, K.V. and Narasimhan, V.S.:Text and Translation of Tantrasangraha of Nlakantha Somayaj, Supplement to the Indian Journal of History of Science, (INSA, New Delhi), 33 (1998), pp.148.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Astronomy, Mathematical Analysis, Mathematical operations ',' 1 Muskan Vishnoi, 2S.R. Singh, 3* Rashmi Yadav',' 1-7','YES','muskan itmsc (1) (1).pdf','International Transactions in Mathematical Sciences and Computer','95','150','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',1,'rashmi.y94@gmail.com',' Department of Mathematics, Vardhaman College Bijnor','','pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1513,'<p>\r\n	On Some Integral Relations involving N-Function with Applications</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	<em>In an attempt to give extensions of the results in the theory of special functions, we have established two integr