 Sciences and Computer','97','152','2026-02-17 16:47:49','E',1,'rashmi.y94@gmail.com',' Department of Mathematics, Vardhaman College Bijnor','','pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1516,' Benefits of Preservation Technology on Inventory Model for COVID-19 Disaster Relief deteriorating item with price and stock dependent demand and variable holding cost under inflation','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n	<span lang=\"EN-US\">Owing to the COVID-19 pandemic disaster, there are unimaginable hazards to the survival of human society and the business world. The COVID-19 disaster influence directly affects customer&#39;s ability to make purchases. A customer&#39;s desire for products declines when his ability to make purchases is reduced. Again, Retailers and suppliers of deteriorating items face risks in this disaster market due to the short duration of shelf life of COVID-19 disaster relief items. To keep their commercial profession alive in this situation, they had to have a suitable business plan. An inventory model for deteriorating&nbsp;items with price and stock-dependent demand and preservation technologies under carbon emission is developed by taking all of these elements into consideration. When there is a shortage, demand is solely influenced by the item&#39;s price .This model takes into account fully backlogged shortages, time-dependent deterioration, variable holding costs, and the effects of inflation. A numerical example is given with the software MATHEMATICA 12.0 to show the model&#39;s efficacy. To display the behavior of the various parameters in an optimal solution, sensitivity analysis is carried out.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	Ahmad, Naeem, <em>et al</em>.,A green realistic inventory model with preservation technology for deteriorating items under carbon emission,&nbsp;<em>Materials Today: Proceedings</em>&nbsp;<strong>2023</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Bhawaria, Sushil, and Himanshu Rathore ,Economic production quantity model for deteriorating ite