ature and concentration profile. The equations of momentum, flow, thermal and concentration aspects have been governed as per the physical aspects considered for this research. Suitable similarity variables are applied to simplify the momentum equation and to alter the remaining governing equations to non linear ordinary differential equations for solution. The complex system of equations is evaluated by the R-K Felhberg (Runge -Kutta Fifth order) method based on the shooting technique. This work examines the heat and mass transfer rate for the various profiles viz. velocity, temperature, concentration for different values of the skin friction constraint, Nusselt quantity, and Sherwood quantity.</p>\r\n','<p style=\"margin-left:14.2pt;\">\r\n	1.&nbsp;&nbsp; Abderrahmane, A., Jamshed, W., Abed, A. M., Smaisim, G. F., Guedri, K., Devi, S. U., Akbari, O. A., Younis, O., &amp; Baghaei, S. (2022). Heat and mass transfer analysis of non-Newtonian power-law nanofluid confined within annulus enclosure using Darcy-Brinkman-Forchheimer model. <em>Case Studies in Thermal Engineering</em>, <em>40</em>. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.csite.2022.102569</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:14.2pt;\">\r\n	2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Amani, M., Amani, P., Bahiraei, M., Ghalambaz, M., Ahmadi, G., Wang, L. P., Wongwises, S., &amp; Mahian, O. (2021). Latest developments in nanofluid flow and heat transfer between parallel surfaces: A critical review. In <em>Advances in Colloid and Interface Science</em> (Vol. 294). Elsevier B.V. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cis.2021.102450</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:14.2pt;\">\r\n	3. Anwar, M. I., Firdous, H., Zubaidi, A. Al, Abbas, N., &amp; Nadeem, S. (2022). Computational analysis of induced magnetohydrodynamic non-Newtonian nanofluid flow over nonlinear stretching sheet. <em>Progress in Reaction Kinetics and Mechanism</em>, <em>47</em>. https://doi.org/10.1177/14686783211072712</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:14.2pt;\">\r\n	4. Atofarati, E. O., Sharifpur, M., &amp; Hua