ection</strong></p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	In this publication, we explore the hypersurfaces of a Riemannian manifold with a quarter symmetric semi-metric connection. Furthermore, we show that the induced connection is a semi-metric connection with quarter symmetry. We consider the minimality, total geodesicness, and total umbilicity of a hypersurface of a Riemannian manifold with a quarter symmetric semi-metric connection. We obtain the Gauss, Weingarten, and Codazzi equations for the quarter symmetric semi-metric connection. Additionally given is the connection between the sectional curvatures of and +1 with regard to the quarter symmetric semimetric connection.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	1 .T. Imai, Notes on semi-symmetric metric connection. Tensor, 24 (1972), pp. 293-296.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2 .Agashe, S. Nirmala and M.R. Chaffle, A semi-symmetric non-metric connection on a Riemannian manifold. Indian J. Pure and Appl. Math, 23(1992) pp. 399-409.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3 .B. Barua, and S. Mukhopadhyay, A sequence of semi-symmetric connection on a Riemannian manifold. Proceedings of seventh national seminar on Finsler Lagrange and Hamilton space, Brasov, Romannia (1992).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	4. S. Golab, On semi-symmetric and quarter symmetric connection. Tensor N.S., 29 (1975), pp. 249-254.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	5. R.S. Mishra and S. N. Pandey, On quarter symmetric metric F-connections. N. S. Tensor, 34 (1980), pp. 1-7.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	6. K. Yano, T. Imai, Quarter symmetric metric connections and their curvature tensors, Tensor (N.S.), 38 (1982), pp.13-18.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	7. M. Ahmad, J.B. Jun, Shamsur Rahman and A. Haseeb, On almost r-parcontact Riemannian manifold with certain connection, Communications of the Korean Mathematical Society 25 (2) (2010), pp. 235-243. doi : 10.4134/CKMS.2010.25.2.235 MR2662972.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	8. M. Ahmad, S. Rahman and S. Rizvi, Submanifolds of an almost r-paracontact Riemannian manifold endowed with quarter symmetric semi-metric connection. Bulletin of Calcutta Mathematical