','pending',NULL,NULL,'open',NULL),(1547,'<p>\r\n	Stochastic Modeling of a Robot Safety System with Standby, Imperfect Switching and Common Cause Shock Failure</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	The current research explores a robot safety system that includes standby robot units together with imperfect switching mechanisms and the effects of common cause shock failure. The system contains an active robot and several operational standby units while it also features safety equipment. .The switching of standby robot units may be imperfect sometimes, the observable fact is known as imperfect switching. The system fails because of shock failure alongside other unit failures. Analysis of state transition diagrams enables researchers to establish multiple system performance measures by using obtained probabilities. A numerical experiment validates the developed model.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<p style=\"margin-left:.5in;\">\r\n	<strong>1.&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong>Cui, Y., Tao, Y. and Li, Z. (2023): Research on the Reliability of a Two-Robot Security System with Early Warning Function, J. Mathematics, Vol. 2023, Article ID 3214866, 20 pages, <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1155/2023/3214866\">https://doi.org/10.1155/2023/3214866</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:.5in;\">\r\n	<strong>2.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Dhillon, B. S. and Cheng, S. (2008): Probabilistic analysis of a repairable robot-safety system composed of (<em>n - </em>1) standby robots, a safety unit, and a switch, J. Quality Maintenance Engg., Vol. 14, No. 3, pp. 306-323.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:.5in;\">\r\n	<strong>3.&nbsp; </strong>Dhillon, B. S. and Li, Z. (2004):Stochastic analysis of a maintainable robot-safety system with common-cause failures,J. Quality Maintenance Engg., Vol. 10, No. 2, pp. 136-147.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:.5in;\">\r\n	<strong>4.&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong>Hajeeh, M. A. (2011):&nbsp;Reliability and availability of a standby system with common cause failure, Int. J. Oper. Res., Vol. 11, No. 3, pp. 343-36